10001394-null-.name: The Call of the Minister
10001394-null-.desc: $npc:11000119$ said that $npc:11000074$ made an order to recommend a person that could be trusted with the utmost confidentiality. I was told to go to $map:02000065$ and meet $npc:11000074$.

10001400-null-.name: The Minister's Request
10001400-null-.desc:
After hearing what $npc:11000074$ said, I remember finding $item:30000174$ among the wreckage of the stolen royal carriage while chasing the red cape in $map:02000238$. At that time, $npc:11000119$ and $npc:11000074$ didn't speak much and only provided some vague answers after seeing $item:30000174$... After all, what could these two know?
Let's first go to $map:02000218$ in $map:02000001$ and look for the picture $npc:11000074$ asked for.

10001401-null-.name: The Vid-Bleim Mansion
10001401-null-.desc:
What could have happened in the Vid-Bleim family?
$npc:11000074$, $npc:11000119$, and even $npc:11000530$...
The fact that everyone is giving off such a tense vibe is making me a bit suspicious.
What kind of stories will I hear if I bring back the picture to $npc:11000074$?
Let's go to $map:02000190$ in $map:02000119$.

10001402-null-.name: A Daughter's Face
10001402-null-.desc:
$npc:11000058$ was left alone to watch over $map:02000190$. Observing $npc:11000058$'s mood, there seems to be a silent but profound pain between her and her father $npc:11000074$... Why did $npc:11000074$ order this portrait...?
Take the $item:30000182$ you received from $npc:11000058$ and return to $map:02000065$.

10001410-null-.name: Comprehending the Situation
10001410-null-.desc:
$npc:11000044$ asked for assistance in finding $npc:11000069$, who has gone missing.
Typically level-headed $npc:11000044$ is exhibiting an impatience you've never seen before, as she does not want to lose $npc:11000069$ to $npc:11000522$, just like her father and previous leader Win Stilton had in the past. Could $npc:11000522$ really have kidnapped $npc:11000069$?

10001411-null-.name: QUESTDESCRIPTION_10001411_NAME
10001411-null-.desc: $npc:11000258$ says that $npc:11000531$, who resents the Dark Wind, is not divulging any details regarding the disappearance of $npc:11000069$, and told me to go talk to $npc:11000531$ if I want more details.

10001412-null-.name: Start of the Clue
10001412-null-.desc: It's going to be difficult gaining any more useful information from $npc:11000531$. However, carefully tracking $npc:11000069$'s movement before the disappearance may lead to more clues that could become invaluable for this search.
10001412-null-.complete: Look for any clues between $item:39000012$ and $item:39000013$, and enter investigative questioning

10001413-null-.name: Deadliest Part-Time Job
10001413-null-.desc:
$npc:11000532$ says that he was paid from a person he never met to merely borrow and return books. Just exactly who paid $npc:11000532$ to do this job? Could that person be connected to $npc:11000069$ disappearance?
I still don't see how all of the clues I have really fit together, but I have no choice but to follow each clue like a trail of bread crumbs and continue my search...

10001414-null-.name: A Surreptitious Pursuit
10001414-null-.desc:
$npc:11000301$ didn't see anyone suspicious looking in the area, but did mention that there is an area below the moving bone bridge in $map:02000045$ that hasn't started construction and could be a perfect place for someone to hide.
If this person went through such great lengths to stay hidden, what $npc:11000301$ said about dark and hidden places is likely to be true, and these locations could possibly unearth some vital clues.
10001414-null-.manual: Look for the hideout beneath the moving bone bridge in $map:02000045$

10001415-null-.name: Perion and Yamarcha
10001415-null-.desc:
You found the words Yamarcha and $map:02000051$ written on the dusty walls of $map:02000223$.
I'm pretty sure $map:02000051$ is the name of a location,
but Yamarcha... What could that mean...?
Would the people in $map:02000051$ know the meaning behind this?
10001415-null-.complete: Go to $map:02000051$ and find out what Yamarcha means

10001416-null-.name: The Pursuit of Meaning
10001416-null-.desc:
$npc:11000018$ apologized for not knowing what Yamarcha means, but was still helpful enough to refer me to $npc:11000136$.
$npcName:11000136$, a unique girl that can tame savage wolves as if they were mere puppies... Could she possibly know what Yamarcha means?

10001440-null-.name: Holding Back Reinforcements
10001440-null-.desc:
$npc:11000119$ suddenly held back the $map:02000146$ Defender reinforcements, even though $npc:11000044$ is leading the Dark Wind.
Suspending the Defender reinforcements out of nowhere like this... Could there have been a more dangerous and urgent situation than the protection of $map:02000146$?

10001580-null-.name: Praise the Pigming
10001580-null-.desc:
$npc:11000136$ asked me to fill the $item:30000086$ in $map:02000077$, and take it to $npc:11000039$ in $map:02000049$.
Would $npc:11000039$ know about Yamarcha?

10001581-null-.name: Enemy of the Pigming
10001581-null-.desc:
$npc:11000039$ explained that the Yamarcha was one of the tribes that existed in ancient Perion, and asked me to stop the Inakimos that were prowling around the altar attempting to interrupt the Pigmings' tribal activities.
Let's go to $map:02000049$ and defeat the strange $npc:21000332$ and $npc:21000333$, who were continuously flapping their wings, and return to $npc:11000039$ to learn more about the Yamarcha.

10001582-null-.name: Murpagoth's Eagle
10001582-null-.desc:
$npc:11000039$ relays the story of the Yamarcha's insatiable lust for power, and their subsequent decline after falling for a demon's trap.
Yamarcha...the only clue that was left in $map:02000223$...
The answer is still shrouded in mystery.
Will I be able to find $npc:11000069$ using only this clue?
I wish Perion's chief $npc:11000069$ would return soon since he is the only person I feel is capable of unraveling this mystery, thanks to his vast knowledge about the Yamarcha...
There are five Murpagoth's eagles in $map:02000049$. The eagles all sit along the edges of the cliffs on the east, west, south, and north sides. I think it'd be a good idea to send an eagle to the chief!

10001830-null-.name: Prison Pen Pals
10001830-null-.desc: Unable to face $npc:11000526$, who has been connected to the death of $npc:11000492$, $npc:11000012$ of $map:02000001$ requested that a letter be delivered to $npc:11000526$, who is currently trapped in $map:02000310$.

10001831-null-.name: Nelph's Keepsake
10001831-null-.desc: $npc:11000526$, currently trapped in $map:02000310$, handed over $npc:11000492$'s keepsake, a tape containing an audio message from $npc:11000492$ for $npc:11000492$'s blind mother, and asked to have it delivered to $npc:11000178$ in $map:02000076$.

10001832-null-.name: Broken Promises
10001832-null-.desc:
Being blind, $npc:11000178$ gave $item:30000342$ back and asked to have the audio message be played for her.
Find the small audio player next to the bed in $map:02000198$ and play $item:30000342$.

10002060-null-.name: Red Dead Witness
10002060-null-.desc:
$map:02000001$'s $npc:11000119$ said that the red caped man was found at $map:02000117$, counterattacking with $npc:23000008$ when $npc:23000001$ fell in combat.
The search began quickly after the report came in, but there has been no news from the guards themselves... Did something happen to them?
No time to waste! Go find out what happened at $map:02000117$!

10002061-null-.name: Traversing the Cliff Cave
10002061-null-.desc:
$map:02000117$'s $npc:11000549$ saw the guards locked in fierce combat at $map:02000238$ below the cliff.
$map:02000238$ is now unusually still and quiet... Just exactly happened there?
Return to $map:02000117$'s $map:02000238$.

10002062-null-.name: Battle of Cliff Cave
10002062-null-.desc:
$npc:11000551$, who fell in $map:02000238$, could no longer continue speaking due to the immense pain.
$map:02000238$ seems to be a trap set for the red cape's pursuers.
I can lend a hand to the guards who are currently engaged in an intense battle with the monsters from $map:02000238$.
10002062-null-.manual: Take care of the monsters at $map:02000117$'s $map:02000238$

10002063-null-.name: The Color Green
10002063-null-.desc:
You managed to discover $item:30000174$ from a broken wagon deep inside $map:02000238$.
Ask $npc:11000551$ to find out more information about it.
10002063-null-.manual: Pick up $item:30000174$ from the $npc:11000550$ wreck at $map:02000117$'s $map:02000238$

10002100-null-.name: Harbinger of Doom
10002100-null-.desc:
When the Royal Guard came to check her safety, $npc:11000058$'s intuition told her that something had happened to $npc:11000074$. Was she right in thinking that something bad had happened...?
Let's go to $map:02000001$'s $npc:11000119$ and learn what exactly transpired.

10002101-null-.name: Chasing Footprints
10002101-null-.desc:
$npc:11000119$ seems to place great priority on the value of justice. As $npc:11000119$ said, the world is full of disagreements, and  everyone has their own personal reasons for their own perspective. I suppose then it does make sense that some people would see merit in the concept of sacrificing the few for the good of the many...
$npc:11000075$ must also have carefully considered the options after $npc:11000057$ returned as a servant of evil...
Let's trust $npc:11000075$ for now and join the Royal Guard Chasers following $npc:11000057$ as $npc:11000119$ says.
10002101-null-.complete: Find the Royal Guard Chasers at $map:02000053$

10002102-null-.name: Endless Pursuit
10002102-null-.desc:
I saw $npc:11000602$ collapsed in the alleyway in $map:02000053$, which leads to $map:02000090$. He seemed to be more concerned about the other members who were hot on the tail of the red-caped figure.
Let's head to $map:02000090$ before anything else.
10002102-null-.complete: Find the Royal Guard Chasers at $map:02000090$

10002103-null-.name: Inside the Forest of Chaos
10002103-null-.desc:
Deep inside $map:02000090$, the Royal Guard Chasers were found collapsed and severely injured near the entrance of $map:02000206$. $npc:11000603$ was still somewhat conscious, and said that $npc:23000025$ emerged from the deep, dark $map:02000206$ to protect the red cape from the Royal Guard Chasers.
Let's not take any chances and head to $map:02000001$ to report to $npc:11000119$ and request for backup.

10002104-null-.name: The Fog Sets In
10002104-null-.desc: As $npc:23000025$'s punishment is prepared, $npc:11000119$ requested that the $npc:11000057$'s news be delivered to $npc:11000075$.

10002105-null-.name: Conflicting Hearts
10002105-null-.desc:
$npc:11000075$'s resolve to return to $npc:11000057$ seems to be unshaken. Despite the difficult decision, even for $npcTitle:11000075$, who is essentially the guardian of Maple World, her firm determination is a testament to her unbreakable will.
How will $npc:11000074$ respond to $npcTitle:11000075$'s resolve...?

10002110-null-.name: Know Thy Enemy
10002110-null-.desc:
In order to defeat $npc:23000025$, the Royal Guards have been collecting all sorts of information. $npcName:11000169$ wants to make up for not having been able to properly protect the armory, but his timid personality that makes him shy and fidgety in front of women is worrisome.
Let's go to $map:02000031$ in $npc:11000169$'s place and retrieve the Book of Shadow Healing from $npc:11000005$.

10002111-null-.name: The Book of Legends
10002111-null-.desc: $map:02000031$'s $npc:11000005$ said that more can be learned about the Book of Shadow Healing from $map:02000023$'s $npc:11000033$.

10002112-null-.name: Apollo the Genius
10002112-null-.desc:
$npc:11000033$ said that the last person who read the Book of Shadow Healing, $npc:11000604$, might remember the contents of the tome.
Let's look for $npc:11000604$ at $map:02000023$'s $map:02000109$.

10002113-null-.name: A Fastidious Demand
10002113-null-.desc:
$npc:11000604$ will share the information related to $npc:23000025$ from Book of Shadow Healing...if I bring $item:30000179$.
Let's defeat $npc:22090107$, often found in $map:02000112$ near $map:02000023$, and bring back $item:30000179$.

10002114-null-.name: The Brothers Grim
10002114-null-.desc:
Here are the passages in the Book of Shadow Healing pertaining to the Baphomet Brothers...

"The Baphomet Brothers were immensely powerful demons who were able to open their eyes and see through the darkness of the Demon King.
The eldest, $npc:23000026$ was filled with unspeakable evil,
the second, $npc:23000025$ was overflowing with wickedness,
and the third, $npc:23000024$ was consumed with pure insanity, annihilating everything in its wake.
$npc:23000025$ was the one responsible for engulfing $map:02000023$ with darkness and chaos...which is why it is now called $map:02000206$.
As the source of chaos overwhelming the forest stems $item:30000190$, once $npc:23000025$ loses control of it, only then will the Shadow of Chaos be diminished."

There appears to be even more information, but much of the text has withered away...

10002120-null-.name: Wisdom of a Sage
10002120-null-.desc: $npc:11000075$ said that $map:02000023$'s $npc:11000031$ might be able to find a way to rescue $npc:11000057$, and asked me to deliver a letter.

10002121-null-.name: Library of the Forest
10002121-null-.desc: $npc:11000031$ told me to find $map:02000019$ in $map:02000019$ and bring back $item:30000191$ from $npc:11000282$.
10002121-null-.complete: Find and enter $map:02000019$ in $map:02000215$ to meet with $npc:11000282$

10002122-null-.name: Curse of Akabonari
10002122-null-.desc:
$npc:11000282$ was finicky for a long time. Looking for the hidden $map:02000219$ in a library this large...
Guess I don't have much of a choice.
Since it's been said that $map:02000219$ is hidden behind a bookcase, let's first find the bookcases that can be moved in $map:02000019$ and try pushing them.
10002122-null-.manual: Find $map:02000219$ hidden behind a bookcase in $map:02000019$ | Find $item:30000191$ in $map:02000219$

10002130-null-.name: Confirming the Legend
10002130-null-.desc:
$map:02000019$'s $npc:11000282$ said that in order to obtain $item:30000191$, I must find Hephaestus's travel log, figure out where he hid $item:30000184$, and bring $item:30000184$ back.
As it is somewhat of a convoluted request, there is no time to waste, especially considering the urgency at which $npc:11000031$ wants $item:30000191$ back.
Let's first search the bookshelves in $map:02000019$ for Hephaestus's travel log!
10002130-null-.manual: Search $map:02000019$'s bookshelves to find $item:39000008$ | Go to the marked location on $item:39000008$ and find $item:30000184$

10002140-null-.name: Witchin' Treasure
10002140-null-.desc:
Considering all the difficulty $npc:11000282$ went through in order to obtain $item:30000191$, I guess it shouldn't be a surprise that analyzing the contents have also taken an excruciatingly long time. Fortunately, the everything that's been learned thus far made it clear that $item:30000187$ is necessary.
$item:30000187$, the treasure of the witches that is passed from one generation to the next... Can it be obtained?

10002141-null-.name: Orb of Souls
10002141-null-.desc:
$npc:11000304$ divulged the hidden location of $item:30000187$, and imparted some particularly deep and profound messages.
Although I can't seem to get $npcName:11000304$'s messages out of my mind, let's try to push that to the side and find $item:30000187$ first before returning.
Let's also find the fairy $npcName:11000284$ in the center of $map:02000006$'s large lake and look around the pink-leafed tree for the hidden passageway that goes under the lake. The jar hidden in the bottom of the lake contains $item:30000187$.
10002141-null-.manual: Find $item:30000187$ at the bottom of $map:02000006$'s lake

10002142-null-.name: You Can Never Be Too Careful
10002142-null-.desc:
Although $npc:11000031$ finished decoding $item:30000191$'s records and secured $item:30000187$, there seems to be a bigger issue at hand.
Using the witches' Soul Curse spell to save $npc:11000057$ runs the risk of throwing off balance one of the powers that drives this world, the balance of life itself.
What will $npcTitle:11000075$ decide to do...?
Let's return to $map:02000025$ and meet $npc:11000075$.

10002150-null-.name: What a Witch Wants
10002150-null-.desc:
As expected, $npc:11000304$ was not willing to lend out $item:30000187$ so easily.
Considering the circumstances, I guess I can't say I'm all that surprised.
Let's go to $map:02000113$ and bring $npc:21000266$'s prey, $item:30000072$.

10002160-null-.name: Specialized Order
10002160-null-.desc:
After careful deliberation, $npc:11000075$ ordered me to enter $map:02000220$.
It's possible that a live being entering $map:02000220$ can disturb the order of life... But if this is necessary to ensure the current world does not fall into confusion and chaos, then such an act should not be solely viewed as transgression against the very nature of life itself.
It's time to go to $map:02000023$ and meet $npc:11000031$.

10002170-null-.name: The Chief of Perion
10002170-null-.desc:
Perion Chief $npc:11000134$ has returned!
I should go meet with him and hear more about Yamarcha.

10002171-null-.name: Muphaza the Wolf King
10002171-null-.desc: I'll meet with $npc:11000078$ at $map:02000170$ as $npc:11000134$ said.

10002172-null-.name: Unexpected Discovery
10002172-null-.desc:
I found a suspicious bag in $map:02000229$...
My first instinct was that this was $npc:11000069$'s bag.
10002172-null-.manual: Find clues from the bag behind $map:02000229$'s altar

10002173-null-.name: A Heartwarming Reunion
10002173-null-.desc:
To meet $npc:11000407$ here, who regaled me with so many stories during the Maple Island days... The nostalgia warms my heart.
$npc:11000407$ shared everything, all the way from the first encounter with $npc:11000064$, to how $npc:11000064$ left for the Land of Darkness to save $npc:11000069$.
$npc:11000064$ left a letter for $npc:11000529$ before leaving!
I wonder what kind of message he left to one of his most dependable friends?
Let's go to $map:02000166$'s $map:02000208$ and deliver $item:30000340$ to $npc:11000529$.

10002174-null-.name: Unyielding Friendship
10002174-null-.desc:
$item:30000340$ contained a request for $npc:11000529$'s help, as $npc:11000069$ left alone for Katramus, the slave's tower.
Overjoyed at the news that $npc:11000064$ is still alive, $npc:11000529$ began preparing to leave for Katramus without a moment's hesitation. He left one piece of advice before he left...

"Remember, you still have time to listen to the entire story from $npc:11000064$ first before relaying the news of $npc:11000064$ to $npc:11000044$."

It is now up to me to decide how much should be reported to $npc:11000044$. Let's first go to $map:02000100$'s $map:02000152$ and meet $npc:11000044$.

10002180-null-.name: The Final Gift
10002180-null-.desc:
After sharing $map:02000229$'s location, $npc:11000078$ asked me to help free the trapped soul of his fallen friend, the Red Wolf King Machar.
Let's carefully take $item:30000076$ from $npc:11000078$ and travel to the entrance of $map:02000229$ in the red lands below the center of $map:02000170$.
10002180-null-.manual: Defeat the monsters at $map:02000229$ | Free Machar's soul with the embers of purification at $map:02000229$

10002190-null-.name: Witness Protection
10002190-null-.desc:
$npc:11000529$ could not help but show unbridled joy while meeting with $npc:11000064$ at Katramus.
Although it isn't completely credible, $npc:11000529$ said that there has been an anonymous informant who can reveal $npc:11000044$'s true identity, and that he must be found before the Dark Wind finds him.

10002191-null-.name: No Corner Left Behind
10002191-null-.desc:
$npc:11001021$ at $map:02000279$ requested that I conduct a thorough investigation of $map:02000307$.
I'll head to $map:02000307$'s entrance, which is right behind $npc:11001021$.
10002191-null-.manual: Enter through $map:02000307$'s entrance behind $npc:11001021$ and defeat the monsters

10002192-null-.name: Everybody Loves Raymon
10002192-null-.desc:
The anonymous informant from $map:02000279$... He was $npc:11000526$, thought to have been dead for a long time now.
$npc:11000526$ said that both the robbery of the armory and the death of $npc:11000492$ are $npc:11000044$'s doings, and that the proof can be found behind $map:02000226$'s wall clock.

10002193-null-.name: Decisive Evidence
10002193-null-.desc:
$npc:11001021$ told me to go to $map:02000139$ and look behind $map:02000226$'s wall clock.
$map:02000226$ can be reached by going up through $map:02000225$.
10002193-null-.manual: Find the evidence behind $map:02000226$'s wall clock at $map:02000139$

10002194-null-.name: The Unusual Suspect
10002194-null-.desc: $npc:11000529$ said that $npc:11000044$ can be proven to be guilty with testimony from $npc:11000526$ and $item:30000075$ as evidence. I was told to go to $map:02000152$ and make sure $npc:11000044$ cannot run away.

10002195-null-.name: Into Thin Air
10002195-null-.desc:
$npc:11000044$ has already left $map:02000153$ and vanished.
It's apparent that $npc:11000044$ already figured out what was going on and hid.
I should return to $map:02000208$ and tell $npc:11000529$ the news.

10002196-null-.name: Flip Flopped
10002196-null-.desc: $npc:11000529$ told me to show $item:30000075$ to $map:02000001$'s $npc:11000119$ and say that a bounty must be set for $npc:11000044$.

10002197-null-.name: Reporting Facts
10002197-null-.desc: $npc:11000119$ told me to report everything to $npcName:11000075$.

10002200-null-.name: The Great Rescue
10002200-null-.desc:
The doppelganger of $npc:11000685$, the absolute good...$npc:11000068$, the absolute evil!
Until $npc:11000068$ is sealed away back into the Shadow World, not even Green Lapenta's safety is guaranteed... This is a crisis that only the Defenders, the guardians of the world, must resolve.
It's vital that $npc:11000057$'s rescue plan first be executed. Let's find the door to $map:02000227$ near the Green Lapenta's apparition at the lowest part of $map:02000023$.
10002200-null-.manual: Receive $item:30000107$ from $npc:11000031$ at $map:02000023$'s $map:02000035$ | Find and enter $map:02000227$'s entrance near Lapenta's apparition

10002201-null-.name: Soul Dimension
10002201-null-.desc:
$npc:11000685$ in $map:02000227$ said that in order to diminish the impact of the fissure from both life and soul, the Spirit Lantern must be absorbed.
Let's enter $map:02000220$ after absorbing the Spirit Lantern behind $npc:11000685$.
10002201-null-.manual: Receive $item:30000107$ from $npc:11000685$ at $map:02000227$ | Enter $map:02000220$ after absorbing the Spirit Lantern

10002202-null-.name: No Turning Back
10002202-null-.desc:
Bella was found hardened like a rock at $map:02000220$, and was unresponsive to $item:30000107$.
Just what in the world happened to Bella's soul...?

10002203-null-.name: A Lost Hope
10002203-null-.desc: It seems like the only hope of saving $npc:11000057$ has been extinguished.

10002204-null-.name: Back to Square One
10002204-null-.desc:
The memories of all the work I did for $npc:11000282$ and $npc:11000304$ with the hopes of saving $npc:11000057$ from the Demon King flashed before my eyes.
But now... Everything's back to square one...
Is it time to give up trying to save $npc:11000057$...?

10002205-null-.name: A Hole That Cannot Be Filled
10002205-null-.desc: Unable to see $npc:11000074$ face to face, $npc:11000075$ asked me to deliver the news along with some words of consolation to $npc:11000057$.

10002206-null-.name: A Word A Day
10002206-null-.desc: $npc:11000074$ asked me to deliver the news that $npc:11000057$ will not be returning, so that $npc:11000057$ will not have to suffer more from any pretense of false hope.

10002210-null-.name: Incoming Storm
10002210-null-.desc:
$npc:11000076$ said that $npc:11000057$ and his minions stormed $map:02000146$ and attempted to overtake it. I was asked to join the reinforcements $npc:11000119$ and $npc:11000057$ brought in order to track $npc:11000057$ down.
Let's find an entrance to a tunnel near the path to $map:02000145$!
10002210-null-.complete: Find $map:02000237$ in $map:02000146$ and join the reinforcements

10002211-null-.name: Light at the End of the Tunnel
10002211-null-.desc:
The reinforcements $npc:11000119$ and $npc:11000015$ brought from $map:02000237$ have already been almost completely obliterated.
$npcName:11000015$ told me to leave the injured $npcName:11000119$ with him and to continue pursuing $npc:11000057$.

10002212-null-.name: The One That Got Away
10002212-null-.desc: $npc:11000703$, who was injured while pursuing $npc:11000057$, told me to return to the Defender's Alliance HQ and request for reinforcements to continue chasing $npc:11000057$.

10002270-null-.name: Lennon the Defender
10002270-null-.desc: $map:02000146$'s $npc:11000076$ said that $npc:11000064$ has joined the Defenders, and asked that I go see him at $map:02000228$.

10002272-null-.name: Facing the Darkness
10002272-null-.desc: $npc:11000069$ said that $npc:11000064$ went after $npc:11000044$ into $map:52000003$ and asked me to help $npc:11000064$ stay safe.

10002350-null-.name: Losing Hope
10002350-null-.desc: $npc:11000058$ told me to find $npc:11000869$, a researcher who has been assigned to investigate the Lidibrium area by the Chaos Time Center, and inquire if time travel is possible with the Red Lapenta's powers.
10002350-null-.complete: Find the Chaos Time Center's researcher at $map:02000008$

10002351-null-.name: Grasping at the Straws of Time
10002351-null-.desc: Left alone in $map:02000008$, $npc:11000868$ said that $npc:11000869$ can be found at $map:02000142$.

10002352-null-.name: Come on Feel the Noise
10002352-null-.desc: $npc:11000869$ asked me to defeat the monsters of $map:02000142$, who are disrupting the research with an abundance of noise.

10002580-null-.name: A Daughter's Letter
10002580-null-.desc:
$npcTitle:11000074$ from $map:2000190$'s daughter, $npcName:11000058$, is requesting the delivery of a letter to her father at $map:2000065$ of $map:2000001$.
Let's get to $map:2000065$ of $map:2000001$ and meet $npcTitle:11000074$.

10002581-null-.name: Location of Ermen
10002581-null-.desc:
$npc:11000074$ says $npcName:11000058$ left a farewell letter before running off to find a way to save $npcName:11000057$, and that $npcName:11000058$ must be found before she falls to danger.
I'll have to find $npc:11000012$ in $map:2000001$ and see if there is any unique mail that has been delivered to $map:2000190$ recently.

10002582-null-.name: The Place She Left
10002582-null-.desc:
$npc:11000012$ said that a few days ago, a thick research packet was delivered from $map:2000309$ of $map:2000270$ to $map:2000190$.
Let's go to $map:2000309$ of $map:2000270$ and investigate.

10002583-null-.name: Traces of Invasion
10002583-null-.desc:
$map:2000309$ of $map:2000270$ was left a mess in the wake of an unidentified assailant. Luckily, $npc:11000843$ in $map:2000309$ handed over $item:30000380$, which may have the assailant's image caught on it. First I need to find out if the video data can be recovered.
I'll need to take $item:30000380$ to $map:2000324$ and meet with $npc:11001097$.

10002584-null-.name: A Factory in Stasis
10002584-null-.desc: $npc:11001097$ of $map:2000324$ says that in order to recover the video, the generator that the monsters attacked must be reconnected. If I find the generator installed at the edge of $map:2000277$, I should be able to turn it on.
10002584-null-.manual: Defeat the robot monster at $map:2000277$|Operate $map:2000277$'s generator

10002585-null-.name: Unidentified Truth
10002585-null-.desc: $npc:11001097$ of $map:2000324$ found indiscernible scenes within the recovered video and asked that I return to $map:2000309$ and check with $npc:11000843$.

10002590-null-.name: Tremor of Time
10002590-null-.desc:
At $map:2000276$, $npc:11000843$ has found a strange signal coming from the time energy that flows along the Time Barrier.
Could it be connected to the incident at $map:2000309$?
First, let's get to $map:2000276$ and assess the situation.

10002591-null-.name: Dynamic Energy Research
10002591-null-.desc:
$npc:11001098$ of $map:2000276$ requested an analysis of all the data on the dynamic detection device.
Let's go and collect all the $item:30000382$ in $map:2000276$.

10002592-null-.name: Questions in the Code
10002592-null-.desc: $npc:11001098$ of $map:2000276$, confused, said that there was something strange in the results of the analysis from the data collection of $item:30000382$. Let's return to $map:2000309$ of $map:2000270$ and give $item:30000383$ to $npc:11000843$.

10002593-null-.name: Into the Time Barrier
10002593-null-.desc:
When $npc:11000843$ of $map:2000309$ placed $item:30000383$ in the time matrix of the research lab, the time matrix turned on and the entrance to $map:52000011$ opened.
Let's go to $map:52000011$!

10002594-null-.name: The Trembling Time Barrier
10002594-null-.desc:
$npc:11001099$ at $map:52000011$ stated that an unidentified strength shook $map:52000011$ and made it unstable. A request was made to help stabilize $map:52000011$.
With $npc:11001099$, we should be able to defeat the monsters threatening $map:52000011$.
10002594-null-.manual: Defeat the monsters within $map:52000011$, which is connected through $map:2000309$, and stabilize the barrier

10002595-null-.name: Back to Reality
10002595-null-.desc:
$npc:11001099$ at $map:52000011$, wishing to show gratitude, told me to go ask $npc:11000843$ to aid in the cause of discovering the shaking in $map:52000011$.
I should return to $map:2000270$ $map:2000309$ and meet $npc:11000843$.

10002596-null-.name: Combination of Clues
10002596-null-.desc: Upon hearing of the situation in $map:52000011$, $npc:11000843$ of $map:2000309$ stated that he would personally go to $map:2000298$ and chase the unidentified assailants following the chaos time key log in an attempt to control time. He asks I return to $map:2000001$ and report on the situation at $map:52000011$ and $map:2000309$.

10002597-null-.name: Guardian of Time
10002597-null-.desc: After understanding the seriousness of the situation, $npc:11000074$ ordered $npcTitle:11000075$ to explain in further detail.

10002598-null-.name: The Red Lapenta's Truth
10002598-null-.desc:
After receiving reports on the situation, $npc:11000075$ revealed that not only is the guardian protecting the Lapenta, but the Lapenta has also shown the willpower to protect the guardian. He tells me that what probably drew me to $map:52000011$ was the Red Lapenta's willpower.
Accepting the idea around the Red Lapenta, $npc:11000075$ requested that I remain a reliable comrade to $npc:11000015$ until the power threatening $map:52000011$ is completely uprooted.

10002600-null-.name: In the Details
10002600-null-.desc:
$npc:11000075$ requested that I care for $npc:11000058$, who has returned from $map:2000298$, and watch for any sign of injuries.
Let's get to $map:2000190$ of $map:2000119$ and meet $npc:11000058$.

10002601-null-.name: Red Lapenta Guardian
10002601-null-.desc:
$npc:11000058$ saw $npc:11001113$ at $map:2000304$ and asked the Red Lapenta guardian to find a way to put $npc:11000057$ back in the original place.
While a difficult request, $npc:11000058$'s eyes are filled with desperation.
I should get to $map:2000076$ and meet $npc:11000015$.

10002602-null-.name: Coexist as One
10002602-null-.desc:
$npc:11000015$ of $map:2000076$ revealed that when the time floor at $map:2000304$ froze, the past and present became one at that moment... I've been ordered to go into $map:2000016$ and meet $npc:11000845$.
Could $npc:11000845$ know a way to protect $npc:11001113$'s soul vial?
FirstI must get to $map:2000016$!

10002603-null-.name: Labyrinth
10002603-null-.desc:
$npc:11000845$, met in $map:2000016$'s past, said the only way to save $npc:11001113$ is to find where $npc:11001113$ was before the order of time is completely restored and the past closes. 
The only clue to go by is the giant orb of evil energy that was situated behind $npc:11001113$!
I must hurry to $map:2000076$ and meet $npc:11000015$.

10002604-null-.name: The Returned
10002604-null-.desc:
$npc:11000015$ of $map:2000076$ believes that $npc:11001113$ is somewhere in the Land of Darkness, and recommends traveling to $map:3009017$ to talk to the people who were rescued from Katramus.
$map:3009017$ can be found at $map:3000143$, in the Land of Darkness.

10002605-null-.name: Asking Survivors
10002605-null-.desc: $npc:11000069$ was unexpectedly encountered at $map:3009017$. He had come with $npc:11000064$ to take care of the Katramus rescuers. As for the giant orb of evil energy, he said to ask the rescuers, as they've lived in the Land of Darkness for a long time.

10002606-null-.name: Legendary Terror
10002606-null-.desc:
$npc:11001106$ of $map:3009017$ called the giant demonic orb the "Soul Orb" and said that it was located in $map:52000012$.
Let's find out if anyone knows where $map:52000012$ is.

10002607-null-.name: Children's Stories
10002607-null-.desc: $npc:11001107$ of $map:3009017$ overheard the Katramus supervisors say that $map:52000012$ is located in $map:3000007$.

10002608-null-.name: Past a Fierce Wind
10002608-null-.desc: $npc:11000069$ heard that $npc:11000064$ is at $map:3009018$ in $map:3000007$, but says to find $npc:11000064$ first.

10002609-null-.name: Faith Maintained
10002609-null-.desc: Having heard all the circumstances, $npc:11000064$ agreed to come along to $map:52000012$ to help save $npc:11000057$.

10002610-null-.name: Once More, Together Now!
10002610-null-.desc:
$npc:11000064$ said we should hurry and find the entrance to $map:52000012$ that $npc:11000807$ told us about before the order of time completely restores. 
Let's find $map:52000012$ near the road going from $map:3000007$ to $map:3000021$.

10002611-null-.name: QUESTDESCRIPTION_10002611_NAME
10002611-null-.desc:
$npc:11000064$ said to go into $map:52000013$ and look for $npc:11001113$'s soul. 
...I recall a heartbreaking memory of returning to $map:2000220$ and falling to my knees before the hardened $npc:11001112$. Will I be able to save $npc:11001112$ this time?
I will enter $map:52000013$, the place standing in the middle of $map:52000012$.

10002612-null-.name: Like a Dream
10002612-null-.desc:
Did I lose consciousness at $map:52000013$? That flashing glare... I woke up at $map:3009017$. As I was wandering around $map:52000013$, the order of time must have been restored, and in the process of $map:52000012$ returning to the present I must have been tossed from $map:52000013$.
The memory of $npc:11001112$, though like a dream, feels all too real...
I'll head to $map:2000190$ and share the news of $npc:11000057$ with $npc:11000058$.

10002613-null-.name: Feeling Bella
10002613-null-.desc:
Having heard news of $npc:11000057$, $npc:11000058$ says she felt the exact memories and emotions as when they were growing up together. It must be a special bond between the twin sisters...
Let's go to $map:2000001$ $map:2000065$ and share $npc:11000057$'s news with $npc:11000074$.

10002614-null-.name: Striving for Desire
10002614-null-.desc:
After hearing news of $npc:11000057$, $npc:11000074$ became speechless as the sadness, guilt, and remorse toward his daughter sank in. In that instant I witnessed the soft-hearted father hidden behind the dignity and grace of the kingdom's royal minister. 
If time could be reversed...would $npcName:11000074$ make the same decision? If he had saved $npc:11000057$ instead of $npc:11000075$, how different would the world be...?
It seems like $npcName:11000074$ is lost in guilt and sadness, and needs some time to himself. I should head to $map:2000025$ and share $npc:11000057$'s news with $npcTitle:11000075$.

10002780-null-.name: The Alliance Acts
10002780-null-.desc: The invasion of Tria cost many lives—including Joddy, who fought bravely when the time came. But this latest attack has only strengthened $npcName:11000075$'s resolve to band together and fight back against the darkness.

10002781-null-.name: The Forgotten Ones
10002781-null-.desc: Until now, the forces of darkness have had Tria and its allies on the defensive. Empress $npcName:11000075$ wonders if Madria's dragon might somehow be related to the lumarigon, an ancient race of dragons who vanished long ago. Captain Allon reports that a dragon-like monster has appeared in Karkar Island. This may be an opportunity to strike back.

10002782-null-.name: To a New Land
10002782-null-.desc:
The Maple Alliance has set up a temporary headquarters in $map:02010002$ of Karkar Island. However, the seas around the island have been rough lately, so $npc:11000076$ had to commission a special ship to make the trip.

Find $npc:11001276$ in $map:02000183$ to charter your trip.

10002783-null-.name: Earthbound
10002783-null-.desc: $npcName:11001276$ invented the Lumiwind, a ship that can fly through the air. Unfortunately, it broke down after its maiden voyage. Get the full story from $npcName:11001276$.

10002784-null-.name: The Retired Inventor
10002784-null-.desc: $npcName:11001011$ is the engineer who helped build the Lumiwind with $npc:11001276$. He's the only one who can repair the ship, but he recently retired to $map:02000182$.

10002785-null-.name: His Story
10002785-null-.desc: $npcName:11001011$ dedicated his youth to building the Lumiwind. But, right as the invention was nearing completion, he realized that he and his family had drifted away from each other. The Lumiwind was his passion, but it's not worth losing the ones he loved...

10002786-null-.name: The Lumiwind of My Youth
10002786-null-.desc: $npcName:11001011$ steadfastly refused to repair the Lumiwind... until you put his pride as an engineer on the line. However, while he's doing the repairs, you need to do his chores so his family is none the wiser. Today's chore: fighting pirates at $map:02000182$.

10002787-null-.name: Take to the Skies
10002787-null-.desc: $npcName:11001011$'s repairs are complete. Return to $map:02000183$, and ask $npcName:11001276$ to let you ride the Lumiwind.

10002788-null-.name: A Desert Land
10002788-null-.desc: $npcName:11001276$ let you ride the Lumiwind all the way to Karkar Island. Meet his assistant, $npcName:11001403$, and ask for directions to the $map:02010059$.

10002789-null-.name: A Base away from Home
10002789-null-.desc: Now that you've arrived at Karkar Island, it's time to go to the $map:02010059$ in $map:02010002$. Meet $npcName:11001310$ in $map:02010002$.

10002790-null-.name: An Unexpected Problem
10002790-null-.desc: According to $npcName:11001310$, strange things have been happening at Karkar Island. Get the details from $npcName:11001311$ in the $map:02010059$.

10002791-null-.name: Words Are Cheap
10002791-null-.desc: The guards are paralyzed by fear since hearing of the attack on $map:02000001$. They haven't made any progress, but for some reason $npcName:11000251$, the infamous mob boss, is in town. It's possible he knows something useful. Find him in the $map:02010020$.

10002792-null-.name: A Shady Encounter
10002792-null-.desc: After you put the Blackstar gangsters in their place, the $npcName:11003119$ arranged for you to meet $npcName:11000251$. Meet him in the $map:52010010$.

10002793-null-.name: The Criminal Express
10002793-null-.desc: In exchange for his information, $npcName:11000251$ wants your help taking back a train that was stolen from his group. Defeat the thieves who hijacked the Blaknov.
10002793-null-.manual: Defeat $npcName:24001507$ in Blaknov No. 1|Defeat $npcName:24002109$ in Blaknov No. 2

10002794-null-.name: Unfair Trade
10002794-null-.desc:
According to $npcName:11000251$, the dragon-like creature is searching for traces of the lumarigon, just like you. Although this race of dragons no longer exists, there are certain children who still carry their legacy. He'll tell you more... for a price.

Go to $map:02010019$ and see how you can help $npcName:11001342$ with their bug problem.

10002795-null-.name: Bug Attack
10002795-null-.desc: A swarm of bugs have invaded all of $map:02010019$, making business impossible. You know what to do.

10002796-null-.name: Pest Extermination
10002796-null-.desc: You have the insect menace on the ropes—it's time to finish the job! Go into $map:02010019$ and defeat the king of the bugs, the $npcName:23190066$!

10002797-null-.name: Done Deal
10002797-null-.desc: After thanking you for saving the park, his job, and his last chance for happiness, $npcName:11001342$ tells you to return to headquarters for your pay. Speak with $npcName:11000251$ at the $map:52010010$.

10002798-null-.name: The Four Children
10002798-null-.desc:
It is said that Biset, the last Dragon Master, died protecting four children. It is said that one of these children has the Lumenstone, an artifact of light, and that the mysterious dragon-man is looking for it.

Two of the children are in Blackstar's clutches. Since you've been so nice to $npcName:11000251$, he will let you see one of them. Go to $map:02010064$ in the $map:02010016$ and meet her.

10002800-null-.name: Circuit Queen
10002800-null-.desc: $npcName:11001297$ insists that you help her friend—$npcName:11001294$, another one of Biset's wards. Go to the $map:52010004$ in $map:02010020$ and rescue him from Blackstar.

10002801-null-.name: Champion's Favor
10002801-null-.desc:
After hearing that Blackstar is after the lumarigon, $npcName:11001294$ is worried about his friends. He wants you to make sure the other two are still safe.

Go to $map:02010053$ in $map:02010002$ and talk to $npcName:11001292$.

10002802-null-.name: The Prickly Chef
10002802-null-.desc:
$npcName:11001216$ is certain that $npcName:11000735$'s favorite rock must be the Lumenstone. He thinks your best bet is to ask one of the local meerkat patrols for help finding her.

Go to $map:02010063$ and look for a meerkat named $npcName:11001313$.

10002803-null-.name: The Awoken Dead
10002803-null-.desc:
$npcName:11001313$ wants you to investigate a pyramid where the undead have been rising. It belonged to a kingdom of lumarigon-worshipers, but they vanished after giving in to the darkness. Do this, and he'll help you find Mika.

Enter the Illusory Pyramid dungeon and report what you find.

10002804-null-.name: In Another Temple
10002804-null-.desc: $npcName:11001313$ saw a girl go into the $map:02010052$ at the $map:02010026$. Search for her in the $map:02010052$ dungeon.

10002805-null-.name: A Desert People
10002805-null-.desc: While he couldn't help you find the girl, $npcName:11001313$ has heard of a dragon-like monster. Go to $map:02010023$ and meet with $npcName:11001315$, granddaughter of the Moropapa Tribe's chief, and ask her about the monster that attacked their village.

10002810-null-.name: The Fallen Chief
10002810-null-.desc:
$npc:11001214$ has been wary of outsiders ever since the Land of Darkness was sealed years ago. His granddaughter, $npcName:11001315$, is hesitant to deal with you... but she needs $item:30000492$ to treat her ill grandfather.

Look in the herb jars, exterminate any bugs that pop out, and get $item:30000492$ for $npcName:11001315$.
10002810-null-.manual: Check jars and defeat bugs for $item:30000492$

10002811-null-.name: The Monster's Identity
10002811-null-.desc: Since you were such a big help, $npcName:11001315$ has agreed to let you meet with her grandfather, the chief. Meet $npc:11001214$ in $map:52010011$.

10002812-null-.name: Rescue Mika
10002812-null-.desc:
Deep within Nazkar Temple, there is a $map:52010006$. $npcName:11001214$ says that $npcName:11001363$ is there, and you are the only one who can rescue her.

Hurry to the $map:52010006$ in $map:02010030$!

10002813-null-.name: Visitor from Another World
10002813-null-.desc:
Following your example, the guards tracked down and chased the dragon-man into the $map:02010055$, the shrine of the lost Merjit civilization in the $map:02010029$. It is said that whatever caused Merjit to collapse began in this chamber...

Use the Enter Alone button to go to the $map:02010055$ and put a stop to this monster's plans, or find a group of fellow adventurers and face this challenge with a party.
10002813-null-.manual: Press Enter Alone to go to $dungeonTitle:20018002$ and defeat $npcName:23000068$

10002814-null-.name: Friends Reunited
10002814-null-.desc:
$npcName:11000735$ came by and asked the guards to thank you on her behalf. You should meet her in person before you return to $map:02000001$.

She should be back at $map:52010014$ by now.

10002815-null-.name: A Dead End
10002815-null-.desc: The soldiers are withdrawing from Karkar Island. It's time to return to $map:02000001$ with them. Report to $npc:11001969$ in the $map:52000087$.

10002816-null-.name: Mika and Moropapa
10002816-null-.desc:
As soon as I met $npc:11001314$, he yelled to get out.
Will I be able to change his mind?

10002817-null-.name: Dragon's Footprints

$npcName:11000046$ told me to go to $map:52000026$ of $map:02000025$ to uncover the reason the guardian representatives have gathered upon the request of $npc:11000031$.

10002993-null-.manual: Enter $map:52000026$ through the $map:02000119$ palace wall, northwest of $map:02000001$, and observe the situation

10002994-null-.name: Up in the Air!
10002994-null-.desc:
Believing it may be the perfect chance to test the newly acquired weapon, the super cannon, and to show off the blinding power of the Heavy Gunners, $npcName:11000046$ decided to join the Starlight Expedition.
$npcName:11000046$ says to go to $map:02000023$ $map:02000035$ and meet $npcName:11000031$.

10003000-null-.name: These Rookies
10003000-null-.desc: $npcName:11000050$ says to go to the pirates' base in $map:02000063$ and defeat them for our Thief comrades who were hit by the pirates in $map:02000063$.
10003000-null-.complete: Go to $map:02000063$ and defeat the pirates inside $map:52000025$ by the water in the $map:02000067$.

10003001-null-.name: Injured Runeblader
10003001-null-.desc:
$npcName:11001230$ has fallen from an injury inside $map:52000025$.
He requested that I defeat the pirates to help $npcName:11001229$ and the expedition team.

10003002-null-.name: Sincere Greetings
10003002-null-.desc:
Before respectfully saying his good-byes, $npcName:11001229$ said that one day he will repay me for my kindness. 
Let's get back to $npcName:11000050$ at $map:02000188$ of $map:02000001$ and report everything that has happened in $map:02000063$.

10003003-null-.name: Walk Hard
10003003-null-.desc:
$npcName:11000050$ told me to go to $map:52000026$ of $map:02000025$ to uncover the reason the guardian representatives have gathered upon the request of $npc:11000031$.
The entrance to $map:52000026$ can be found by the $map:02000119$ entrance, northwest of $map:02000001$, toward the top part of the palace walls.
10003003-null-.manual: Enter $map:52000026$ through the $map:02000119$ palace wall, northwest of $map:02000001$, and observe the situation

10003004-null-.name: Without a Choice
10003004-null-.desc:
$npcName:11000050$ strongly disagrees in assisting other troops who offer no help of their own. However, the Thief troop leader, Jonathan Button, has commanded that they go support the expedition. And so it appears they've no choice but to join the Starlight Expedition.
Let's go to $map:02000023$ $map:02000035$ and deliver the news to $npcName:11000031$.

10003010-null-.name: Outside of Interest
10003010-null-.desc:
$npcName:11000051$ says there is an emergency at the palace and to get to $map:52000026$ immediately. $npc:11000051$ seems irritated and hopes it's not all a waste of time...
The entrance to $map:52000026$ can be found by the $map:02000119$ entrance, northwest of $map:02000001$, toward the top part of the palace walls.
10003010-null-.manual: Enter $map:52000026$ through the $map:02000119$ palace wall, northwest of $map:02000001$, and observe the situation

10003011-null-.name: Interest Is Poison
10003011-null-.desc: It wasn't something the assassin was part of, says $npcName:11000051$. Nevertheless, $npcName:11000006$ asked what the emergency was about. $npcName:11000051$ requested I go to $map:02000208$ in $map:02000166$ and relay what happened at the banquet hall to $npcName:11000006$.
10003011-null-.complete: Speak with $npcName:11000006$ at $map:02000208$ located somewhere in $map:02000166$

10003012-null-.name: Individual Duty
10003012-null-.desc:
$npcName:11000529$ shook his head nonchalantly at $npcName:11000051$'s words, and said an assassin just needs to do an assassin's job. $npc:11000529$ says I should help $npcName:11000051$, who was going to $map:52000027$ alone. A Humples member went undercover into Darkstar in order to reveal the link between $npc:11000065$ and $npcName:11000251$, but was caught and isolated in $map:52000027$. We must rescue him as well as acquire the evidence.
Let's go to $map:52000027$ to help $npcName:11000051$ rescue the isolated Humples member.
10003012-null-.manual: Help $npcName:11000051$ at $map:52000027$ and secure the evidence

10003013-null-.name: A Courageous Act
10003013-null-.desc:
$npcName:11000006$ says that $npcName:11000051$ took the Humples member and the Runeblader to the hospital. $npcName:11000006$ also says that the Humples member was able to stay alive before $npcName:11000051e$ got there because of the Runeblader. Touched by the courageous act of the Runeblader protecting one of his men, $npcName:11000006$ revealed that he will join the Starlight Expedition.
$npcName:11000006$ says since $npcName:11000051$ left with the first group to $map:02000023$, I should hurry and go to $map:02000035$ of $map:02000023$ and meet with $npcName:11000031$.

10003066-null-.name: Revealed Identity
10003066-null-.desc:
A member of the Red Cape has infiltrated $map:02000025$ and kidnapped $npc:11000074$. 
There is no time to wait for the Royal Guard to be summoned, for $npc:11000074$'s life may be in danger.
Let's hurry to $dungeonTitle:21004001$ and rescue the minister.

10003067-null-.name: Protect the Barrier of Life
10003067-null-.desc:
$npc:11000031$ at $map:02000023$ $map:02000035$ intuits that the barrier of life is in danger from the dark energy coming from the east part of the forest.
Let's go to $dungeonTitle:21002001$, located deep in the $map:02000023$ eastern forest, and cleanse the darkness!
10003067-null-.complete: Follow the open road at $map:02000066$, go inside $map:02000179$, and speak with $npcName:11000032$

10003068-null-.name: Honest Logs
10003068-null-.desc: $npc:11000136$ of $map:02000051$, having shared that an eagle from distant seas came and delivered news of ghost pirates, expressed curiosity in regards to the secret logs that could potentially reveal the identity of the pirate captain.
10003068-null-.manual: Defeat $npc:23000015$ in the $dungeonTitle:20010001$ dungeon and acquire $item:39000032$

10003069-null-.name: The Secret of the Clocktower
10003069-null-.desc: $npc:11000039$, having a memorial service in $map:02000049$, said that an ominous energy was felt from the northwest skies, and that I should observe it before something bad occurs.

10003070-null-.name: Real Friendship
10003070-null-.desc: $npcName:11000044$ says to go find Katramus, whom $npcName:11000006$$ mentioned, and bring back every clue that could help find Lennon or Eve.

10003072-null-.name: Turn Back Time!
10003072-null-.desc:
$npc:11000003$ of $map:02000001$, sharing the story of the $map:02000309$ robbery incident, said with confidence that the culprit who stole the time key had to have gone to $dungeonTitle:21008001$. 
Could $npc:11000003$'s assumption be right?
Let's go to $dungeonTitle:21008001$ and check it out.

10003073-null-.name: To the Highlands
10003073-null-.desc:
The forces of darkness have set their sights on the Seven Heroes. The only two who remain in the public eye are $npc:11000134$ and $npcName:11000601$. It's up to you and Allon to keep them safe from the so-called "ragged wraith."

Head to $map:02000051$ and protect $npcName:11000134$.

10003074-null-.name: The Warrior's Test
10003074-null-.desc: $npcName:11003421$ refuses to let you into $map:02000051$ without passing his test. Go to $map:02000010$ and vanquish the $npcNamePlural:21090102$ and $npcNamePlural:21000088$.

10003075-null-.name: After the Attack
10003075-null-.desc:
$npcName:11000134$ joined the war party that's tracking down the mysterious figure in rags who attacked town. Meet with the town shaman, $npcName:11000039$, and warn her of the danger.

If you leave by mistake, talk to $npcName:11000289$ in $map:02000051$ to return to $map:52010033$.

10003076-null-.name: Wolf Girl
10003076-null-.desc: $npcName:11000039$ is off looking for medicine to treat all the wounded. She's left $npcName:11000136$ behind to watch the hospital in the meantime, but it seems like she has something to ask you...

10003077-null-.name: Shells of Wellness
10003077-null-.desc:
The shell of $npcName:21000267$ can be used as a medicine to treat the injured. These critters like to live near the lava flows in places like $map:02000010$.

Gather some for $npcName:11000136$. It's not like you have more pressing business.

10003078-null-.name: Honorary Doctor
10003078-null-.desc: $npcName:11000136$ wants you to use her medicine to treat the injured. You're not a doctor, but what have you got to lose?

10003079-null-.name: Perion Persistence
10003079-null-.desc: You've finally found a responsible adult. Tell $npcName:11000039$ about your business in $map:02000051$.

10003080-null-.name: The Missing Warriors
10003080-null-.desc: $npcName:11003422$ says that the war party was ambushed. You should look for more survivors.

10003081-null-.name: The Casualty
10003081-null-.desc: You found $npcName:11003423$ from the war party, but she's badly hurt. Find something nearby that you can use to treat her wounds.

10003082-null-.name: Path of War
10003082-null-.desc: In spite of your best efforts, $npcName:11003423$ was too wounded to save. Before she passed away, she said that the war party was headed for the $map:02000048$.

10003083-null-.name: The Interlopers
10003083-null-.desc: You met $npcName:11000541$ at the $map:02000048$. She seems to know something about the war party, but she refuses to say anything until someone does something about the $npcNamePlural:21000065$, $npcNamePlural:21090082$, and $npcNamePlural:21091082$.

10003084-null-.name: End of the Chase
10003084-null-.desc: The war party should still be at $map:02000046$. But they were ambushed, and now monsters are closing in on the area. You need to find $npcName:11000134$ before something happens to him.
10003084-null-.complete: Search for $npcName:11000134$ at the top of $map:02000046$

10003085-null-.name: Burning Clue
10003085-null-.desc: $npcName:11000134$'s trail ends at the top of $map:02000046$. Where did $npcName:11000134$ and $npcName:11000009$ vanish to? It seems the nearby torches have been lit recently. Perhaps you should see what happens when you relight them.
10003085-null-.manual:
Light the first torch
 |Light the second torch
 |Light the third torch
 |Light the fourth torch
10003085-null-.complete: Search the hidden temple at the top of $map:02000046$

10003086-null-.name: Inside the Hourglass
10003086-null-.desc:
You found the entrance to a hidden temple at the top of $map:02000046$. There's a good chance that $npcName:11000134$ and $npcName:11000009$ are inside.

If you leave by mistake, examine the $npc:11003430$ in $map:02000046$ to return.

10003087-null-.name: Son of the Chief
10003087-null-.desc: $npcName:11000134$ attacked his own son, $npcName:11000009$. What could have caused him to do so? Since both father and son are unconscious, talk to $npcName:11000009$ in $map:52010033$.

10003088-null-.name: The Mysterious Woman
10003088-null-.desc:
$npcName:11000009$ isn't sure what happened to $npcName:11000134$. The so-called ragged wraith seems to be involved, along with a mysterious woman.

If $npcName:11000134$'s mind is being controlled, who is doing it... and how?

10003089-null-.name: Returned from Darkness
10003089-null-.desc: $npcName:11000039$ seems especially distressed after hearing what $npcName:11000009$ had to say. She's asked you to meet her in $map:52010034$.

10003090-null-.name: A Secret Treatment
10003090-null-.desc: $npcName:11000039$ is convinced that the attack on Perion was led by the Inakimo, a tribe that vanished into the Land of Darkness a generation ago. She's seen their magic before, and she thinks she knows how to treat $npcName:11000134$'s illness. Gather $item:30000864$ from $map:02000095$.

10003091-null-.name: The Sleepy Witch
10003091-null-.desc: $npcName:11000039$'s medicine will stop $npcName:11000134$ from getting any worse, but it's not a true cure. $npcName:11000746$, the witch of the $map:02000103$ in Ellinia, knows many rituals to purify dark magic. Seek her out.

10003092-null-.name: A Divine Being
10003092-null-.desc: The ritual to cure the war chief requires pure, divine energy—and, as a witch, $npcName:11000746$ doesn't have access to that kind of energy. However, the unicorns of $map:02000053$ may be able to help.

10003093-null-.name: Unicorn Rescue Party
10003093-null-.desc: $npcName:11000027$, the unicorn you met in $map:02000053$, is in dire need of your help. All of his unicorn friends have been transformed by dark magic. You'll need those unicorns' help if you're going to save $npcName:11000134$...
10003093-null-.manual: Purify the $npcNamePlural:21000109$ by beating them up

10003094-null-.name: Aura of Light
10003094-null-.desc: $npcName:11000027$ and his friends have granted you the aura of light you need to save $npcName:11000134$. Return to $npc:11000039$ in $map:52010032$.

10003095-null-.name: The Light of Hope
10003095-null-.desc: The ritual successfully purified $npcName:11000134$ of darkness, but...

10003096-null-.name: The Guardian of Perion
10003096-null-.desc:
Even though the purification ritual was successful, the curse on $npcName:11000134$ returned moments later. $npc:11000039$ suspects that the Inakimo have found a way to corrupt $npcName:11003392$, a guardian golem who shares a magical bond with the war chiefs of $map:02000051$.

$npcName:11003391$ was sent to scout out $map:52010029$ and never returned. Go there and save both him and $npcName:11003392$ from the Inakimo's clutches!
10003096-null-.manual: Go to the $map:52010029$ via $map:52010031$, then save $npcName:11003392$ and $npcName:11003391$

10003097-null-.name: Perion's Coldest Heart
10003097-null-.desc: You had a... falling out with $npcName:11003391$ in $map:52010029$. How are you going to win him back over to your side?

10003098-null-.name: A Quick Apology
10003098-null-.desc:
Nothing says "I'm sorry" like a gift that you obtained for free. Give some incense to $npcName:11003391$ so that he forgives you for your earlier disagreement.

$npcName:11000289$ should be able to get you to $npc:11003391$'s house.

10003099-null-.name: House Visit
10003099-null-.desc:
$npcName:11000289$ says that $npcName:11003391$ looks depressed. Go to $npcName:11003391$'s house in $map:52010027$ and leave your gift.

If you leave by mistake, talk to $npcName:11000289$ in $map:02000051$ to return.

10003100-null-.name: A Gift Left Behind
10003100-null-.desc: You just missed $npcName:11003391$. Break into his house and leave your apology gift for him to find later.

10003101-null-.name: A Bad Turn
10003101-null-.desc: There's something happening outside. You're certain you hear screaming. Go outside to $map:52010027$ and see what's happening.

10003102-null-.name: Suspect Victory
10003102-null-.desc:
You encountered $npcName:11003431$, chief of the Inakimo, in $map:52010027$. But where has he vanished to? And who is this viper he mentioned?

For now, hurry back to $map:02000051$.

10003103-null-.name: An Unexpected Raid
10003103-null-.desc:
You've returned to $map:02000051$ to find it under attack by the Inakimo. It seems that $npcName:11003431$ was a diversion...

$npcName:11000289$ will get the civilians to safety. You need to get to $map:52010031$ to join forces with $npcName:11000078$ and $npcName:11000009$.

10003104-null-.name: Save the Guardian
10003104-null-.desc:
$map:02000051$ won't be able to survive another attack if the Inakimo manage to take control of $npcName:11003392$'s golems. While $npcName:11000078$ and $npcName:11000009$ fight off the main Inakimo force, you need to sneak off to $map:02000313$ and save $npcName:11003392$ from its captivity.

Use the secret passage to get there.

10003105-null-.name: The War Chief's Mission
10003105-null-.desc: Go to $map:02000313$ through the $npcName:11003468$ in $map:52010031$ and rescue $npcName:11003392$ from the Inakimo.

10003106-null-.name: Looking Forward
10003106-null-.desc: After a long battle, $npcName:11000134$, $npcName:11000078$, and $npcName:11003392$ fell to protect $map:02000051$. $npcName:11000039$ blames herself for not doing enough to save them.

10003107-null-.name: A New Chief for a New Age
10003107-null-.desc: The new war chief of $map:02000051$, $npcName:11003457$, has pledged to support the battle against the darkness.

20001080-null-.name: Cat on a Crane
20001080-null-.desc: $npcName:11000366$ is wandering around $map:02000139$, worried sick about her lost cat, $npcName:11000367$. Maybe if you climb the crane behind her, you'll find the poor little kitty.

20001080-null-NA.name: Cat on a Crane
20001080-null-NA.desc: $npcName:11000366$ is wandering around $map:02000139$, worried sick about her lost cat, $npcName:11000367$. Maybe if you climb the crane behind her, you'll find the poor little kitty.

20001081-null-.name: The Break Up
20001081-null-.desc: $npcName:11000367$ has eloped with another cat. Break the news to $npcName:11000366$.

20001081-null-NA.name: The Break Up
20001081-null-NA.desc: $npcName:11000367$ has eloped with another cat. Break the news to $npcName:11000366$.

20001170-null-.name: Balloon Grabber
20001170-null-.desc: Let's retrieve the balloon over the tree above the portal to get to $map:02000116$. $npc:11000389$, who sells balloons in $map:02000115$, wants it.
20001170-null-.manual: Use rock climbing skills to retrieve the balloon from the tree above the $map:02000116$ portal

20001180-null-.name: Into the Woods
20001180-null-.desc: Let's deliver the packed lunch to $npc:11000128$ in $map:02000116$.

20001240-null-.name: Below His Station
20001240-null-.desc: $npc:11000065$ is complaining of a bad stench coming from lower $map:02000100$, where his least favorite constituents live. Help clean up that part of town.

20001240-null-NA.name: Below His Station
20001240-null-NA.desc: $npc:11000065$ is complaining of a bad stench coming from lower $map:02000100$, where his least favorite constituents live. Help clean up that part of town.

20001241-null-.name: Interview of a Lifetime
20001241-null-.desc: To thank you for your service, $npc:11000065$ has sent a letter of recommendation on your behalf to Goldus Group. Go to $map:02000189$ for your interview.

20001241-null-NA.name: Interview of a Lifetime
20001241-null-NA.desc: To thank you for your service, $npc:11000065$ has sent a letter of recommendation on your behalf to Goldus Group. Go to $map:02000189$ for your interview.

20001242-null-.name: Praise Goldus
20001242-null-.desc: As Goldus Group's newest employee, it's time for you to meet $npc:11000252$ and sing the company song to him. The lyrics to the song, "$npc:11000477$," are hanging on the wall next to him.

20001242-null-NA.name: Praise Goldus
20001242-null-NA.desc: As Goldus Group's newest employee, it's time for you to meet $npc:11000252$ and sing the company song to him. The lyrics to the song, "$npc:11000477$," are hanging on the wall next to him.

20001250-null-.name: Demonic Roots
20001250-null-.desc:
$npc:11000169$ requested that I go to $map:02000315$ and steal the $item:30000190$ from $npc:23100025$.
Although I am bothered by his attitude (he seems to ask others for help in every difficult situation), I will aid him this one time, like $npc:11000169$ said to.

20001260-null-.name: Secret of the Dance
20001260-null-.desc:
$npc:11000542$ loves to dance, so he decided to raise some $npcPlural:21000069$ to dance with. However, his $npcPlural:21000069$ look pretty sad compared to the ones you see dancing in the wild.

Hunt some wild $npc:21000069$ around the $map:02000049$ and learn their secret.

20001260-null-NA.name: Secret of the Dance
20001260-null-NA.desc:
$npc:11000542$ loves to dance, so he decided to raise some $npcPlural:21000069$ to dance with. However, his $npcPlural:21000069$ look pretty sad compared to the ones you see dancing in the wild.

Hunt some wild $npc:21000069$ around the $map:02000049$ and learn their secret.

20001261-null-.name: Dance of the Cacti
20001261-null-.desc: You found $itemPlural:30000029$ while hunting $npcPlural:21000069$. Is this what Tanz needs to get his own $itemPlural:30000029$ to dance?

20001261-null-NA.name: Dancing Cactus
20001261-null-NA.desc: You found $itemPlural:30000029$ while hunting $npcPlural:21000069$. Is this what Tanz needs to get his own $itemPlural:30000029$ to dance?

20001270-null-.name: Rain, Rain, Come Again
20001270-null-.desc: Worried about the lack of rain in the Perion region, $npc:11000039$ set up totems in the lower area of $map:02000049$. Let's hold a rain ritual in front of all the totems in $map:02000049$.
20001270-null-.manual: Hold a rain ritual in front of all the totems in $map:02000049$

20001730-null-.name: The Enemy Within
20001730-null-.desc: $npc:11001043$'s job was to make sure the core technology of $map:02000277$ doesn't leak out. Unfortunately, there was a traitor from within; one of the team members was bribed by the mafia and stole the technology. The most urgent task at hand is to destroy the robotic weapons by manipulating the system, while simultaneously escaping the area. I have to destroy all of $npc:21000245$, $npc:21000247$, and $npc:21000242$ in $map:02000277$.
20001730-null-.manual: Destroy the killer robot weapons devastating $map:02000277$

20001731-null-.name: Heavy Security
20001731-null-.desc: Fortunately, the number of dangerous robotic weapons has been greatly reduced thanks to a quick response. But it's still too early to relax! $npc:11001043$ says the ones who stole the technology will come back to $map:02000277$ in order to destroy the evidence. $npcName:11001043$ is going to do whatever possible to capture the suspects. I'll need to activate the intruder detection sensor installed in $map:02000277$.
20001731-null-.manual: Install the intruder detection sensors in various spots around $map:02000277$

20002245-null-.name: QUESTDESCRIPTION_20002245_NAME
20002245-null-.manual: Search for clues in $map:02000129$ to find out the truth behind the Ultimate Transcendence

20002250-null-.name: QUESTDESCRIPTION_20002250_NAME
20002250-null-.desc:
$npcName:11000031$ stated that through combining the $item:30000538$ we may be able to discover the history of how the ancient ancestors of the Runebladers collected the "Ultimate Transcendence" and find the method to restore its power.
Let's watch $npcName:11000031$ combine $item:30000538$.

20002263-null-.name: Tria in Crisis
20002263-null-.desc:
$npcName:11000069$ warns that the forces of darkness are marching on Tria. $npcName:11000064$ is rallying the royal guards, but there simply aren't enough forces to protect the city. Hold the line while $npcName:11000069$ gets reinforcements!

If you leave by mistake, talk to $npcName:11001238$ to return.
20002263-null-.manual:
Hold off $npcName:11001698$'s army at $map:52000068$
<font color="#909090">If you leave by mistake, talk to $npcName:11001238$ to return.</font>

20002264-null-.name: The Shield of Tria
20002264-null-.desc:
The enemy failed to capture Tria, but many guards fell in the battle. Speak to the injured with $npc:11000076$ at the $map:52000068$.

If you leave by mistake, speak with $npcName:11001238$ to return.

20002265-null-.name: Unite
20002265-null-.desc: The Maple Alliance needs your assistance. Speak with Empress $npcName:11001969$ in $map:52000087$.

20002266-null-.name: Eccentric Interests
20002266-null-.desc:
$npcName:11000042$, the master wizard, has concocted a spell using the Lumenstone to track the magical power of the lumarigon. Her expertise is vital in the mission to find $npcName:11001698$, but she's stubbornly refusing to do any field work.

See if you can change her mind.

20002267-null-.name: Eclipse of Ice and Fire
20002267-null-.desc: $npcName:11000042$ finally agreed to go on the mission with you. Begin by meeting her at $map:52000088$.

20002268-null-.name: Remnants of Dragon Magic
20002268-null-.desc: $npcName:11000042$ senses lumarigon magic coming from the rune stones in $map:52000088$. Take a closer look at these stones.

20002269-null-.name: Bathing in Fire
20002269-null-.desc: $npcName:11000042$ is sure that the dragon you're tracking is in fact lumarigon—or at least related to the lumarigon in some way. Based on what you found, you should search for more evidence in $map:52000089$ at $map:02000268$.

20002270-null-.name: The Wounded Dragon
20002270-null-.desc: $npcName:11000042$ can learn a lot about a dragon from its scales. Examine the scales in $map:52000089$.

20002271-null-.name: Teleportation Tag-along
20002271-null-.desc:
The dragon scales in $map:52000089$ were tainted with dark magic. $npcName:11000042$'s spell is now pointing her towards the Land of Darkness, but first she needs to visit the $map:02000146$ to get a more precise reading.

Speak with $npcName:11003089$ at the $map:02000146$.

20002272-null-.name: Breath of Darkness
20002272-null-.desc:
After arriving at $map:02000146$, $npcName:11000042$ picked up massive amounts of lumarigon magic in $map:52000090$. She needs you to hurry there, as the natural dark energies of the forest could make the dragon hard to track if it moves on.

Defeat $npcNamePlural:29000164$ in $map:52000090$, which can be found at $map:03000043$ in the Land of Darkness.

20002273-null-.name: The Phase-shifted Shadows
20002273-null-.desc:
$npcName:11000042$ has pinpointed the exact mix of lumarigon and dark magic needed for her tracking spell. Surprisingly, the location revealed to her by the spell isn't far.

Meet her at the $map:52000092$ beneath the $map:02000146$.

20002274-null-.name: Magic Counter
20002274-null-.desc:
$npcName:11000042$ discovered a stretch of distorted space. It's as if something is being hidden by magic. She is preparing a counterspell to remove the cloak, but she needs your help to gather reagents.

Gather $item:30000726$ in $map:52000093$.
20002274-null-.manual: Defeat monsters in $map:52000093$ or collect $item:30000726$ from runes

20002275-null-.name: Dark Essences
20002275-null-.desc: To continue the plan to reveal whatever is hidden here, gather $item:30000727$ in $map:52000094$.

20002276-null-.name: Uncover the Darkness
20002276-null-.desc: To complete the counterspell, place rune stones on the circles of the magic seal. You can get rune stones in the $map:52000092$.
20002276-null-.manual: Place rune stones from $map:52000092$ on the magic seal

20002277-null-.name: Finally, Suddenly
20002277-null-.desc: The counterspell is ready! Overload the phase distortion with $npcName:11000042$.

20002278-null-.name: Shadows on the Move
20002278-null-.desc:
The cloak has been lifted, revealing none other than $npcName:11001698$'s stronghold. As if on cue, you've spotted her armies preparing to launch a new attack.

There's no time to call for reinforcements. Do what you can to delay the enemy's movements for now, then fall back and alert the alliance when you have a chance.

20002279-null-.name: Planted Feet
20002279-null-.desc:
There is no end to $npcName:11001698$'s army. $npcName:11000042$ will try to teleport alliance reinforcements to the battle. Stand your ground until then.

If you leave by mistake, talk to $npcName:11003091$ in $map:52000091$ to return.
20002279-null-.manual:
Survive the enemy's attack
<font color="#909090">If you leave by mistake, talk to $npcName:11003091$ in $map:52000091$ to return.</font>

20002280-null-.name: Secret Knights on the Scene
20002280-null-.desc: $npcName:11000042$ successfully teleported your reinforcements to the battlefield! Captain Allon and his Secret Knights are just in time to help you take care of the enemy army.

20002281-null-.name: Locked Down
20002281-null-.desc: Blackeye and his Dark Wind agents are dominating the battlefield, thanks to the master wizard's mass teleportation spell.

20002282-null-.name: Militia's Arrow
20002282-null-.desc: $npcName:11001585$ and her Green Hoods have cut off the retreat of $npcName:11001698$'s army.

20002283-null-.name: The Stronghold Revealed
20002283-null-.desc:
After all this time, you finally stand before $npcName:11001698$'s stronghold. It was hidden in a pocket dimension in the center of Maple World this entire time!

With $npcName:11001698$'s forces routed, the Maple Alliance plans to push its advantage and go on the offensive. Speak with $npcName:11003089$ about your next steps.

20002284-null-.name: The Maple Alliance Attacks
20002284-null-.desc:
The time has come for the Maple Alliance's counterattack! Strike into the heart of $npcName:11001698$'s base, Madrakan, and win a victory for justice!

Use the Enter Dungeon button in the quest notification window to enter the dungeon and do the quest.
20002284-null-.manual: Use the Enter Dungeon button to travel to $dungeonTitle:21024001$ and clear Madrakan Castle Bailey

20002285-null-.name: First Victory
20002285-null-.desc:
The siege on Madrakan was a rousing success! With her army destroyed and her stronghold under Maple Alliance control, $npcName:11001698$ was forced to retreat. Somehow you doubt you've seen the last of her, however...

Return to $map:52000087$ and deliver the good news to $npcName:11001969$.

20002286-null-.name: Magically Late
20002286-null-.desc:
You're late. To class. Again.

But you're a mage, so who cares, right? In fact, you used to skip class all the time, so just being late is an improvement. So relax. Take your time.

20002287-null-.name: Chores in Silence
20002287-null-.desc: You missed class after all. Professor $npcName:11000032$ may look like an angel, but there's nothing angelic about his punishments.

20002288-null-.name: The Weight of Knowledge
20002288-null-.desc: Cleaning without magic? The indignity of it! You have a feeling that $npcName:11000032$ is just getting started. Find out what other punishments he has in mind.
20002288-null-.manual: Bring text books to the podiums

20002289-null-.name: On the Banishing of Monsters
20002289-null-.desc:
How humiliating! What's the point of learning magic if you still have to do chores by hand? Why, you might as well be a lowly warrior, rolling around in the dirt!

Oh, $npcName:11000032$ is staring at you. You'd better close your quest journal and talk to him.

20002290-null-.name: An Unorthodox Lesson
20002290-null-.desc:
Fighting those monsters was fun, but now $npcName:11000032$ is standing in the corner mumbling to himself. It's a little creepy.

He's probably thinking up your next lesson. What could it be?

20002291-null-.name: An Unexpected Duel
20002291-null-.desc:
Did those monsters seem a little strong for a classroom practice session...? Nah, must be your imagination.

$npcName:11003146$ looks pretty unhappy right now. What's going on?

20002292-null-.name: Transfer Student
20002292-null-.desc:
Even though you lost your duel with $npcName:11003146$, it was still a ton of fun. $npcName:11003146$ didn't seem to have much fun, though...

And now Headmaster Asimov is here, and at some point the classroom exploded, and... and...

You may be in a lot of trouble.

20002293-null-.name: Thrilling Life Abroad
20002293-null-.desc:
And so began your life in Tria, where the only escape from your days of boredom is taking the occasional oddball assignment. Luckily for you, there's a caravan coming from $map:02000062$, and they could use an extra pair of arms to make sure the merchants aren't scared off by any especially aggressive butterflies.

Talk to $npcName:11003180$ to let him know you've arrived.

20002294-null-.name: Infiltrate Madrakan
20002294-null-.desc:
The time has come for the Maple Alliance's counterattack! Strike into the heart of $npcName:11001698$'s base, Madrakan, and win a victory for justice!

Use the Enter Dungeon button in the quest notification window to enter the dungeon and do the quest.
20002294-null-.manual: Use the Enter Dungeon button to travel to $dungeonTitle:21025001$

20002295-null-.name: Madrakan's Monarch
20002295-null-.desc:
The time has come for the Maple Alliance's counterattack! Strike into the heart of $npcName:11001698$'s base, Madrakan, and win a victory for justice!

Use the Enter Dungeon button in the quest notification window to enter the dungeon and do the quest.
20002295-null-.manual: Use the Enter Dungeon button to travel to $dungeonTitle:20022002$ and clear Madrakan Spire

20002296-null-.name: Fusion Core Test
20002296-null-.desc: A world where people do not have to rely on magic for power—that is your dream! And today, you make a great step towards your dream. Follow $npcName:11003291$ into your lab to test your latest invention, the fusion core.

20002297-null-.name: Blazing Passion
20002297-null-.desc: A fire started during the fusion core test. You need to put it out before something terrible happens!

20002298-null-.name: Slime Coolant
20002298-null-.desc: You put out the fire, but the core's temperature is critical. You need $itemPlural:30000771$ to cool it down.

20002299-null-.name: Shutting Down
20002299-null-.desc: You managed to stop the fusion core from going critical. It's time to replace the fuses and reboot the system.
20002299-null-.manual:
Replace the core fuses
(Pick them up and place them on the orange rectangles)
 |Reboot the fusion system

20002300-null-.name: Unexpected Guests
20002300-null-.desc: Some old friends have paid an unexpected visit. Well, ex-friends. Nowadays they're more interested in stirring up trouble than helping Maple World. Defeat their $npcName:29000260$ and kick them out.

20002301-null-.name: Who Needs Friends?
20002301-null-.desc: Years ago, $npcName:29000261$ was your friend. Now he's been ordered to take your fusion core by force. Show him that you won't give up your invention so easily!

20002302-null-.name: The Mayor Speaks
20002302-null-.desc: The HAPPY protocol worked perfectly. Sure, your workshop was destroyed, and Edelstein Square got hit hard by the blast, but otherwise, a great success. Talk to $npcName:11003294$.

20002303-null-.name: Big Picture
20002303-null-.desc: Your savior has appeared! $npcName:11000264$, the great alchemist of $map:02000270$, has come to pay for the damage to Edelstein. But what are his intentions?

20002304-null-.name: Ladin's Watchful Eye
20002304-null-.desc: Left with no other options, you went to work for $npcName:11000264$. Your first assignment: escort goods from $map:02000001$ from $map:02000270$. Meet with your contact in the guard, $npcName:11003180$.

20002305-null-.name: Rendezvous
20002305-null-.desc: You've arrived in Kerning City for a mission. Meet with $npcName:29000290$ and the Rooks at the entrance to $map:52000112$.

20002306-null-.name: The Raid
20002306-null-.desc: Your mission: raid the Dark Wind headquarters disguised as a $map:52000112$.
