The members of your organization are ruthless killers, but you are determined to complete this mission without any fatalities on either side. Convince $npcName:29000290$ to let you complete this mission solo.

20002307-null-.name: Interrogation
20002307-null-.desc: You successfully defeated the $npcNamePlural:11003336$ without killing any of them. You intended to interrogate the bartender, but $npcName:11003185$ showed up without warning and seems annoyed at your non-lethal methods.

20002308-null-.name: Underground
20002308-null-.desc: Even though you weren't able to get answers from your hostage, $npcName:11003185$ seems to know a lot about this facility. Continue your raid and subdue the remaining $npcNamePlural:11003336$... without killing anyone.

20002310-null-.name: Dark Wind's Secrets
20002310-null-.desc: You managed to capture a $npcName:11003337$ and learn the whereabouts of the information the Rooks need. Search through the books to find $item:30000775$. If you hadn't shown mercy, you doubt the $npcName:11003337$ would have been so cooperative...

20002311-null-.name: Way of the Rooks
20002311-null-.desc: Do the Rooks know only killing? Convince $npcName:11003185$ that there is another way.

20002312-null-.name: Traitor
20002312-null-.desc: $npcName:11003185$ has declared you a traitor to the Rooks simply because you want to end the senseless killing. You have no choice but to fight your fellow $npcNamePlural:29000293$.

20002313-null-.name: Resurfacing Emotions
20002313-null-.desc:
$npcName:11003185$ keeps talking about things you don't remember. A Rooks soldier isn't supposed to have emotions, so why do you feel so conflicted? Angry? Sorrowful?

Questions for another time. $npcName:11003185$ is trying to kill you. Defend yourself!

20002314-null-.name: Farewell
20002314-null-.desc:
You couldn't defeat $npcName:11003185$, but you did manage to use one of his own techniques to escape. It was a move usually used to take a life, but you used it instead to save your own.

There's no time for sentimentality. Speak with the $npcName:11003337$ and make your escape.

20002315-null-.name: Lost Assassin
20002315-null-.desc:
Starting today, you are no longer a Rook. You have taken countless lives in their name—lives that you may never be able to atone for—but now you have a chance to take a stand against their evil. Head to $map:02000062$ and stop the Rooks' attack on the caravan.

Thus begins your search for redemption... and your lost memories.

20002316-null-.name: Rage and Peace
20002316-null-.desc: Out of 998 matches against the old man, you have won... none. But you won't give up yet! Nothing will quench your rage! Not even Lilin forcing you to help her with her stupid flower arrangement!

20002317-null-.name: An Escalation of Events
20002317-null-.desc: These $npcNamePlural:29000294$ have no fighting spirit. Cut them down! Cut them all down!!

20002318-null-.name: The Old Man's Thoughts
20002318-null-.desc: You were feeling better after taking out your anger on the flowers, but then Lilin had to go and prod you some more. The old man appeared and broke up your fight, and now he's getting ready to talk your ears off...

20002319-null-.name: The Red Blade
20002319-null-.desc: Lilin wants you to gain complete control over the god of rage sealed inside of you. Until you do, the original inhabitants of the island can never return—including her know-it-all big brother. You aren't against her goal. You also want to control the rage inside so that you can use its power. The old man things you should work together, and has even offered to train you himself. You can't wait to turn that training against him...

20002320-null-.name: Real Training
20002320-null-.desc: You thought you would have to waste time with practice dummies, but the old man actually summoned monsters for you to practice against! As it turns out... real battle is fun!

20002321-null-.name: Real Training Part 2
20002321-null-.desc: This is fun. Fun! Fun!! You defeated the second round of monsters with ease. Why didn't the old man let you do this sooner?!

20002322-null-.name: The 999th Match
20002322-null-.desc:
999 matches against the old man. This last one was... different. For a moment there, it was if he could actually kill you. You need to work on your defenses...

It was a lesson you will never forget. The 1,000th match will be different!

20002323-null-.name: Looming Omen
20002323-null-.desc: Just as you finished training, a letter came for the old man. From the capital! As soon as he read it, he turned pale and set sail for the mainland. It's been days since he left. Lilin's a nervous wreck. She's even started seeing things, like the creepy shadows that are crawling your way. Wait, there are creepy shadows crawling your way...!

20002324-null-.name: Finding the Old Man
20002324-null-.desc:
You fought off the shadow monsters that attacked without warning. It seems your training is already paying off.

But now Lilin is freaking out. She's pulled something out of the monsters you defeated. What could it be...?

20002325-null-.name: Never Back Down
20002325-null-.desc:
Lilin found a piece of the old man's cape on one of the monsters. She's scared, but you know it takes more than that to stop the old man!

You've decided to leave the island and find him. After all, he owes you more training! It looks like you're going on that warrior's pilgrimage, after all.

20002326-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Hero's Rest
20002326-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Tria Royal Cemetery is the final resting place for those brave heroes who made the ultimate sacrifice to protect Maple World. You've come here to visit an old friend and compatriot, $npcName:11003344$.

20002327-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: What You've Missed
20002327-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: In a visit to Tria's cemetery, you catch your old friend $npcName:11003344$ up on the events of recent days. Things aren't quite the same without him around.

20002328-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Regrets
20002328-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: While visiting your old friend $npcName:11003344$ at Tria's cemetery, you can't help but wonder whether there was something you could have done to save him. Suddenly, your musings are interrupted by a mysterious knight.

20002329-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: An Early Inspiration
20002329-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
The mysterious knight reveals herself to be $npcName:11003897$, former captain of Tria's Royal Knights, and one-time instructor to both $npcName:11003679$ and $npcName:11003861$. Further, it seems she was the one who saved you from hoodlums during your childhood and set you on the path of the knight. 

It seems she's come to check up on you after a talk with $npcName:11003679$ and $npcName:11003861$.

20002330-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: A Knight's Purpose
20002330-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: As you wrestle with feelings of guilt and sorrow over Joddy's death, $npcName:11003897$ tries to help you. She hands you a mysterious crystal.

20002331-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Will of the Fallen
20002331-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
The crystal turns out to be something called a lapenshard. Said to grant special power to those who seek it, they began appearing throughout the world some time after the attack on Tria.

Seeking to wake you from your sorry state, $npcName:11003897$ offers to help you with your training as a knight.

20002332-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: A Knight's Watch
20002332-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: After some gentle nudging by $npcName:11003897$, you resume your training as a knight.

20002333-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Training's End
20002333-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: After a difficult but successful period, you've completed your training with $npcName:11003897$. Speak with her to find out what comes next.

20002334-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Lapenshard's Might
20002334-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: No wonder it was tough... you weren't aware of the weights added to the armor and shield! That is why the training was tough! Looking back, it was tough at first, but you didn't feel the weights at all towards the end of the training. Was this all... because of the power of the lapenshard?

20002335-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Shield of the Frontier
20002335-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: It seems the power of the lapenshards are more than simple rumor. $npcName:11003897$ suggested you join the Frontier Foundation to learn more about the shards, and test your newfound strength.The Foundation is an organization dedicated to regulating the possession and usage of lapenshards so they do not fall into the wrong hands.

20002336-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Call of the High Priest
20002336-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: After a group of Royal Guards encountered an unidentified wraith and were inflicted with incurable wounds, you were called to the priest academy to assist. There you met with Bishop $npcName:11003901$ and High Priestess $npcName:11003904$. Considering their own healing magic came to no avail, you can't help but wonder how you're supposed to help.

20002337-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Power of Belief
20002337-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: It seems your light, and the darkness that wounded these soldiers are two sides of the same coin. It was to that end the High Priestess requested your aid in healing them. Can you succeed where $npcName:11003901$ and $npcName:11003904$ have failed? You have to at least try. You might not have been able to save $npcName:11003344$, but perhaps you can help these men...

20002338-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: When Hope is Lost
20002338-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Despite your great effort, it seems you cannot save the wounded guardsmen. Whatever affliction they are suffering from only seems to feed upon your efforts to heal the soldiers. As you stand powerless to aid them, you can only wonder, is this truly what is meant to be?

20002339-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Darkest Hour
20002339-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: One of the guards mustered the last of his strength to thank you for trying to save him and his brothers-in-arms before closing his eyes, perhaps for the last time. As all signs of life vanished from his body, you can't help but wonder, is there truly nothing you can do?

20002340-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Traces of Life
20002340-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: ...No, not yet! You can still feel the trace of life within the wounded soldier... You can't let these men die without a fight!

20002341-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: And Then, Something Miraculous
20002341-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Much to everyone's surprise, a miracle has occurred. After all your efforts and determination, have you managed to conjure a light bright enough to stave off even the unyielding embrace of death?

20002342-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Brilliant Light
20002342-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: It seems that the brilliant light you conjured restored the guardsmen to health. Did the goddess herself answer your prayer? How did you manage to perform such a feat?

20002343-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Radiant Potential
20002343-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: As the guardsmen profess their unending gratitude for your saving their lives, you cannot help but be humbled. It seems reward enough that they're alive, but if the men have their way, there will be a celebration before the day is through.

20002344-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Unleashing the Divine
20002344-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
According to High Priestess $npcName:11003904$, your little miracle may be connected to a crystal known as a lapenshard. These lapenshards are said to bestow power upon those that seek it. 

$npcName:11003904$ said the guardsmen and the specter alike were both seeking one such lapenshard, resulting in their confrontation. It seems in the dust-up, fragments of the lapenshards ended up in the soldiers' wounds.

In a fortunate turn of events, it was these very fragments which empowered your magic enough to save the soldiers' lives. If you could only learn to harness the lapenshards' incredible power, you could use it to do truly great things.

20002345-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Looking Toward Tomorrow
20002345-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: High Priestess $npcName:11003904$ told you about the Frontier Foundation, a newly established organization created by the royal court to govern the use of lapenshards. There's a lot you could learn at a place like that. If there's a chance that unlocking the secrets of the lapenshards means you'll never again be powerless to save the people you care about, then the road ahead is clear.

20002346-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Priest Job Rank Quest 10
20002346-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: High Priestess $npcName:11003904$ told you about the Frontier Foundation, a newly established organization created by the royal court to govern the use of lapenshards. There's a lot you could learn at a place like that. If there's a chance that unlocking the secrets of the lapenshards means you'll never again be powerless to save the people you care about, then the road ahead is clear.

20002347-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Aisha's Letter
20002347-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: You received a letter from $npcName:11003929$. Why would she send you a letter? Is her phone broken? What is this madness?!

20002348-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Sweet Science
20002348-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: $npcName:11003929$ has been secretly working with a new material called lapenshard. She claims that it generates an incredible amount of energy, but you doubt such a thing is possible. Still, it wouldn't hurt to look...

20002349-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Off the Charts
20002349-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: These readings can't be right. According to $npcName:11003929$'s research, a single lapenshard outputs over 100 times the energy of the fusion core! If Ladin gets his hands on this, it's only a matter of time before he tries to weaponize it...

20002350-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Make a Mint
20002350-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: So, $npcName:11003929$ had her eye on the almighty meso. A lapenshard generator could create enough electricity to power Tria for a week after being turned on for just one minute. But...

20002351-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: In the Wrong Hands
20002351-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: If someone were to use the lapenshards to create a bomb, it could change the world forever—and not in a good way. You don't know how your enemies found out about the fusion core in the first place, but you can't afford the same to happen with this new technology. You have to take steps to make sure that nobody can use this tech, no matter how revolutionary it is...

20002352-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Back to Reality
20002352-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
Money is meaningless. Patents won't make you happy. Heck, being rich is more trouble than it's worth.

At least, that's what you keep telling yourself...

20002353-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Big Picture
20002353-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: To your surprise, $npcName:11003929$ had a really good idea. Use quantum cryptography to prevent the bad guys from getting their hands on your specs, then use it to upgrade your own weapons. After all, Maple World needs more powerful heroes—heroes like you!

20002354-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Peacemaker
20002354-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Now it is time to create a weapon to end all wars: the Peacemaker! You and $npcName:11003929$ had better get to work before $npcName:11000264$ gets back from his business trip.

20002355-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Power On
20002355-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: It's the 60th boot-up attempt. Quantum cryptography is locked and energy output is optimal. We are a go!

20002356-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Search for Lapenshards
20002356-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Your greatest invention, the Peacemaker, is online! But you'll need to find more lapenshard samples if you want to keep improving the technology. Where could you get such a thing?

20002357-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Climbing the Ladin Corp Ladder
20002357-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: $npcName:11003929$ suggests you join the Frontier Foundation, an organization dedicated to studying lapenshards. While you're at it, you can get some more lapenshard samples for her. But why does she insist on staying behind...?

20002358-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: A Boss's Promise
20002358-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
While you were off adventuring, $npcName:11003929$ made a life for herself at Ladin Corp. But even if Ladin treats her better than you ever did, she still believes in you!

You resolve to give her back pay and even a bonus when this is all over. Somehow!

20002359-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Breaking Limits
20002359-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: You set off to train in the hopes of growing stronger, but the same old methods just aren't cutting it. You need a new approach...

20002360-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Master Haster
20002360-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: $npcName:11003932$ showed up out of the blue! He seemed pretty composed for someone who betrayed the Green Hoods and handed a lapenta over to the forces of darkness! But the biggest surprise of all was that he came here... to train you?

20002361-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Terms of the Deal
20002361-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: $npcName:11003932$ offered to train you, under one condition: no questions. That's no easy choice. On the one hand, you have a lot of unanswered questions. On the other, there's a lot the man could teach you...

20002362-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Accelerated Learning
20002362-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: You reluctantly accepted $npcName:11003932$'s offer to train you. Your progress is expedited by the lapenshard, a miraculous crystal capable of awakening new power in those that seek it.

20002363-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Finding Your Path
20002363-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: You decide to give up on getting answers about $npcName:11003932$ actions in exchange for his help with your training. At least for now, it's time to forget about the past and focus on becoming stronger.

20002364-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Nock and Loose
20002364-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Your training with $npcName:11003932$ wasn't easy, but after a while it was almost like old times. But things will never be like before, will they? Not after what $npcName:11003932$ did.

20002365-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Questions and Answers
20002365-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: $npcName:11003932$ said he had nothing more to teach you. After your training, you feel stronger. $npcName:11003932$ may think his business here is done, but he owes you some answers!

20002366-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Seeya Never
20002366-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Training's over, so you can't hold that over me! Now tell me, where have you been all this time?! Why did you betray us?!

20002367-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Haster's Note
20002367-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: By the time you awakened, $npcName:11003932$ was gone. You never even got a chance to say goodbye. $npcName:11003932$ didn't even have the courtesy to leave a note, but instead left behind some sort of pamphlet.

20002368-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: A Clear Path
20002368-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: $npcName:11003932$ left a pamphlet for you to find calling for adventurers to join something called the "Frontier Foundation." Apparently, it's the new governing body in charge of regulating access to lapenshards. Maybe Haster wants you to go there. You can learn more about the lapenshards, and maybe you'll run into Haster again in the process. Your reunion with $npcName:11003932$ was short-lived, but at least he's shown you the way forward.

20002369-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Moonlight on the Serene Sea
20002369-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Having returned home to Calibre Shore. The unchanging moonlight sea puts you at ease. Worried that your abilities have peaked, you have come to seek out your old teacher. Perhaps he can show you the way forward?

20002370-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Confronting Holstatt
20002370-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: It's difficult to believe the traitor $npcName:11004028$ has returned to Calibre Island after all this time. It seems he's searching for something called a lapenshard. Whatever he's up to, he must be stopped!

20002371-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Obtaining Vengeance
20002371-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Can you really defeat one of the Eight Blades? Can you defeat $npcName:11004028$? No, there's no time for self-doubt... You must win!

20002372-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Resonance
20002372-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: When you crossed blades with $npcName:11004028$, a torrent of energy was released which permeated your body. As the strange energy flowed through you, you recognized it immediately... It was the very same rune magic used by $npcName:11004028$ and his fellow Jibricia traitors.

20002373-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Heir to the Twin Arts
20002373-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Just as you somehow obtained the power of the Jibricia, it seems that $npcName:11004028$ has obtained the power of the Pelgia. Thus it seems you have both become "heirs to the twin arts"...

20002374-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Echoes of the Clash
20002374-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: The timely arrival of your teacher and his associates has spared you what would certainly have been the battle of your life. Your master also noticed the changes in your powers. It seems you have a lot to talk about.

20002375-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Miraculous Crystal
20002375-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Runeblades who can muster the power of both Jibricia and Pelgia are known as Rune Sages. Such a state is said to be unattainable, and yet you and $npcName:11004028$ are the living proof. Acting Elder Blade Landevian believes it was the lapenshards' influence that made it possible. A miraculous crystal that grants power to those who desire it. What was $npcName:11004028$ planning to do with such power?

20002376-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Path of the Rune Sage
20002376-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Your master says that the royal court has requested that Terrun Calibre offer their assistance to the Frontier Foundation, an organization responsible for securing and regulating the lapenshards. Preventing $npcName:11004028$ from getting his hands on the lapenshards is reason enough to join, but this may prove a good opportunity to train your new power. The next time you face $npcName:11004028$, you plan to be ready.

20002377-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Wolf Returns to Its Den
20002377-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: You returned to your old neighborhood after a series of hectic adventures, only for no one to greet you. You can't help but wonder what it's all been for—your quest to defend the weak. If you yourself have reached the limits of your power, how can you really defend anyone?

20002378-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Big Fish's Lament
20002378-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: In a way, $map:63000020$ is where your grand adventure really began. You can't help but reminisce over old memories. Your identity, your sense of self-worth, it all springs from having the power to defend others. But on the cosmic scale, the famous Gray Wolf is just a small big fish in a wide ocean.

20002379-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Dr. Chen, Pugilist and Therapist
20002379-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
Training alone won't be enough to reach the new heights of power you seek. You need to make an evolutionary leap. As you stood around $map:63000020$ moping about your situation, you ran into $npcName:11003948$. 

Much to your surprise, $npcName:11003948$ seemed quite willing to help you unwind your dilemma.

20002380-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: People Like Us
20002380-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Vasara Chen believes that all of your self-righteous talk about protecting the world is just a pretext for what you truly love: fighting. Perhaps he's right.

20002381-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: A Dialogue of Fists
20002381-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Maybe all this started off being about fighting and getting stronger, but somewhere along the way you found that defending those who couldn't defend themselves was your calling. But is this philosophy holding you back from the power you seek? They only way to settle the question is with a duel.

20002382-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Rivals
20002382-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Your fight with $npcName:11003948$ showed him to be a formidable opponent worthy of the title of $map:63000020$'s champion. You may not have defeated him, but much was revealed to you over the course of your battle.

20002383-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Roads We Walk
20002383-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
Your fight with $npcName:11003948$ has left you with a newfound perspective, and a new sense of direction. You find yourself feeling faster and stronger than ever before. 

It seems $npcName:11003948$ too owes his new path to your battle. But, he reveals, the two of you had a little help in the form of something called a lapenshard.

20002384-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Wolf and the Stone
20002384-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: It seems Vasara was ordered to bring you the lapenshard by $npcName:11000251$. $npcName:11000251$ wants to send you to the Frontier Foundation—the governmental body responsible for regulating the lapenshards—as a Blackstar mole. Vasara however has another idea.

20002385-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: A Wolf Unchained
20002385-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
$npcName:11003948$ ignored $npcName:11000251$'s instructions and destroyed the Blackstar listening device, thereby setting you free. It seems he wants you to granted you to become stronger. 

He suggests you travel to the Frontier Foundation to learn about the lapenshards and grow stronger. The next time you meet, he's expecting a good fight.

20002386-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Welcome to the Foundation
20002386-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: You've arrived at the Frontier Foundation, a sprawling manor filled with adventurers.
20002386-LapentaFrontierQuest-.complete: Go to the center of the foyer

20002388-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Commencement Speech
20002388-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: $npcName:11003971$, director of the foundation, began her commencement speech in which she explained the mission of the organization. That is until she noticed you, and became quite distracted. Have the two of you met somewhere?

20002389-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Hero of the Family
20002389-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: According to $npcName:11003972$, personal butler to the foundation director, you saved $npcName:11003971$'s life during the siege on Tria. Henceforth, and without your knowledge, you became a hero to her family—resulting in a special assignment. Special assignments are a good thing... right?

20002390-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: A Special Assignment
20002390-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: While the other adventurers have already formed into groups and commenced their missions, you await instruction regarding a special assignment. What could it be?

20002391-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Unseasonable Weather
20002391-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
The Frontier Foundation has two major concerns when it comes to the lapenshard: The first is preventing their unauthorized distribution and misuse, and the second is investigating a series of strange phenomena endangering lives.

Your mission is to deal with the latter. It seems that at just about the same time the lapenshards made their first appearance, strange weather conditions began cropping up around the globe. Further, they've persisted for far longer than one would expect of normal weather. Odds are, they are tied in some way to the lapenshards.

It's not clear where this investigation will take you, but one thing is certain: adventure awaits!

20002392-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Lapenshards and You
20002392-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: It's been suggested that your special assignment from the Foundation gives you dispensation to use the lapenshards as you see fit. Why not use the powers of the lapenshards to give the bad guys what-for? You've earned it. Go wild!

40002480-null-.name: Celebratory Gathering
40002480-null-.desc: $npcName:11001292$, $npcName:11001297$, and $npcName:11001294$ are celebrating having safely completed their missions as dragon knights. Let's join the gathering.

40002490-null-.name: By Neccessity, Not Chance
40002490-null-.desc: The Huntis Federation and the dragon knights, two groups destined to unite, completed the missions together. $npcName:11001297$ is happy to have met $npcName:11001292$ and $npcName:11001294$ through this event. I've heard that $npcName:11001292$ has a similar story of how he met $npcName:11001294$...

40002500-null-.name: Grand Opening
40002500-null-.desc: $npcName:11001292$ recalled the grand opening of $map:02010053$ and  $npcName:11001294$ described the circumstances of that day.
40002500-null-.manual: Speak with $npcName:11001493$ and go to the past|Speak with $npcName:11001499$ of the past

40002510-null-.name: The Customer Is Right
40002510-null-.desc: $npcName:11001294$ continued to explain that because he was the only customer, he was able to eat without stopping. However, after he appeared, $npcName:11001292$ couldn't handle cooking alone... $npcName:11001292$ finished the story for $npcName:11001294$ of that nightmarish day...
40002510-null-.manual: Speak with $npcName:11001498$ and go to the past|Observe the situation of that day

40002520-null-.name: Origins of Fate
40002520-null-.desc: From the mark on his wrist, $npcName:11001292$ recognized that $npcName:11001294$ was a dragon knight just like him. $npcName:11001297$ also brought up the first day she met $npcName:11001292$.

40002530-null-.name: Second Fate
40002530-null-.desc: $npcName:11001297$ suffered from an unknown source of pain until $npcName:11001292$ recognized that she was a dragon knight after hearing about her symptoms.

40002540-null-.name: QUESTDESCRIPTION_40002540_NAME
40002540-null-.desc: $npcName:11001292$ is curious what's written on $item:30000515$. Let's go to $map:52010022$ and bring back $item:30000515$.

40002660-null-.name: Popularity
40002660-null-.desc: $npcName:11000076$ needs your attention urgently. What a burden it is to be so popular!

40002661-null-.name: Settling the Ranks
40002661-null-.desc: Though $npcName:11000044$ has left Dark Wind, his agents remain in Dark Wind and the army. You must track down his allies and remove them from the ranks. Meet with $npc:11000119$ and come up with a plan.

40002662-null-.name: Scene of the Crime
40002662-null-.desc: It's time to root out $npcName:11000044$'s spies. Search $map:52000073$ for clues.

40002663-null-.name: A Careful Search
40002663-null-.desc: Search the $map:52000073$ carefully to see if $npcName:11000044$ left any evidence behind. Start with the desk.

40002664-null-.name: A Hidden Place
40002664-null-.desc: Everything is not always what it seems. As $npcName:11000044$ had a hidden side, the $map:52000073$ may also be hiding something.

40002665-null-.name: Accomplice
40002665-null-.desc: Someone is covering $npcName:11000044$'s tracks. Ask $npcName:11000215$ if there have been any other visitors to the office.

40002666-null-.name: Cold Sweat
40002666-null-.desc: $npcName:11000215$ denies being a follower of $npcName:11000044$. You'll have to keep looking for suspects...

40002667-null-.name: The List
40002667-null-.desc: The charred documents that you found contain a list of people who have crossed $npcName:11000044$ and their location. Much of it is illegible, but you can just make out the words "$map:52000075$."

40002668-null-.name: Criminal Protection
40002668-null-.desc: $npcName:11000526$ may be a criminal, but he still deserves a fair trial. Make sure that he's safe and secure in the $map:02000134$.

40002669-null-.name: The Next Target
40002669-null-.desc: You weren't able to save $npcName:11000526$, but $npcName:11000064$ is also on $npcName:11000044$'s list. Make sure that he's safe.

40002670-null-.name: Increased Guard
40002670-null-.desc: You've let the guard know that $npcName:11000064$ may be in danger. That should be enough... right?

40002671-null-.name: A Difficult Rumor
40002671-null-.desc: It seems that $npcName:11000266$ has something to say.

40002672-null-.name: Reassuring the Ranks
40002672-null-.desc: To help bolster morale, $npcName:11000076$ suggests making $npcName:11000064$ the leader of Dark Wind. However, $npcName:11000266$ isn't sure if the other members would agree with this idea...

40002673-null-.name: The Leader of Dark Wind
40002673-null-.desc: I must first find out if $npcName:11000064$ is even interested in becoming the leader of Dark Wind.

40002674-null-.name: A Worthy Proposition
40002674-null-.desc: $npcName:11000064$ suggests that you ask $npcName:11000006$ to be the new leader of Dark Wind, instead.

40002675-null-.name: The Bait
40002675-null-.desc: Humblis has been investigating $npcName:11000044$'s activities on their own, and they think they've found the members of Dark Wind who are loyal to him. They have a plan...

40002676-null-.name: Misdirection
40002676-null-.desc: Set the trap by feeding false information to $npcName:11000215$, who happens to be a terrible gossip.

40002677-null-.name: Cleaning House
40002677-null-.desc: It's time to spring the trap on $npcName:11000044$'s spies. Defeat $npcNamePlural:29000146$ in the $map:52000070$.

40002678-null-.name: Elated Victory
40002678-null-.desc:
Now that $npcName:11000044$'s spies have been captured, the members of Humblis are going to rejoin Dark Wind.

Deliver this news to the guard.

40002679-null-.name: Too Soon to Celebrate
40002679-null-.desc: $npcName:11000064$ is curious about the news of $npcName:11000006$ and $npcName:11000044$'s spies. Bring him up to date.

40002680-null-.name: Strange Disappearance
40002680-null-.desc: There's urgency in $npc:11000076$'s voice. What does he have to say?

40002681-null-.name: Taken Away
40002681-null-.desc: $npcName:11000076$ believes that $npcName:11000523$ was kidnapped. It seems like a trap for $npcName:11000064$—one that he willingly jumped into. Make sure he isn't jumping into the trap alone.
40002681-null-.manual: Enter the $map:52000072$ at the $map:02000146$ and find $npcName:11001915$

40002682-null-.name: Her Reasons
40002682-null-.desc: It seems that $npcName:11000523$ left with $npcName:11000044$ of her own free will. $npcName:11000064$ is sure she must have had a reason, but the guard would never understand. Why don't you just tell them that she's gone on a... a trip?

40002683-null-.name: Getting Lennon
40002683-null-.desc: $npcName:11000064$ has yet to return. $npcName:11000266$ wants to discuss the matter of Dark Wind's new leader with him. Go find him.

40002684-null-.name: Losing Lennon
40002684-null-.desc: $npcName:11000064$ is nowhere to be found. Wouldn't $npcName:11000006$ know where he went?

40002685-null-.name: Low Profile
40002685-null-.desc: $npcName:11000006$ has an idea about how to find $npcName:11000064$ more quickly.

40002686-null-.name: A Kind of Lead
40002686-null-.desc: Since $npcName:11000006$ can't afford to make any waves in the search for $npcName:11000064$, he wants you to reach out to one of his less conventional sources. Meet the informant at the $map:03000103$.

40002687-null-.name: Searching Sight
40002687-null-.desc: $npcName:11001238$ will show you the way to $npcName:11000064$. Of course, she needs you to fetch ingredients for her first.
40002687-null-.manual: Get $item:30000614$ from $npcName:40000145$ in $map:03000060$ |Get $item:30000615$ from $npcName:40000128$ in $map:03000024$ |Get $item:30000616$ from $npcName:40000126$ in $map:03000101$

40002688-null-.name: An Unseen Threat
40002688-null-.desc:
It seems that $npcName:11000064$ is in trouble. Perhaps $npcName:11001238$ will send you to his side.

If you don't want to speak to $npcName:11001238$, you can take the temporary portal to the $map:52000076$, instead.
40002688-null-.complete: Go to $map:52000068$ from $map:02000349$ and speak with $npcName:11001917$

40002689-null-.name: Guard Captain's Lament
40002689-null-.desc: $npcName:11000119$ thanks you for saving $map:02000001$. He looks like he's aged ten years...

40002690-JobIntro-.name: Rob from the Rich
40002690-JobIntro-.desc: Empty out the safe before the coppers arrive.
40002690-JobIntro-.manual: Move $item:30000776$ from the safe to the exit

40002691-JobIntro-.name: Give to the Poor
40002691-JobIntro-.desc: Share the money you took from $map:52000128$ with the poor of $map:52000129$.
40002691-JobIntro-.manual: Give money to $npcName:11003277$ |Give money to $npcName:11003278$ |Give money to $npcName:11003279$

40002700-JobIntro-.name: Holy Mission
40002700-JobIntro-.desc: The soldiers who went out with $npcName:11003328$ all returned from the mission with grave injuries. Fulfill your duties as a Priest and heal them.

40002710-JobIntro-.name: Picking Up
40002710-JobIntro-.desc: Clean up the trash in $map:52000145$ for $npcName:11003189$.

40002711-JobIntro-.name: Quiver Basket Cleanup
40002711-JobIntro-.desc: While $npcName:11003189$ gets some "well deserved" sleep, move the quiver baskets into position for today's practice.

40002721-JobIntro-.name: A Friend in Need
40002721-JobIntro-.desc: If you don't hurry, $npcName:11003399$ will die of terminal nausea! Get help from the priest, $npcName:11003402$.

40002722-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Homebound
40002722-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Jonathan Button reached out to say that he'd found something interesting he wants you to see. It's been a while since you've been back home, why not go see what he has to say? Meet with Jonathan in $map:52000156$.

40002723-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: An Unexpected Reunion
40002723-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Jonathan called you into the $map:52000155$—a former Dark Wind hideout. Thankfully, they've abandoned the place. Apparently he's been living there with some associates. Well, might as well go inside and see what he wants to show you.

40002724-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Fresh-Squeezed Joy
40002724-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: $npcName:11003272$... $npcName:11003273$... You thought they were dead. But here they are waiting for you at the Jazz Club. They said $npcName:11001927$ tried to kill them, too, but failed to finish the job. All that matters now is you've been reunited with your old crew!

40002725-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: An Important Discussion
40002725-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: With $npcName:11003272$ and $npcName:11003273$ in a sugar coma after your juice party, Jonathan becomes very serious. He wants to talk to you about something. Meet him in the basement.

40002726-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: An Old Grudge
40002726-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: You followed Jonathan to the basement, where he shows you a photograph that opens some old wounds, and causes you to adjust your priorities. See what else Jonathan has to say.

40002727-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Call of Vengeance
40002727-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Jonathan showed you a picture of $npcName:11001927$, the man who betrayed you and attempted to kill you and your friends. It seems he's been illegally dealing in lapenshards. With this information in hand, you begin to form a plan to take your revenge.

40002728-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Appointed Time
40002728-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Your training is complete and the power of the lapenshard is yours. The question remains: are you ready to take down $npcName:11001927$? Talk to Jonathan and see what he thinks.

40002729-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Nothing Comes Free
40002729-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: With your newfound power, Jonathan believes you just might be up to the challenge of defeating $npcName:11001927$. But if you're going to have your revenge, you'll need to actually find the guy. Lucky for you, Jonathan has a plan! Listen to what he has to say.

40002730-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Debt Comes Due
40002730-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Jonathan says that his help was not free, but rather comes at a steep cost... Though you are initially filled with dread, it turns out his terms are actually quite reasonable. In a way, they've already been paid. Speak with Jonathan.

40002731-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Such Sweet Sorrow
40002731-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: The cost of Jonathan's help was to be his friend? Little did he realize, you were friends from the start. Now, a new mission awaits you at the Frontier Foundation. It's time to say goodbye to your friends once again—the old, and the "new."

40002732-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Recovering Lost Memories
40002732-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: In pursuit of your lost memories, you close your eyes and think of $map:52000156$. There in your mindscape, you recall a conversation you had with $npcName:11000006$.

40002733-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Memories of the Past
40002733-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: The lapenshard $npcName:11000006$ gave you was being studied by Dark Wind. Owing to its connection to the red lapenta which controls time, he's optimistic the crystal can help you recover your lost memories.

40002734-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Mystery Man
40002734-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: $npcName:11000006$ gave you something called a lapenshard and a report on what Dark Wind had learned about them. His hope was that you might be able to use it to recover your lost memories, and it seems to be working! You find yourself whirled away to a different place in the midst of calamity.

40002735-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Distorted Memories
40002735-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: You found yourself in a burning, but when you approached the flames you couldn't feel their heat. It was a memory, and in it you witnessed $npcName:11003185$ speaking with a $npcName:11004044$. You were not prepared for what came next.

40002736-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Forgotten Truth
40002736-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: After witnessing the $npcName:11004044$'s death at the hands of $npcName:11003185$, your head begins to reel. That child next to the $npcName:11003915$... Is that you? A murderous rage overtakes you.

40002737-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: An Origin Remembered
40002737-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: As the $npcName:11003915$ breathed his last, a murderous rage washed over you. $npcName:11003185$ said something about seeing if you have what it takes. What did he mean by that? You awaken from your memory to a startling realization.

40002738-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Muscle Memory
40002738-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Awakening from your memory, you come to the startling realization that your whole life has been spent in service of the man who murdered your father—the monster known as $npcName:11003185$. There was more to the memory, though. Something that may help you quell your burning desire for vengeance.

40002739-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: A Lethal Technique
40002739-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: After reliving one of your lost memories, a thought strikes you. The technique $npcName:11003185$ used is one that he never taught you. $npcName:11003185$ may have taught you everything you know, but apparently not everything he knows. If you can master this skill, perhaps you can use it when you give $npcName:11003185$ his just desserts.

40002740-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Exacting Vengeance
40002740-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: The skill $npcName:11003185$ used in your memory seems to have been intentionally hidden from you. Perhaps he feared you would use it against him. Now that you've memorized it, it's time to resume your journey.

40002741-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Cruelty and Justice
40002741-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Now that you have mastered $npcName:11003185$'s secret technique, it's time to figure out where to go from here. Since he provided you with the lapenshard in the first place, you decide to speak with $npcName:11000006$ and bring him up to speed on what happened.

40002742-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: As the Crow Flies
40002742-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: After emerging from your memory and mastering a new technique, you returned to $npcName:11000006$. It seems that $npcName:11000006$ was also familiar with the technique, but resolved never to use it because it was too cruel. He also filled you in on the latest intel regarding $npcName:11003185$.

40002743-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Renewed Pursuit
40002743-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: $npcName:11000006$ says that Dark Wind has received word of $npcName:11003185$'s recent movements. As much as you want to track down $npcName:11003185$ and end his life, you can't do that without finding him first. Talk to $npcName:11000006$.

40002744-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Introspection
40002744-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: On a visit to Lith Harbor, you stumbled over some crystals sitting on the ground and just about blew your top. Maybe if you take a moment to reflect on your thoughts, you can calm down a little.

40002745-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: A Familiar Face
40002745-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: After a conversation with your $npcName:11003918$ that sounded suspiciously like $npcName:11003920$, who should you encounter but your adoptive sister herself! But what is she doing here? Speak with $npcName:11003920$.

40002746-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: A Not-So-Stupid Stone
40002746-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Wait a second! How did $npcName:11003920$ know you were in Lith?! Is she stalking you? $npcName:11003920$ said she paid some information broker to find you... Was she that worried about you? Maybe it's time you told $npcName:11003920$ about what's going on with you.

40002747-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Awakened Rage
40002747-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: $npcName:11003920$ seemed unsurprised to hear what you had to say. In fact, she seems to know more about that dumb rock than you do! Even though sisters are annoying and should be ignored as a general rule, maybe you should listen to what $npcName:11003920$ has to say.

40002748-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Anger Management
40002748-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: $npcName:11003920$ says that stone you've been kicking around is something called a lapenshard. Apparently they've been making people stronger and giving them new abilities. Wow! It's a good thing it hasn't exploded or anything. Anyway, she says maybe that lapenwhatever's started to wake up the god of rage's power which has been slumbering within you. Welp, now what? Speak with your smarty-pants sister.

40002749-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Whack-An-Island
40002749-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: While you were away from $map:52000161$, $npcName:11003920$ thumbed through your old man's books on the god of rage. She has this crazy theory that if you can master the abilities the god of rage used, maybe you can control your rage too. That would be awesome! And at the very least, it's an excuse to break things. So you hopped on a boat with $npcName:11003920$, and off you go!

40002750-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Mastery of Rage
40002750-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Hoping to learn to control your anger and unlock the power of the god of rage without unleashing untold destruction, $npcName:11003920$ develops a training regimen for you. After destroying the many—thankfully unoccupied—outlying islands around Rien, your training is complete. Now what? Talk to $npcName:11003920$.

40002751-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: An Upscale Affair
40002751-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: With your training complete and your rage under slightly better control, it's time to figure out what comes next. Thankfully, $npcName:11003920$ has a plan!

40002752-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Real Agenda
40002752-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Though your training is over, your work has just begun. Apparently all this was to help get your anger under control so you can go somewhere fancy. When all's said and done, maybe you'll find the old man. Talk to $npcName:11003920$ to learn more.

40002753-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: We'll Meet Again
40002753-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
$npcName:11003920$ told you about the "Frontier Foundation," an organization responsible for regulating the lapenshards. She says you have a responsibility to use your power to help the world, but it sure seems like her main goal is tracking down the old man. Still, that's fine by you. You'll go to the Frontier Foundation, learn about the lapenshards, and get any help they can offer toward finding the geezer.

Before you go, you should probably say goodbye to $npcName:11003920$.

40002754-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: A Barbecue Among Friends
40002754-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
After a long journey, a letter from an old friend brings you back to Ellinel. What could be better than a barbecue with your best bud Kate?!

You and $npcName:11003925$ should catch up!

40002755-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Stoking the Flames of Friendship
40002755-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: You're having a lovely visit with your old friend $npcName:11003925$, but for some reason your dinner isn't roasting properly! $npcName:11003925$ seems really worked up about something. She must be hungry.

40002756-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: One-Track Mind
40002756-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: $npcName:11003925$ has been talking to herself for quite some time... Something about Professor Einos? Why isn't this stupid meat cooking faster?!

40002757-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Crunchy Crystal Candy
40002757-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Kate's been nagging you about something again, but it was hard to pay attention with your stomach grumbling like that. But what's that shiny thing over there, a bit of tasty rock candy?!

40002758-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Power Overwhelming
40002758-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: You found a tasty-looking piece of rock candy on the ground, and your hunger got the better of you. Forget the five second rule, a wizard's gotta eat!

40002759-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Mana Overload
40002759-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: You feel a little funny after munching on your ground-candy. Perhaps something to do with that explosion? $npcName:11003925$ seems worried, but what ever for? Sure eating off the floor was kinda gross, but you were starving!

40002760-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: A Wizard Reborn
40002760-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: So eating the floor-candy might not have been a such a good idea... It was a GREAT one. Sure it was weird that the mana overflowing from your body created an explosion that rocked the whole forest, but you feel AMAZING! Still, Kate seems really worried. You should talk to her.

40002761-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: What Do You Mean it Wasn't Candy?
40002761-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Contrary to you, who feels totally awesome, $npcName:11003925$ is worried. She took you back to Ellinel for a checkup, but you don't know what the big deal is. See what she has to say.

40002762-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Word of Mouth
40002762-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: According to Kate, what you thought was carelessly misplaced rock candy was actually a powerful magical object called a lapenshard. Apparently they make people stronger? Given your strange new situation, Kate proposes an idea.

40002763-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: What's a Wizard to Do?
40002763-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
Now that you're a lapenshard-enhanced wizard, $npcName:11003925$ suggests you join the Frontier Foundation to learn more about the lapenshards. Apparently the Frontier Foundation is an organization responsible for researching the lapenshards.

It could be worth considering. See what else Kate has to say!

40002764-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Professor Kate
40002764-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
Inspired by your battles against the forces of darkness, $npcName:11003925$ wonders aloud if she has a bigger part to play. After all, with the power of the lapenshards, any wizard could become strong enough to join the fight!

Wait... Kate's still talking?

40002765-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: If You Say So
40002765-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Kate says you should join the Frontier Foundation, and who are you to disagree? She's a pretty smart girl. That means it's time to say bye bye $npcName:11003925$ for now!

40002766-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: A Much-Needed Break
40002766-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: After a long and difficult journey, you decide to pay a visit to your old home on Halo Mountain in the hopes of encountering your friends. Much to your delight, there you encountered $npcName:11003952$ and $npcName:11001709$. It's about time you three caught up.

40002767-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Drifting Off
40002767-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: After you told them of your adventures since parting, your friends suggested that you get some well-deserved rest. That was when $npcName:11001709$ let something slip about events going in Maple World. $npcName:11003952$ said that was a discussion best left for later. Just what is going on?

40002768-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: A Power Sealed Within
40002768-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: You were about to ask $npcName:11003952$ what was going on when your head got a little foggy. Next thing you knew, you found yourself somewhere else and were met by a familiar face.

40002769-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Will to Power
40002769-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
It seems you were called into this inner space by $npcName:11003951$. There you learned that gems called "lapenshards" had appeared throughout Maple World.

Somehow related to the lapentas, these shards had awakened the power of the Munakra sealed within you. As this power grows, it threatens to break the shackles that bind it—the force of which could end your life. 

If you are to survive, you must free this power immediately. For that however, you need determination, and clarity of purpose. Speak with $npcName:11003951$ to learn more.

40002770-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Clarity of Purpose
40002770-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: I can't tell you whether you're worthy of the power of the Munakra or not but... Your intentions are true. Well then, let's begin.

40002771-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Power of the Munakra
40002771-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
With $npcName:11001560$'s aid, you succeeded in freeing the power of the Munakra sealed within you, saving your own life and unleashing new power.

You awakened to find $npcName:11001558$ and $npcName:11003949$ worrying over you. Speak with $npcName:11003949$.

40002772-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Unshackled and Empowered
40002772-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
When you came to your senses, you were lying in Guidance's lodgings on Halo Mountain. It seems you were out for some time. And according to your friends, the chi flowing through your body moves more powerfully than ever. 

Out of the corner of your eye you spot a familiar face... one you never expected to see here.

40002773-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: A Time for All Things
40002773-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Who's that over there? ...$npcName:11001560$?! Apparently as a bonus from unleashing the power of the Munakra, $npcName:11001560$ can come into the real world to chat. See what else $npcName:11001560$ has to say!

40002774-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Inside Information
40002774-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: You're a little worried about what it means to have $npcName:11001560$ walking about the real world unseen, but $npcName:11001560$ says not to worry about that right now. Your friends are probably worried about you. Why not talk with $npcName:11003952$?

40002775-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Walk Your Own Path
40002775-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
$npcName:11003952$ said he and Tinchai were getting ready to go help the "Frontier Foundation" with their investigation into the lapenshards. $npcName:11001558$ was taken aback by your knowledge of the lapenshards, but answered your questions about the Foundation anyway. 

With that matter settled, it seems that $npcName:11003952$ has an unusual request for you.

40002776-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Constant Companion
40002776-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
$npcName:11001558$ and $npcName:11003949$ have set off for the Frontier Foundation. Before you follow suit, you have unfinished business with $npcName:11003951$.

Speak with $npcName:11003951$.

40002777-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Strange Swordsman
40002777-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Upon arriving at the Frontier Foundation, you discovered a group of powerful-looking adventurers. As you take in the scenery, a long-haired swordsman strikes up a conversation with you. Speak with the $npcName:11003963$.

40002778-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: A Different Manner of Bladecraft
40002778-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Upon arriving at the Frontier Foundation, you discovered a group of powerful-looking adventurers. Say, is that person over there a swordsman like you? What's up with her shield? Go speak with the $npcName:11003955$.

40002779-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Little Miss Fancypants
40002779-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: You arrive at the Frontier Foundation and discover a group of tough-looking adventurers. They'd probably make a decent challenge. You asked if anyone wanted to spar, but some self-important little jerk started cramping on your style. Does this $npcName:11003956$ think she's better than you?

40002780-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Accosted By a Brute
40002780-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: You finally arrived at the Frontier Foundation, a place of true splendor. As you admire your surroundings, you can't help but be distracted by a loud and uncivilized individual shouting in your ear. What is such a person doing in a place like this?

40002781-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: A Matter of Methods
40002781-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: As you arrived at the Frontier Foundation, finding $npcName:11003932$ was still the first thing on your mind. Where did he go? Perhaps someone here can help you track him down?

40002782-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Magical Superiority
40002782-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
Wow the Frontier Foundation has so much free food, and it's all delicious! You decided to take a break from eating to explore the premise when you bumped into a real jerkwad. 

All you wanted to do was help out a stranger and the guy decided to bite your head off.

40002783-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Technical Superiority
40002783-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: You arrived at the Frontier Foundation and bumped into a hapless fellow with a dilemma only you could solve! You suggested the perfect solution, but naturally, an air-headed wizard couldn't help butting in.

40002784-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Wolf's New Fan
40002784-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: So you've arrived at the Frontier Foundation. There are a few people here who look really tough. Maybe they'd be up for a fight? But first maybe you should introduce yourself and let them know that you are in fact the famous Gray Wolf. It's only polite.

40002785-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: An Unusual Introduction
40002785-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: You finally arrived at the Frontier Foundation and marveled at its decadence. It's filled with strong-looking adventurers. But who is that strange man, and why is he approaching you?

40002786-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Opportunity and Motive
40002786-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: You arrived at the Frontier Foundation and found it packed to the gills with priceless junk. You could easily sneak off with a small fortune's worth of goodies, if it weren't for that nosy lady staring at you.

40002787-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: A Crime of Opportunity
40002787-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: You arrived at the Frontier Foundation only to discover a loud and obnoxious individual clearly casing the establishment. You can't help but feel angry about his blatant intent. You should keep an eye on him.

40002788-JobChange_02-.name: First Order of Business
40002788-JobChange_02-.desc: You've arrived in the new land, and already $npcName:11004341$ needs to see you. Check in with her and make sure everything is okay.

40002789-JobChange_02-.name: A Thorough Investigation
40002789-JobChange_02-.desc: $npcName:11004341$ has detected a source of lapenta energy on Kritias. How could it have come to be here? Speak with her to learn more.

40002790-JobChange_02-.name: Epiphany
40002790-JobChange_02-.desc: Sky Fortress doesn't have the manpower to investigate $npcName:11004341$'s unexpected readings. Go to the coordinates she provided and see if you can find the source of this lapenta energy.

40002791-JobChange_02-.name: Unknown yet Familiar
40002791-JobChange_02-.desc: There was a cave at the coordinates $npcName:11004341$ gave you. This place is stunning! Examine the strange light.

40002792-JobChange_02-.name: Instinct for Power
40002792-JobChange_02-.desc: The energy in the cave is strangely familiar. Examine the $npcName:11004339$.

40002793-JobChange_02-.name: An Inner Change
40002793-JobChange_02-.desc: The light of the lapenta energy is captivating. Without thinking, you reached out to touch it, and then...

40002794-JobChange_02-.name: A Powerful Resonance
40002794-JobChange_02-.desc: A change occurred within you after coming into contact with the lapenta energy. For now, go back to $npcName:11004341$ and give her your report.

40002795-JobChange_02-.name: Your New Self
40002795-JobChange_02-.desc: You're resonating with lapenta energy. With this new power, you feel ready to take on anything Kritias throws at you!

50001320-ShadowCataclysm-.name: Mission from the Empress
50001320-ShadowCataclysm-.desc: $npc:11000075$ needs to see you. Meet her in $map:02000025$.

50001321-ShadowCataclysm-.name: The Royal Lowdown
50001321-ShadowCataclysm-.desc: $npc:11000075$ has received disturbing reports from the Land of Darkness. Followers of the ancient Demon King have appeared. She wants you to venture into the Land of Darkness and discover the origin of these monsters.

50001330-ItemSocketSystem-.name: A Potent Light
50001330-ItemSocketSystem-.desc: $npcName:11000601$ has decided to tell you about gemstones, a kind of material that holds extraordinary power. Meet her in $map:02000025$ to learn how you can make their power your own.

50001510-PirateOcean-.name: Imperial Planning
50001510-PirateOcean-.desc: Empress $npcName:11001969$ has sent for you. Meet her at $map:52000087$.

50001511-PirateOcean-.name: Insights from the Sea
50001511-PirateOcean-.desc:
$npc:11001969$ is concerned that so little is known about the enemy. You've suggested checking with the sailors of the Adventurer's Guild to see if they've heard anything in their travels.

Go to the $map:02000068$ in $map:02000062$ and see what you can learn.

50001512-PirateOcean-.name: The Great Explorer
50001512-PirateOcean-.desc: $npcName:11000019$ doesn't know anything useful, but the famous explorer  But since the famous explorer $npcName:11003080$ is staying in the $map:52000095$. Ask if he's seen anything unusual in his travels.

50001513-PirateOcean-.name: An Ominous Warning
50001513-PirateOcean-.desc:
$npcName:11003080$ was injured in a pirate attack and is bedridden. While he hasn't seen the forces of darkness himself, he did hear a prophecy from the siren $npcName:24003002$ about a great disaster. You've decided to travel to $map:02000391$ and hear the rumor for yourself, but you'll need a ship and a good navigator to get there.

Go to $map:02000182$ and meet with $npcName:11003082$.

50001514-PirateOcean-.name: Chorrie's Bad Day
50001514-PirateOcean-.desc: $npcName:11003082$ is the only navigator who can get you to the sirens. He's also being attacked by pirates in his cabin. Perhaps you should lend him a hand.

50001515-PirateOcean-.name: Green-eyed Monsters
50001515-PirateOcean-.desc:
$npc:23000015$ targeted $npcName:11003080$ out of jealousy. It seems the pirate captain has a thing for $npcName:24003002$...

$npcName:11003082$ doesn't want anything to do with this business, but he's agreed to help you get to $map:02000391$ out of respect for $npcName:11003080$.

50001516-PirateOcean-.name: In Search of Sirens
50001516-PirateOcean-.desc:
$npcName:11003082$ is ready to set sail. Go to $map:02000391$ and meet with $npcName:24003002$. 

Use the Enter Dungeon button to travel to the dungeon regardless of your item level.
50001516-PirateOcean-.manual: Use Enter Dungeon button to go to $dungeonTitle:21022001$ and calm $npcName:24003001$ |Calm $npcName:24003002$
50001516-PirateOcean-.complete: Return to $map:52000096$ in $map:02000182$ and meet with $npcName:11003082$

50001517-PirateOcean-.name: A Meeting with Alvanos
50001517-PirateOcean-.desc:
The sirens intend to hijack the pirates' ship. Join $npcName:24003001$ in the attack, and then meet with $npcName:24002931$.

Use the Enter Dungeon button to travel to the dungeon regardless of your item level.
50001517-PirateOcean-.manual: Use Enter Dungeon button to go to $dungeonTitle:21023001$ and calm $npcName:24002931$

50001518-PirateOcean-.name: Guardian of the Seas
50001518-PirateOcean-.desc:
$npcName:24002931$ is calming. Use $npcName:24003002$'s power to drive away the mists and have a conversation with $npcName:24002931$.

Use the Enter Dungeon button to travel to the dungeon regardless of your item level.

50001519-PirateOcean-.name: The Explorer and the Sea
50001519-PirateOcean-.desc: Your meeting with $npcName:24002931$ was short, but it gave you plenty to think about. Meet with $npcName:11003080$ and tell him what the sirens are up to.

50001520-PirateOcean-.name: A Tale Untellable
50001520-PirateOcean-.desc: $npcName:11003080$ is giddy that you met $npcName:24002931$, but you can't possibly tell him about the vision you saw. Return to the $map:52000087$ in $map:02000001$ and report to Empress $npcName:11001969$.

50001530-SnowKingdom-.name: Captain's Calling
50001530-SnowKingdom-.desc: $npc:11000076$ is on a mission deep in the frozen wastes and has requested your help. Meet him at the $map:52000080$ in $map:02000261$.

50001531-SnowKingdom-.name: Unknown Enemy
50001531-SnowKingdom-.desc: $npcName:11000076$ was scouting the ice cave in $map:02000260$ when he encountered the forces of darkness. A $npcName:11003062$ appeared during the fight and left the captain with his injured. Head to the $map:52000081$ and look for clues.

50001532-SnowKingdom-.name: The Swordsman in the Cold
50001532-SnowKingdom-.desc:
You were trapped and surrounded in the $map:52000081$, but the $npcName:11003062$ appeared and gave you a chance to escape. Before he vanished into the blizzard, he warned you to go no further if you value your life.

Return to the $map:52000080$ and report this to $npc:11000076$.

50001533-SnowKingdom-.name: The Frozen Path
50001533-SnowKingdom-.desc: $npc:11003054$ has heard tales of $map:52000082$ and its $npcName:11003064$. He suggests you ask $npcName:11003060$, who was a citizen of the snow kingdom that used to be here, if there's a way through the frozen path.

50001534-SnowKingdom-.name: The Recluse Herbalist
50001534-SnowKingdom-.desc: $npcName:11003060$ knows of a potion that can make you resistant to the cold of the blizzard in $map:52000082$. Another yeti, $npcName:11003063$, knows how to make it. Find him at $map:02000263$.

50001535-SnowKingdom-.name: Burning Breath
50001535-SnowKingdom-.desc:
$npcName:11003063$ is not exactly happy with his former queen. You barely managed to convince him to make you the potion.

Of course, now you have to gather the ingredients for him.

50001536-SnowKingdom-.name: The Wavering Queen
50001536-SnowKingdom-.desc:
$npcName:11003063$ made you a bottle of $item:20000451$ that will let you pass through $map:52000082$. The potion's effects are temporarily, so be sure to use it just before you enter! Once you enter the $map:52000083$, continue your investigation.

If you need more $item:20000451$, go to $npcName:11003063$ in $map:02000263$.
50001536-SnowKingdom-.manual: Drink $item:20000451$ and search $map:52000083$ at the end of $map:52000082$

50001537-SnowKingdom-.name: The Queen's Knight
50001537-SnowKingdom-.desc: Long ago, $npcName:11003060$ was the palace gatekeeper for the kingdom of snow. $npcName:11003065$ needs his help to get to the $map:52000085$, where $npc:11003069$ is. Since $npcName:11003065$ is injured, deliver her message to $npcName:11003060$ and go to the $map:52000085$ in her place.

50001538-SnowKingdom-.name: The Raging Snowstorm
50001538-SnowKingdom-.desc:
$npc:11003060$ says that the $map:52000085$ guards the path to the $map:52000086$, where the snow kingdom's secret treasure was kept. He's worried that the specter who appeared to $npcName:11003069$ is connected to the darkness and is using her to get the treasure.

Enter the hidden cave door in $map:02000260$ to join $npcName:11003060$ at the $map:52000084$, then investigate the $map:52000085$.
50001538-SnowKingdom-.manual: Enter $map:52000084$ through the hidden path in $map:02000260$ and investigate $map:52000085$

50001539-SnowKingdom-.name: To the Temple
50001539-SnowKingdom-.desc: $npc:11003069$ opened the path to the temple, but the vault to the Frozen Crystal is still locked. It seems likely that the forces of darkness are manipulating events here. Get ready to leave for the $map:52000086$ with $npcName:11003060$.

50001540-SnowKingdom-.name: Frost and Shadow
50001540-SnowKingdom-.desc: Meet $npcName:11003060$ at the $map:52000086$. You can get there through the passageway on the tallest, steepest part of $map:02000263$.
50001540-SnowKingdom-.complete: Return to $map:52000080$ in $map:02000261$ and report to $npc:11000076$

50001541-SnowKingdom-.name: The Captain's Concern
50001541-SnowKingdom-.desc:
$npcName:11000076$ is sorry that he was too busy to help with the investigation. He's also concerned that the enemy seems to preparing for something, and he has no idea what it is.

He's received recall orders back to $map:02000001$. Speak with $npcName:11003060$ in the $map:52000080$.

50001542-SnowKingdom-.name: Those Who Remain
50001542-SnowKingdom-.desc:
$npcName:11003069$ has resealed the path to the $map:02000383$ and sends you her thanks. $npcName:11003060$ will return to his business in $map:02000001$, but he'll be sure to keep an eye on things back at his old home.

Return to $map:52000087$ in $map:02000001$ and report to Empress $npcName:11001969$.

50001550-Quest2017-.name: Dilemma
50001550-Quest2017-.desc: $npc:11000119$ and $npc:11000074$ can't agree on what to do about the attack on $map:02000076$. Perhaps you can provide $npc:11000075$ with an alternative solution.

50001551-Quest2017-.name: Crisis in Henesys
50001551-Quest2017-.desc:
You volunteered to provide reinforcements for $map:02000076$, which is under attack from the forces of darkness. Help $npcName:11000001$ and $npcName:11000015$ defeat the invaders.

Talk to $npcName:11000075$ in $map:52000033$ to join the battle.
50001551-Quest2017-.manual:
Defend $map:52000120$
(Speak with $npcName:11000075$ in the $map:52000033$ to begin)

50001552-Quest2017-.name: Elder's Request
50001552-Quest2017-.desc: $npcName:11000015$ thanks you for defending $map:02000076$. However, the town has sustained some damage, and they need help getting back on their feet. Speak with $npc:11000001$.

50001553-Quest2017-.name: An Immature Son
50001553-Quest2017-.desc: $npcName:11000001$ wants you to bring his son $npcName:11000502$ home. As one of the Seven Heroes, it seems the elder holds his son to extremely high expectations, and now he's worried the boy will do something rash. $npcName:11000502$ may be at $map:02000027$.

50001554-Quest2017-.name: In Search of Armano
50001554-Quest2017-.desc: $npc:11000273$ claims that $npcName:11000502$ hasn't been in to see him all day. $npcName:11000961$ is supposedly $npcName:11000502$'s childhood friend. You may as well deliver the doctor's $item:30000767$ to her in $map:02000076$ when you go to question her.
50001554-Quest2017-.manual: Search the cabinet in $map:02000027$ and take $item:30000767$

50001555-Quest2017-.name: The Hero's Son
50001555-Quest2017-.desc: $npcName:11000961$ is surprised that you're looking for $npcName:11000502$. She knows he has a bad reputation, but it's because he tries so hard to live up to his father's legacy. She hasn't seen him since he fought with his father at the hospital, but she's certain he's still in $map:02000076$ somewhere.

50001556-Quest2017-.name: Henesys at a Glance
50001556-Quest2017-.desc:
$npcName:11000478$ lives at the top of the hill in $map:02000076$. He says it's easy to see what's going on in town if you look through a telescope.

If you still can't find $npcName:11000502$ after using the telescope, try asking $npcName:11000189$ if he's been by her cornfield.

50001557-Quest2017-.name: A Corny Greeting
50001557-Quest2017-.desc: $npcName:11000189$ has a mischievous streak. She'll tell you where to find what you're after... but only if you give her corn stalks a pep talk! You can greet by typing /greet in the chat window or pressing the F1 key.
50001557-Quest2017-.manual: Greet $npcName:11000189$'s corn in $map:02000076$ by pressing the F1 key or typing /greet in the chat window.

50001558-Quest2017-.name: A Helpful Fellow
50001558-Quest2017-.desc:
$npcName:11000189$ always keeps her promises, no matter how strange they are. She tells you that $npcName:11000502$ ran off to get reinforcements from Dark Wind. While he may think that's a great idea, you know that $map:02000100$ is still recovering from the attack, and Dark Wind is in no position to help out.

It seems that $npcName:11000189$'s contact is a gaudily dressed man in $map:02000083$. See if you can find him.

50001559-Quest2017-.name: Den of Thieves
50001559-Quest2017-.desc:
$npcName:11000101$ is trying to pretend he doesn't know $npcName:11000502$. Luckily for you, he's also a complete idiot. It was easy to get the information you needed from him.

It sounds like $npcName:11000502$ is being held in $map:02000243$. You'll have to go through $map:02000241$ to get there.

50001560-Quest2017-.name: The Dupe
50001560-Quest2017-.desc: $npcName:11000173$ confesses to trying to kidnap $npcName:11000502$. However, the elder's son slipped away in the chaos and escaped to $map:02000134$.

50001561-Quest2017-.name: Never Empty-handed
50001561-Quest2017-.desc: $npcName:11000502$ went into the $map:02000224$ in $map:02000134$. He refuses to go home until you get the $itemPlural:20000050$ from the monsters there.

50001562-Quest2017-.name: Another Crisis
50001562-Quest2017-.desc:
$npcName:11000502$ finally agreed to go home, but only if you remembered the fact that he was the real hero today. You were about to agree when $npcName:11000961$ suddenly appeared. It seems $npcName:11000001$ has gone to face the remaining forces of darkness himself.

$npcName:11000502$ has a worrying fire burning in his eyes. Hurry to $map:02000054$.

50001563-Quest2017-.name: A Father's Heart
50001563-Quest2017-.desc: You reached $map:02000054$, where $npcName:11000961$'s sister-in-arms $npcName:11000786$ is wounded. $npcName:11000001$ and $npcName:11000015$ are outgunned in $map:52000121$. Hurry to their side!

50001564-Quest2017-.name: A Late Regret
50001564-Quest2017-.desc: $npcName:11000001$ was injured protecting his son. $npcName:11000502$ wanted to seek revenge, but $npcName:11000015$ and $npcName:11000119$ stopped him. While he's off sulking, you should find out what $npcName:11001838$ is doing here.

50001565-Quest2017-.name: The Next Plan
50001565-Quest2017-.desc: $npcName:11001838$ is thrilled that he's one step closer to being a real guard, but he's not any closer to reaching $npc:11000119$'s standards. Speak with $npcName:11000119$ about your next moves.

50001566-Quest2017-.name: Farewell for Now
50001566-Quest2017-.desc:
$npcName:11001838$ is surprised that you volunteered to go to the $map:02000146$. He promises that he'll become a great guard someday.

Hurry to the $map:02000146$ and meet $npc:11000076$.

50001567-Quest2017-.name: Shadow Research
50001567-Quest2017-.desc:
The work at the $map:02000146$ isn't going very well. You can help by getting $npcName:11000264$ some materials for his research. 

Gather $itemPlural:20000047$ from the monsters at the center of the $map:02000146$, then bring them to $npcName:11000264$.

50001568-Quest2017-.name: The Research Resumes
50001568-Quest2017-.desc: $npcName:11000264$ is impressed that you collected the $itemPlural:20000047$ so quickly. As you were discussing the situation, $npcName:11000032$ of $map:02000023$ appeared. See what he wants.

50001569-Quest2017-.name: A Dark Threat
50001569-Quest2017-.desc: The $map:02000146$ used to be the Door of Light. $npcName:11000032$'s research is about finding a way to fight the darkness that is threatening the world. Now that $npcName:11000264$ is done analyzing the $itemPlural:20000047$, see what he's learned.

50001570-Quest2017-.name: A Blue Light in the Darkness
50001570-Quest2017-.desc: It seems that an unknown glowing substance is either a byproduct or component of $item:20000047$. $npcName:11000264$ has never seen anything like it, but when he questioned $npcName:11000032$ on the matter, $npcName:11000032$ merely asked him if the $itemPlural:20000016$ were ready.

50001571-Quest2017-.name: The Most Dangerous Garden
50001571-Quest2017-.desc:
$itemPlural:20000016$ are made from the $itemPlural:20000045$ that thrive in this place. They're usually hard to farm, but $npcName:11000032$ managed to make a patch of magical soil that they grow in. The $itemPlural:20000045$ would be a piece of cake to harvest... if it weren't for the monsters crowding the garden in front of the $map:02000026$.

Go pick some $itemPlural:20000045$ for $npcName:11000264$.
50001571-Quest2017-.manual: Pick $itemPlural:20000045$ in garden of the $map:02000026$ at the $map:02000146$

50001572-Quest2017-.name: The Amazing Invention
50001572-Quest2017-.desc: $npcName:11000264$ claims that his new medicine formula is super effective and easy to make. Put the $itemPlural:20000045$ in the mixer and try making the $itemPlural:20000016$ yourself.

50001573-Quest2017-.name: An Unknown Substance
50001573-Quest2017-.desc: $npcName:11000032$ is returning to $map:02000023$ to confer with the headmaster, $npc:11000031$. Speak with him to come along.
50001573-Quest2017-.complete:
Speak with $npcName:11000031$ in $map:52000134$
(If you leave by mistake, talk to $npc:11000033$ again to return.)

50001580-Quest2017-.name: Fruits of Research
50001580-Quest2017-.desc:
$npc:11000031$, the headmaster of $map:52000133$, welcomes you to the campus. Listen in as $npcName:11000032$'s delivers his report.

If you leave by mistake, talk to $npc:11000033$ in $map:02000023$ to return.
50001580-Quest2017-.complete:
Speak with $npcName:11003282$ in $map:52000134$
(If you leave by mistake, talk to $npc:11000033$ again to return.)

50001581-Quest2017-.name: Einos's Hypothesis
50001581-Quest2017-.desc: $npcName:11000032$ believes that the substance coming from the $item:20000045$ is the means by which the power of darkness spreads, and he thinks he can prove it. Go to $map:52000135$ and observe his experiment.
50001581-Quest2017-.complete:
Speak with $npcName:11003250$ in $map:52000135$
(If you leave by mistake, talk to $npc:11000033$ again to return.)

50001582-Quest2017-.name: The Excellent Student
50001582-Quest2017-.desc:
The forces of darkness have attacked $map:02000023$, but $npc:11000031$ managed to keep $map:02000023$ safe with a magical shield. His strength is waning, so you need to hurry.

At $npcName:11000031$'s request, work with the academy's star citizen in $map:52000101$.

If you leave by mistake, talk to $npc:11000033$ in $map:02000023$ again to return.
50001582-Quest2017-.complete:
