Meet the academy's star student at $map:52000133$
(If you leave by mistake, talk to $npc:11000033$ to return.)

50001583-Quest2017-.name: A Fresh Start
50001583-Quest2017-.desc:
$npcName:11003146$, star student of $map:52000101$, insists that you purify your body in the spring since you've picked up all kinds of minor curses while fighting the darkness. Take a nice, relaxing soak.

If you leave by mistake, talk to $npc:11000033$ in $map:02000023$ again to return.
50001583-Quest2017-.complete:
Speak with $npcName:11003146$ in $map:52000133$
(If you leave by mistake, talk to $npc:11000033$ again to return.)

50001584-Quest2017-.name: Totem Repair Duty
50001584-Quest2017-.desc:
The barrier around the academy is reinforced by magic totems. These totems are especially fragile, so the students of Ellinel often have to repair them. $npcName:11003146$ sent $npcName:11000284$ to $map:02000006$ to do some totem repairs, but she hasn't come back. Check in with her close underclassman, $npcName:11000029$, in $map:02000023$.

If you leave by mistake, talk to $npc:11000033$ in $map:02000023$ again to return.

50001585-Quest2017-.name: Cheer Up, Arwen
50001585-Quest2017-.desc: $npcName:11000029$ admits that $npcName:11000284$ can be slow sometimes, but it's only because she wants to do a good job. It's possible she's still in $map:02000006$. Take the $item:30000768$ and travel to $map:02000006$ to meet $npcName:11000284$.

50001586-Quest2017-.name: Unexpected Difficulties
50001586-Quest2017-.desc:
$npcName:11000284$ visited one of the locals, $npcName:11000304$, for help. Unfortunately, $npcName:11000304$ doesn't seem to want any visitors. If you defeat the $npcPlural:33000006$ that are roaming the area, it might prove your good intentions to her.

Once you're done with the monsters, find $npcName:11000304$ in the $map:02000073$.

50001587-Quest2017-.name: The Witch's Riddle
50001587-Quest2017-.desc:
$npcName:11000304$ ridiculed $npcName:11000284$ for failing to solve the riddle. Now it's your turn:

"Two divine creatures lost their hearts when darkness fell. End their pain and redeem the forsaken soul"

What does this riddle mean? Return to $npcName:11000284$ and find the answer together.

50001588-Quest2017-.name: The Wrong Answer
50001588-Quest2017-.desc: $npcName:11000284$ thought she had the answer, but she failed. Her answer makes some sense to you, so you've left to investigate. Search the $map:02000074$.

50001589-Quest2017-.name: The Forsaken
50001589-Quest2017-.desc:
You bumped into $npcName:11003146$ in the $map:02000074$, and she figured out the answer to the riddle in a snap.

Go to $map:02000089$ and defeat $npcName:22000038$. Once that's done, meet with $npcName:11000285$.

50001590-Quest2017-.name: A Turtle's Tears
50001590-Quest2017-.desc: $npcName:11000285$ is heartbroken. The day the darkness fell, monsters trampled over the precious flowers that mark the memory of his true love. Save the dying flowers on his behalf.

50001591-Quest2017-.name: The Soul Key
50001591-Quest2017-.desc:
$npcName:11000285$ remembers a mage who dealt in forbidden magic to be with the one he loved. Even when the world called him a villain, he wanted his power to make the world a better place. His power is still hidden in the place where he fell...

Could this power be the thing that's hiding in the $map:02000074$? Return to the $map:02000074$ in $map:02000006$.

50001592-Quest2017-.name: Box of Magic
50001592-Quest2017-.desc: $npcName:11003146$ is gone, but she's left a note behind, as well as some sort of magical box. She also writes that the riddle was easy for her because she's great, and not because $npcName:11000284$ is lacking in any way. For now, check out the box in the $map:02000074$ in $map:02000006$ and then meet $npcName:11000284$ in $map:02000006$.
50001592-Quest2017-.manual: Check the magic box in the $map:02000074$ in $map:02000006$.

50001593-Quest2017-.name: The Aid of the Light
50001593-Quest2017-.desc: The magic box you found is now a totem supporting the headmaster's magic barrier. $npcName:11000284$ is relieved that the situation is finally resolved. Head back to $map:02000023$ and report to $npcName:11000033$.

50001594-Quest2017-.name: Attack from Within
50001594-Quest2017-.desc: $npcName:11000033$ says that something has started attacking the barrier from within. He suspects the disturbance is coming from $map:02000312$, an old dark fairy temple. He sent one of his students, $npcName:11000876$, to $map:02000024$ to check it out.

50001595-Quest2017-.name: Sweet Tooth
50001595-Quest2017-.desc: $npcName:11000876$ asked $npcName:11000293$, the eldest of the creatures here, for clues, but $npcName:11000293$ simply smiled. $npcName:11000876$ is certain that some sweets will jog the creature's memory. Defeat the monsters in $map:02000024$ and gather $itemPlural:20000052$ from the nearby boxes.

50001596-Quest2017-.name: The Seed of Darkness
50001596-Quest2017-.desc: $npcName:11000293$ feels good after eating the $itemPlural:20000052$. He recalls seeing the entrance to $map:02000312$ behind the waterfall at the center of this place. Complete your investigation, then return to $npcName:11000033$ in $map:02000023$.

50001597-Quest2017-.name: Ellinel Express
50001597-Quest2017-.desc: You need to report your findings to $npc:11000031$. To get back to Ellinel, you need to take the Ellinel Express from $map:02000023$. Apparently, you'll need to find the littlest mage in $map:02000023$ to depart.

50001598-Quest2017-.name: The Mages of Ellinel
50001598-Quest2017-.desc:
The littlest mage in $map:02000023$ is $npcName:11003257$, a pretty kitty on a red cushion. After traveling via the Ellinel Express, you met $npcName:11003146$ in $map:52000101$. She tried to drop more work in your lap, but $npcName:11000032$ appeared and asked her to get a report from you.

$npcName:11003146$ is fuming. Go ahead and talk to her.

50001599-Quest2017-.name: The Missing Child
50001599-Quest2017-.desc:
One of the elementary students, $npcName:11001165$, got into the lab storage room and stole an experimental potion. He left behind a note claiming that he'll be a great hero someday... but $npcName:11000032$ is worried that the stolen potion is actually a shadow reagent that could take the child's life.

Meet with $npcName:11001167$, who is looking for his younger brother in $map:02000101$.

50001600-Quest2017-.name: Dang Kids
50001600-Quest2017-.desc: $npcName:11001166$'s older brother, $npcName:11001167$, is worried because his attempts to frighten his little brother straight only made the kid more bold. He'll search to the north while you search to the south of $map:02000101$.

50001601-Quest2017-.name: Think of the Children
50001601-Quest2017-.desc: $npcName:11001166$ and his friends went into the forest to investigate some shadows he saw, but they got separated. He made it out, but his friends are still in there. Enter $map:02000331$ and help $npcName:11001166$ save his fellow kids.

50001602-Quest2017-.name: A Child's Request
50001602-Quest2017-.desc:
$npcName:11003253$ confesses that she drank the potion $npcName:11001166$ brought, thinking it was a mana potion. She also wants to know what kind of snacks $npcName:11003257$ likes...

Speak with $npcName:11003257$ to return to Ellinel.

50001603-Quest2017-.name: Ellinel in Shadow
50001603-Quest2017-.desc:
$npcName:11003257$ says that a huge cloud of dark magic is covering Ellinel, blinding her to whatever is happening in the campus. Her attempt to teleport you directly to $npcName:11000032$ failed, though she thinks she can get you to $npcName:11003146$.

If you leave by mistake, talk to $npc:11003257$ in $map:02000023$ to return.
50001603-Quest2017-.complete:
Speak with $npcName:11003146$ in $map:52000100$
(If you leave by mistake, talk to $npc:11003257$ in $map:02000023$ to return.)

50001604-Quest2017-.name: Two Faces of Einos
50001604-Quest2017-.desc:
Darkness has engulfed $map:52000136$ and driven $npcName:11000032$ into a feral rage. $npcName:11003146$ is still in shock and doesn't know what to do with herself. Shadow magic flows from $map:52000137$, where only $npcName:11000031$ and $npcName:11000032$ remain. It's time for you to see this for yourself.

If you leave by mistake, talk to $npc:11003257$ in $map:02000023$ to return.
50001604-Quest2017-.manual:
Fight the dark creature in $map:52000137$
(If you leave by mistake, talk to $npc:11003257$ in $map:02000023$ to return.)

50001605-Quest2017-.name: Whereabouts Unknown
50001605-Quest2017-.desc:
The scholars of Ellinel believe $npcName:11000032$'s transformation is related to his research. Based on her research as $map:02000001$'s head librarian, $npcName:11000005$ suspects that a shadow seed may have been involved. The mere suggestion seems to have upset $npcName:11003146$...

Finish your conversation with $npcName:11000005$.

50001606-Quest2017-.name: What's Left Behind
50001606-Quest2017-.desc: $npcName:11000005$ is convinced that a mage of $npcName:11000032$'s caliber would have noticed the changes he was undergoing. It's impossible to return to Ellinel, but he did maintain an off-site workspace in $map:02000109$. Search for any records or notes while $npcName:11000033$ and $npcName:11000005$ work on restoring the Ellinel Express.

50001607-Quest2017-.name: The Source of Darkness
50001607-Quest2017-.desc: You found $npcName:11003265$ in a hidden compartment. According to these notes, the strange blue light found on many of the objects and substances around the $map:02000146$ is actually a contagious form of darkness. This power is focused and spreading from the $map:02000326$. Hurry there and cut off the supply of darkness before it spreads further.
50001607-Quest2017-.manual: Search the space behind the waterfall

50001608-Quest2017-.name: Spreading Danger
50001608-Quest2017-.desc:
While reading $npcName:11000032$'s notes, you found evidence that someone else had already been there—including a lost $item:30000769$. You'll have to be sure to give it back to $npcName:11003146$ when you see her again.

Hurry to the $map:02000146$ and warn $npcName:11000076$ of the danger.

50001609-Quest2017-.name: A Critical Moment
50001609-Quest2017-.desc: You arrived at the $map:02000146$, but $npc:11000076$ was already on a mission to the $map:02000213$ to investigate. Hurry there and defeat whoever is behind this spreading darkness.
50001609-Quest2017-.manual: Defeat the source of darkness at the $dungeonTitle:20006001$

50001610-Quest2017-.name: The Flow of Darkness
50001610-Quest2017-.desc:
$npc:11000076$ has brought you up to speed on the happenings around the $map:02000146$. The monster attacks are growing more vicious, and a new disease is spreading alongside the shadow poisons. Thus far, only $npcName:11000264$ and his research associates have managed to slow the infection.

Speak with $npcName:11000264$.

50001611-Quest2017-.name: A Bright New Crisis
50001611-Quest2017-.desc:
$npcName:11000264$ is shocked after hearing about what happened in $map:02000023$.

$npc:11000076$ wants to talk strategy.

50001612-Quest2017-.name: A Regret Too Late
50001612-Quest2017-.desc: Return to the $map:02000146$ and tell $npc:11000076$ about the loss of another one of the Seven Heroes.

50001613-Quest2017-.name: The Guard Captain's Request
50001613-Quest2017-.desc: $npc:11000119$ has requested your help in $map:02000001$. What's so urgent that the captain of the guard needs your help?

50001621-Quest2017_2-.name: Under the Palace
50001621-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000057$ and her minions have kidnapped $npc:11000074$ and vanished into the $map:02000252$. While the guard prepare their assault, go to the $map:02000252$ and keep an eye on $npcName:11000057$'s forces.

50001622-Quest2017_2-.name: A Meeting with the Minister
50001622-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000119$ says that $npc:11000074$ wants to thank you, and suggests that you go meet him. Go to the $map:02000065$ in $map:02000001$ and meet with $npcName:11000074$.

50001623-Quest2017_2-.name: The Minister's Choice
50001623-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000057$ is $npcName:11000074$'s daughter. While he is a loyalist to the throne, she seeks to spread chaos and uproot the empire. He asks you not to tell anyone else that $npcName:11000057$ was here, but you can't shake the feeling that there's something he's not telling you...

50001624-Quest2017_2-.name: Royal Magics
50001624-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11003432$ has come to $npcName:11000074$'s office to borrow the Scroll of $map:02000001$, a manuscript kept by the royal mages. He had it hidden in $map:02000218$ to keep it safe from thieves. Go fetch it while $npcName:11003432$ and $npcName:11000074$ discuss another important matter.

50001625-Quest2017_2-.name: Mind of a Minister
50001625-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000530$ gave you the $item:30000870$, and asked you to give the minister his regards. Return to $npcName:11003432$ in the $map:02000065$.
50001625-Quest2017_2-.complete: Return to $map:02000065$ in $map:02000001$ and speak with $npcName:11003432$

50001630-Quest2017_2-.name: Happy News
50001630-Quest2017_2-.desc:
$npcName:11003432$ has invited you to go with her to see $npcName:11000032$, who's suddenly returned.

If you leave by mistake, use the $npcName:11003497$ next to $npcName:11003257$ in $map:02000023$ to return.
50001630-Quest2017_2-.complete:
Speak with $npcName:11003433$ in $map:52000102$
<font color="#909090">If you leave by mistake, use the $npcName:11003497$ next to $npcName:11003257$ in $map:02000023$ to return</font>

50001631-Quest2017_2-.name: The Return of Einos
50001631-Quest2017_2-.desc:
$npcName:11000032$ is recovering in the $map:52000149$ and still hasn't woken up. Go see how he's doing.

If you leave by mistake, use the $npcName:11003497$ next to $npcName:11003257$ in $map:02000023$ to return.
50001631-Quest2017_2-.complete:
Speak with $npcName:11003438$ inside the $map:52000149$
<font color="#909090">If you leave by mistake, use the $npcName:11003497$ next to $npcName:11003257$ in $map:02000023$ to return</font>

50001632-Quest2017_2-.name: The Unspeakable Truth
50001632-Quest2017_2-.desc:
According to $npcName:11003433$'s research, a great divine being placed an emissary in every dimension to guide and direct that world. These so-called "Innocents" possess the capability for both good and evil, and at some point must choose which of the two they will follow.

He thinks that $npcName:11000032$ is one of these Innocents, and that exposure to the Land of Darkness caused his evil side to temporarily awaken. He's asked you to keep this a secret for now, in order to prevent panic from spreading through $map:02000023$.

If you leave by mistake, use the $npcName:11003497$ next to $npcName:11003257$ in $map:02000023$ to return.
50001632-Quest2017_2-.complete:
Speak with $npcName:11003433$ in the $map:52000149$
<font color="#909090">If you leave by mistake, use the $npcName:11003497$ next to $npcName:11003257$ in $map:02000023$ to return</font>

50001633-Quest2017_2-.name: Life Magic: Study 1
50001633-Quest2017_2-.desc:
$npcName:11003433$ is researching life magic in hopes of finding a way to cure $npcName:11000032$. First, he needs $item:30000179$. Find some for him while he reviews the book $npcName:11003432$ borrowed on his behalf.

If you leave by mistake, use the $npcName:11003497$ next to $npcName:11003257$ in $map:02000023$ to return.

50001635-Quest2017_2-.name: Life Magic: Study 3
50001635-Quest2017_2-.desc: The last item $npcName:11000033$ needs for his treatment is $item:30000190$. Get it from $npcName:23100025$ in the $map:02000206$.

50001640-Quest2017_2-.name: A Twisted Road
50001640-Quest2017_2-.desc:
$npcName:11003442$ attempted to teleport you to $npcName:11000033$ for the healing ritual, but some sort of interference caused you to appear in the $map:52000150$, instead.

If you leave by mistake, use the $npcName:11003497$ next to $npcName:11003257$ in $map:02000023$ to return.
50001640-Quest2017_2-.complete:
Speak with $npcName:11000033$ in $map:52000150$
<font color="#909090">If you leave by mistake, use the $npcName:11003497$ next to $npcName:11003257$ in $map:02000023$ to return</font>

50001641-Quest2017_2-.name: Seed of Uncertainty
50001641-Quest2017_2-.desc:
While $npcName:11003438$ was moving $npcName:11000032$ to the $map:02000179$, his teleportation spell was blocked and he had to take a detour through the $map:52000150$. Hold off the attacking monsters while he keeps $npcName:11000032$ safe.

If you leave by mistake, use the $npcName:11003497$ next to $npcName:11003257$ in $map:02000023$ to return.
50001641-Quest2017_2-.complete:
Speak with $npcName:11003440$ in $map:52000150$
<font color="#909090">If you leave by mistake, use the $npcName:11003497$ next to $npcName:11003257$ in $map:02000023$ to return</font>

50001642-Quest2017_2-.name: Defend the Forest
50001642-Quest2017_2-.desc:
$npcName:11000068$ is trying to enter the $map:02000179$ through the $map:02000066$. If he succeeds, all of $map:02000023$ will be in danger!

If you leave by mistake, use the $npcName:11003497$ next to $npcName:11003257$ in $map:02000023$ to return.
50001642-Quest2017_2-.complete:
Speak with $npcName:11000033$ in $map:02000179$
<font color="#909090">If you leave by mistake, use the $npcName:11003497$ next to $npcName:11003257$ in $map:02000023$ to return</font>

50001650-Quest2017_2-.name: Shrouded in Mystery
50001650-Quest2017_2-.desc:
$npcName:11003439$ needs a book called the "Dimensional Dictionary" to cross-reference his research on the Innocents. Unfortunately, the book's owner doesn't seem keen to lend it out. See if you can convince $npcName:11000282$ of the $map:02000019$ in $map:02000215$ to part ways with it.

If you leave by mistake, use the $npcName:11003497$ next to $npcName:11003257$ in $map:02000023$ to return.

50001651-Quest2017_2-.name: The Librarian's Game
50001651-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000282$ thinks you're no better than a thief for somehow knowing what books he has without asking first. However, if you can find the Dimensional Dictionary on your own, he may be willing to talk. Search inside the $map:02000019$.

50001652-Quest2017_2-.name: The Magic of Reading
50001652-Quest2017_2-.desc:
Someone has put a book in the wrong bookcase, and the $npcName:11000670$ is quite perturbed about the whole matter. Take the $item:30000082$ from the bookcase and return it to its proper location.

You'll need to get the key to the bookcase from a $npcName:21000216$.

50001653-Quest2017_2-.name: The Hidden Room
50001653-Quest2017_2-.desc: The Dimensional Dictionary has been enchanted so that nobody can read it. Even $npcName:11000282$, the book's owner, has no idea what it says. If you can come up with a way to dispel the enchantment, maybe you could convince him to lend it to you...

50001660-Quest2017_2-.name: Clash of Wills
50001660-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000705$ of the $map:02000129$ knows how to remove the enchantment on the Dimensional Dictionary, but she's refused to help $npcName:11000282$ do it. Perhaps you can convince her to help you, instead.

50001661-Quest2017_2-.name: The Lost Ladle
50001661-Quest2017_2-.desc: Mischievous monsters have stolen $npcName:11000705$'s cooking utensil and hid it near $map:02000129$'s waterfall. Find $item:30000204$ on her behalf.
50001661-Quest2017_2-.manual: Find $item:30000204$ in the grass near $map:02000129$'s waterfall

50001662-Quest2017_2-.name: A Word to the Wise
50001662-Quest2017_2-.desc:
According to $npcName:11000705$, you need $npc:22000007$'s $item:30000186$ in order to read the Dimensional Dictionary. She's also insistent that you be the one to open the book when you get it...

Head to $map:02000180$ and get the $item:30000186$.

50001663-Quest2017_2-.name: The Livid Librarian
50001663-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000282$ has agreed to let you read the Dimensional Dictionary with him in the $map:02000219$. Remember, you are supposed to open the book first.

50001664-Quest2017_2-.name: The Librarian's Defeat
50001664-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11003444$ is frustrated because he still can't read the book. He's agreed to lend it to you under the condition that you return with a transcription. It's time to return to $map:02000023$ and meet with $npcName:11000033$.

50001665-Quest2017_2-.name: Deciphering the Meaning
50001665-Quest2017_2-.desc:
Not even $npcName:11000033$ could read the book! There's a chance that $npcName:11000032$ is immune to the effects of the enchantment. Show him the Dimensional Dictionary.

If you leave by mistake, you can talk to $npc:11000033$ in $map:02000023$ to return.
50001665-Quest2017_2-.complete:
Meet with $npc:11003445$ in $map:02000179$
<font color="#909090">If you leave by mistake, you can talk to $npcName:11000033$ in $map:02000023$ to return.</font>

50001666-Quest2017_2-.name: Dark Forces: A Study
50001666-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11003445$ has received reports that many of the divine creatures of Maple World have fallen under the influence of dark magic. Meet with $npcName:11000033$ in $map:02000023$ and come up with a plan to confirm this report.

50001667-Quest2017_2-.name: Dark Forces: Study 1
50001667-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000033$ has heard that two of the ancient creatures of the forest have been acting up, and he'd like to begin by looking into $npcName:23100041$. Travel to $map:02000079$ and find out if the report is true.
50001667-Quest2017_2-.manual: Defeat $npc:23100041$, the ancient divine creature, in $dungeonTitle:20013001$

50001668-Quest2017_2-.name: Dark Forces: Study 2
50001668-Quest2017_2-.desc: Next, you need to check on $npcName:23100021$, who has been indiscriminately attacking passersby. Go to $map:02000316$ and see what you can learn.
50001668-Quest2017_2-.manual: Check on $npc:23000021$, who became wild in $dungeonTitle:20003001$

50001669-Quest2017_2-.name: Dark Forces: A Revelation
50001669-Quest2017_2-.desc:
$npcName:11000032$ needs to speak with you. Meet him in the $map:02000179$.

If you leave by mistake, talk to $npc:11000033$ in $map:02000023$ to return.
50001669-Quest2017_2-.complete:
Meet with $npc:11003445$ in $map:02000179$
<font color="#909090">If you leave by mistake, you can talk to $npcName:11000033$ in $map:02000023$ to return.</font>

50001670-Quest2017_2-.name: Crystal Clarity
50001670-Quest2017_2-.desc:
While studying the Dimensional Dictionary, $npcName:11003445$ learned of a kind of magic crystal that can reveal answers to the questions that wear on the user's mind. He made such a crystal, so take a look.

If you leave by mistake, use the $npcName:11003497$ next to $npcName:11003257$ in $map:02000023$ to return.
50001670-Quest2017_2-.manual:
Look into the crystal
<font color="#909090">If you leave by mistake, you can either talk to $npcName:11000033$ or use the $npcName:11003497$ next to $npcName:11003257$ in $map:02000023$</font>

50001671-Quest2017_2-.name: Tracking the Truth
50001671-Quest2017_2-.desc:
$npcName:11003445$'s crystal showed you $npcName:11000044$, who seems to be looking for $npcName:11000526$. You need to find out how he's connected to the forces of darkness... and if Dark Wind is hiding something. Go to $map:02000157$ and speak to $npc:11000065$.

If you leave by mistake, use the $npcName:11003497$ next to $npcName:11003257$ in $map:02000023$ to return.

50001672-Quest2017_2-.name: A Personal Request
50001672-Quest2017_2-.desc:
According to $npcName:11000361$, $npc:11000065$ won't see anybody without an appointment, and he's not accepting any new appointments at the moment. If you want to get to the mayor, you'll have to curry favor with $npcName:11000361$ first...

Go to $map:02000008$ and check on her younger sister, $npcName:11000868$.

50001673-Quest2017_2-.name: Dashed Dreams
50001673-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000868$ didn't expect her job to involve so many monsters. Her boss wants a report on the monsters' physical composition, but she can't stand to go near them. Defeat them and gather $itemPlural:30000872$ for her.

50001674-Quest2017_2-.name: The New Hire
50001674-Quest2017_2-.desc:
$npcName:11000868$ wants you to deliver her report to her boss, $npcName:11000869$. She also wants you to mention how she did a great job.

Find $npcName:11000869$ in $map:02000142$.

50001675-Quest2017_2-.name: The Clocktower's Secret
50001675-Quest2017_2-.desc: Time flows more slowly around the clock tower. If this effect spreads, the whole world could be thrown into chaos. Enter the $map:02000357$ and find out what's going on.

50001676-Quest2017_2-.name: Budget Wars
50001676-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000869$ is annoyed that he can't continue his very important research with his current budget. $npc:11000065$ pledged to support his work, but has been silent for a while. Perhaps $npcName:11000361$ would help the situation if she knew how much it was hurting her sister's career...

50001677-Quest2017_2-.name: Ear of the Mayor
50001677-Quest2017_2-.desc: Thanks to the science of time travel, your appointment with $npc:11000065$ has finally arrived. Hurry up to the $map:02000154$.

50001680-Quest2017_2-.name: Dark Wind's Shadow
50001680-Quest2017_2-.desc:
$npc:11000065$ has nothing to say about Dark Wind. He did have some cryptic advice for you, however: not everything about a hero is great, and not everyone under a leader believes in the same values.

It looks like you have no choice but to go to $map:52000073$ and speak with $npcName:11000044$ in person.

50001681-Quest2017_2-.name: Weight of the World
50001681-Quest2017_2-.desc:
$npcName:11000044$ put on a big show about $npcName:11000526$ being beneath his concern. Any attempts to bring it up causes him to start talking about the hunt for $npcName:11000064$.

Maybe it's time you track $npcName:11000064$ down and have a nice, private chat about Dark Wind.
50001681-Quest2017_2-.complete: Talk to the $npcName:11003446$ who came to $map:02000152$

50001682-Quest2017_2-.name: The Boss's Fury
50001682-Quest2017_2-.desc: A $npcName:11003446$ is cowering in fear from $npcName:11000044$'s anger. It seems that he's been especially furious ever since $npcName:11000069$ disappeared.

50001683-Quest2017_2-.name: An Order from the Boss
50001683-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000044$ says he needs everyone's help to find $npcName:11000069$. Go to $map:02000147$ and meet with $npcName:11000258$, who was standing guard when $npc:11000069$ disappeared.

50001690-Quest2017_2-.name: Zipped Lips
50001690-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000258$ is convinced that $npcName:11000531$ is holding out on him due to some sort of grudge against Dark Wind. Since the bookseller doesn't know you, try asking him about $npcName:11000069$.

50001691-Quest2017_2-.name: A Tentative Lead
50001691-Quest2017_2-.desc: It doesn't seem like $npcName:11000531$ will have anything useful to say. Perhaps you can trace $npcName:11000069$'s steps to find out where she is.

50001692-Quest2017_2-.name: Dangerous Side Gig
50001692-Quest2017_2-.desc: Somebody hired $npcName:11000532$ to borrow and return the books. Who would do such a thing? Could they be connected to $npcName:11000069$'s disappearance?

50001693-Quest2017_2-.name: In Pursuit
50001693-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000301$ didn't see anyone suspicious in the area, but he did mention an area under the $map:02000045$ that would make a perfect hiding spot. This seems like a good place to continue your search.

50001694-Quest2017_2-.name: Perion and Yamarcha
50001694-Quest2017_2-.desc:
The words "Yamarcha" and "$map:02000051$" are written on a wall under the $map:02000223$. What could Yamarcha mean?

This sounds like a question for $npcName:11000005$ of the $map:52000103$.

50001695-Quest2017_2-.name: Library Lookup
50001695-Quest2017_2-.desc: The Yamarcha were an ancient tribe from $map:02000051$ who sold their souls in exchange for power. $npcName:11000005$ is thrilled at your discovery at the $map:02000223$. Help her search the library for references on $map:02000051$.

50001700-Quest2017_2-.name: The Final Gift
50001700-Quest2017_2-.desc:
$npcName:11000005$ believes that the $map:02000229$ can be found in a place known to be tainted by darkness. Perhaps whatever $npcName:11000064$ was looking for had to do with this darkness.

Use the $item:30000076$ that $npcName:11000005$ gave you to release the soul of $npcName:21900090$, who is imprisoned by the darkness. The entrance to the ruins should be in $map:02000170$.
50001700-Quest2017_2-.manual: Defeat monsters at $map:02000229$ |Use $item:30000076$ to free $npcName:21900090$'s soul

50001701-Quest2017_2-.name: An Unexpected Discovery
50001701-Quest2017_2-.desc: You found a suspicious bag in the $map:02000229$. Could it be $npcName:11000069$'s?

50001702-Quest2017_2-.name: The Story They Shared
50001702-Quest2017_2-.desc: The $npcName:11003483$ tells you that $npcName:11000064$ and $npcName:11000069$ were supposed to meet here, but someone got to $npcName:11000069$ first and kidnapped her. The attacker left behind a green jewel; as soon as he saw it, $npcName:11000064$ ran off by himself. Go to the $map:02000208$ in $map:02000166$ and tell $npcName:11000529$ what happened.

50001703-Quest2017_2-.name: Unyielding Friendship
50001703-Quest2017_2-.desc:
According to $item:30000340$, he went to Katramus alone to save $npcName:11000069$. $npcName:11000529$ urges you to choose your next moves carefully.

It's up to you to decide what to tell $npc:11000044$. For now, go to $map:02000152$ in $map:02000100$ and meet with him.

50001704-Quest2017_2-.name: Run and Hide
50001704-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000044$ wants you to go back into the streets and look for more clues. For now, meet with $npcName:11000005$ at the $map:02000031$.

50001705-Quest2017_2-.name: A Surprising Clue
50001705-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000005$ wants to show you a letter from $npcName:11000032$, but she doesn't remember where she put it. Help her look.

50001706-Quest2017_2-.name: Humblis Hideout
50001706-Quest2017_2-.desc:
The item that $npcName:11000064$ found in the $map:02000306$ definitely belongs to $npcName:11000057$. In all likelihood, he's walking right into a trap.

This is no job for one person. Go to the $map:02000208$ and ask for help.

50001710-Quest2017_2-.name: Help from Humblis
50001710-Quest2017_2-.desc: By the time you got to his headquarters, $npcName:11000006$ was gone. Ask $npcName:11000566$ for his location.

50001711-Quest2017_2-.name: Real Friendship
50001711-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000566$ says $npcName:11000529$ went to Katramus. If you want to join him, you'd better hurry!

50001720-Quest2017_2-.name: Witness Protection
50001720-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000529$ thanks you for your help in Katramus. Now there's a new mission to tackle: an anonymous informant claims to have critical information about $npc:11000044$'s plans. You must get to this informant before Dark Wind does.

50001721-Quest2017_2-.name: Cornered Witness
50001721-Quest2017_2-.desc: The request for help came from $map:02000279$. Meet with $npcName:11000565$ and find the informant.

50001722-Quest2017_2-.name: Power Struggle
50001722-Quest2017_2-.desc: The agents of Humblis are trying to search the station, but robots keep getting in their way. The $npcName:22000042$ is particularly bad, as it has the power to shut down all the electric doors. Get rid of this nuisance. It appears in $map:02000279$ now and then.

50001730-Quest2017_2-.name: No Stone Unturned
50001730-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11001021$ wants you to search the $map:02000307$. The entrance is right behind him.

50001731-Quest2017_2-.name: Raymon Lives
50001731-Quest2017_2-.desc: The informant was $npc:11000526$... who was thought long dead! He claims that the robbery of the armory and the death of $npcName:11000492$ were all $npcName:11000044$'s doing. The proof can be found behind the wall clock in the $map:02000226$.

50001732-Quest2017_2-.name: Cold Hard Proof
50001732-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11001022$ has hidden the evidence in his office at $map:02000225$. Go to the $map:02000226$ and look behind the clock.
50001732-Quest2017_2-.manual: Search the wall clock in $map:02000226$ at $map:02000139$

50001733-Quest2017_2-.name: The Arrest
50001733-Quest2017_2-.desc: With $npc:11000526$'s testimony and $item:30000075$, you have more than enough evidence to prove $npcName:11000044$'s guilt. Go to the $map:02000152$ and capture him.

50001734-Quest2017_2-.name: Into Thin Air
50001734-Quest2017_2-.desc:
By the time you got to the $map:02000153$, $npcName:11000044$ was long gone. It seems he'd already seen the writing on the wall...

Return to $map:02000208$ and tell $npcName:11000529$ the news.

50001735-Quest2017_2-.name: Trading Fortunes
50001735-Quest2017_2-.desc: Bring $item:30000075$ to $npc:11000119$ in $map:02000001$. There won't be a safe place in the entire empire for $npcName:11000044$ to hide when the guard hears about this.

50001737-Quest2017_2-.name: An Ally in Prison
50001737-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000012$ has an important letter to deliver, but he's too terrified to face the recipient—$npcName:11000526$, who is under arrest in connection to $npcName:11000492$'s murder. Deliver the letter to the $map:02000310$.

50001738-Quest2017_2-.name: Nelph's Keepsake
50001738-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000526$ gave you $npcName:11000492$'s keepsake, a tape containing an audio message for $npc:11000492$'s blind mother. Since he can't deliver the tape from behind bars, he's asked you to bring it to $npcName:11000178$ in $map:02000076$.

50001739-Quest2017_2-.name: Broken Promises
50001739-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000178$ has asked you to play $item:30000342$ for her. The tape player is next to the bed in $map:02000198$.

50001740-Quest2017_2-.name: The New Ally
50001740-Quest2017_2-.desc: You haven't checked on the $map:02000146$ in a while. Seek out $npc:11000076$ at $map:02000228$.

50001741-Quest2017_2-.name: Lennon the Hero
50001741-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000064$ has joined in the defense of Maple World! Meet him at $map:02000228$.

50001742-Quest2017_2-.name: The Underground
50001742-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000064$ suspects that $npcName:11000044$ will use a tunnel at the $map:02000146$ to sneak into the Land of Darkness. Search the $map:02000308$.

50001743-Quest2017_2-.name: Facing the Darkness
50001743-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000064$ is hot on $npcName:11000044$'s tail. Follow them into the $map:52000003$.

50001744-Quest2017_2-.name: Survivor's Duty
50001744-Quest2017_2-.desc: $npcName:11000064$ wants you to warn the guard that $npcName:11000044$ escaped... and that he's certain to return with more power than ever.

50001745-Quest2017_2-.name: Fight Another Day
50001745-Quest2017_2-.desc: Now that $npcName:11000044$ is beyond your reach, it's time to report to $npc:11000075$.

50100000-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Waves' Wrath
50100000-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
Your first mission for the Frontier Foundation is to investigate the unexplained ocean disturbances plaguing Maple World, and making the seas more treacherous.

According to $npcName:11003885$, the famed explorer $npcName:11003080$ may know something about what's going on, having himself recently survived the loss of his ship to unprecedented weather conditions.

50100010-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Secrets From the Deep
50100010-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
It seems that the lapenshards may not be directly responsible for the ocean disturbances plaguing Maple World, but instead unidentified dark energies may be the culprits. 

According to $npcName:11003885$, your best shot at uncovering the truth may lie in asking the famed explorer $npcName:11003080$ what he saw the day his ship was lost.

50100020-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Great Explorer
50100020-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
You arrived in $map:02000068$ and spoke with $npc:11000019$. Still recovering from his ordeal, it seems $npc:11003080$ requested not to be disturbed. 

Considering the gravity of the situation, perhaps you can convince $npc:11000019$ to let you speak with $npc:11003080$ about what he saw.

50100030-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Beast Below
50100030-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
According to $npc:11003080$, he was shipwrecked by the guardian of the seas himself, $npc:11003086$. It seems the once peaceful divine beast is not the whale he used to be.

$npc:11003080$ said that the siren sisters $npc:11003888$ and $npc:11003889$ may be able to aid you in finding $npc:11003086$. The only problem is, he doesn't know where to find them.

Fortunately, he knows someone who does, a former pirate named $npc:11003082$. Travel to $map:02000182$ and speak with $npc:11003082$.

50100040-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Chorrie's Bad Day
50100040-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: After arriving in $map:02000182$, you located the $map:52000096$ where $npc:11003082$ lives. When you stepped inside, you found yourself in the middle of a messy situation.

50100050-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Dead Men Tell No Tales
50100050-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
You rescued $npc:11003082$ from his angry former crewmen, but it seems he wants something more in exchange for the location of the siren sisters.

He wants you to erase any trace he was ever a pirate, so he can begin his life anew. It seems you have no other choice than to help him.

50100060-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: In Search of Sirens
50100060-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
$npc:11003082$ told you that the siren sisters live in the $map:52100002$ on $map:52100001$. However, reaching them may not be easy.

It appears the younger sister $npc:29000212$ has caught the attention of the pirate captain $npc:29000213$, who is dead-set on kidnapping the mer-lass.

Head to $map:52100001$ and ensure he does not succeed.

50100070-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: A Seaside Chat
50100070-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: After defeating Captain $npc:29000213$ and clearing up a violent misunderstanding with the siren sisters, it is time you finally learned about $npc:11003086$ and his whereabouts.

50100080-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: An Audience with Alvanos
50100080-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
Rumor has it, something has driven $npc:11003086$ berserk, and his rampage has made oceans worldwide a danger to sail. You resolved to meet with $npc:11003086$ firsthand to resolve the situation.

Reaching $npc:11003086$ on such treacherous seas would be no easy feat, but according to $npc:11003082$, one vessel is up for the task! All you need to do is steal $npc:29000213$'s ship, $map:52100012$.


* You can enter $map:52100011$ through the portal on the dock in front of $map:52000096$ located in the south of $map:02000182$.
50100080-LapentaFrontierQuest-.manual:
Subdue $npc:11003086$
<font color="#909090">* You can enter $map:52100011$ through the portal on the dock located in the south of $map:02000182$.</font>

50100090-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Guardian of the Seas
50100090-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
After subduing $npc:11003086$, you learned about what set off his rampage in the first place.

It all started when $npc:11003795$ crashed into the ocean, the dark energies leeching from his body corrupting the lapenshards which had sprouted deep in the ocean.

Before the corruption might have destroyed his home, $npc:11003086$ summoned the power of the ocean to purge the seas of their corruption. However, in his weakened state, he himself became susceptible to the corrupting power of darkness... 

You should hurry back to $map:52010068$ and report what you've learned.

50100100-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Between Crises
50100100-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Your first assignment for the Frontier Foundation was a success, and Terrun Calibre was quite impressed. However your recent experiences raise many questions that must be answered...

50100110-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Shadow Seed
50100110-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: The raging seas have been quieted, but elsewhere, some of the Seven Commanders gather in the $map:52000185$ at $npc:11003894$'s behest. At the same time, $npc:11000057$ arrives to discuss a request from $npc:11003894$'s...

50100200-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Out in the Cold
50100200-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
Considering what you learned during your undersea adventure, it seems likely the extreme weather in El Nath is tied to the lapenshard. Beatrice has tasked you with traveling there alongside $npcName:11003060$ to join up with the investigation that's already underway.... 

Surnuny's thinks the unnatural blizzard in the region was conjured by Erda, queen of a fallen kingdom in El Nath. He is quite concerned as to whether Queen Erda and the Frozen Crystal she watches after are both safe.

50100210-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: A Frosty Encounter
50100210-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Beatrice has tasked you with joining the ongoing investigation into the unusual weather in El Nath. Head to the $map:52000080$

50100220-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Resuming the Search
50100220-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: $npcName:11003949$ of Guidance was scouting the ice cave in $map:02000260$ when he encountered the forces of darkness. A $npcName:11003062$ appeared during the fight and left $npcName:11003949$ and his fellow expedition members injured. Head to the $map:52000081$ and look for clues.

50100230-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Swordsman in the Snow
50100230-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
Surrounded by monsters in the $map:52000081$, who should come to your aid but a $npcName:11003062$? Before vanishing into the blizzard, he cautioned you not to go any further if you value your life.

Return to the $map:52000080$ and catch $npc:11003949$ up on what happened.

50100240-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Recluse Herbalist
50100240-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: $npcName:11003060$ knows of a potion that will allow you to resist the cold of the blizzard raging in $map:52000082$. Another yeti, $npcName:11003063$, knows how to make it. Find him at $map:02000263$.

50100250-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Burning Breath
50100250-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
$npcName:11003063$ is not exactly happy with his former queen. With great difficulty, you managed to convince him to make you the potion.

Of course, now you have to gather the ingredients for him.

50100260-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: A Chilling Development
50100260-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
$npcName:11003063$ made you a bottle of $item:20000451$ that will let you pass through $map:52000082$. The potion's effects are temporary, so be sure to use it just before you enter! Once you enter the $map:52000083$, continue your investigation.

If you need another bottle of $item:20000451$, go to $npcName:11003063$ in $map:02000263$.
50100260-LapentaFrontierQuest-.manual: Drink the $item:20000451$ and investigate $map:52000083$ at the end of $map:52000082$

50100270-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Hand of the Queen
50100270-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Long ago, $npcName:11003060$ was the palace gatekeeper for the kingdom of snow. $npcName:11003065$ needs his help to get to the $map:52000085$, where $npc:11003069$ is. Since $npcName:11003065$ is injured, deliver her message to $npcName:11003060$ and go to the $map:52000085$ in her place.

50100280-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Secrets in the Snow
50100280-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
$npc:11003060$ says that $map:52000085$ guards the path to the $map:52000086$, where the snow kingdom's secret treasure was kept. He's worried that the specter who appeared to $npcName:11003069$ is connected to the darkness and is using her to get the treasure.

Enter the hidden cave door in $map:02000260$ to join $npcName:11003060$ at the $map:52000084$, then investigate the $map:52000085$.
50100280-LapentaFrontierQuest-.manual: Enter $map:52000084$ through the hidden path in $map:02000260$ and investigate $map:52000085$
50100280-LapentaFrontierQuest-.complete: Return to $map:52000080$ in $map:02000261$ and speak with $npc:11003060$

50100290-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: To the Temple
50100290-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: $npc:11003069$ opened the path to the temple, but the vault to the Frozen Crystal is still locked. It seems likely that the forces of darkness are manipulating events here. Get ready to leave for the $map:52000086$ with $npcName:11003060$.

50100300-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Frost and Shadow
50100300-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Meet $npcName:11003060$ at the $map:52000086$. You can get there through the passageway on the tallest, steepest part of $map:02000263$.

50100310-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Thawing the Ice
50100310-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: The cause of the extreme weather in El Nath was revealed with help from the snowfolk, and a world-ending ice age was averted. However, $npc:11004045$ seems forlorn after losing her beloved $npcName:11004024$ once more. Speak with $npcName:11004045$.

50100320-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: After the Storm
50100320-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Your investigation in El Nath has reached its conclusion. Report your findings to $npc:11003883$.

50100400-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Dragon Magic
50100400-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
$npcName:11004032$'s analysis of the blackshard revealed it to be a lapenshard corrupted using powerful dragon magic. She believes it is possible to use the crystal to track the magic used to create it, but that she's the wrong person for the job.

There is someone who can help, but $npcName:11004032$ is reluctant to call for her aid...

50100410-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Eccentric Interests
50100410-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
$npcName:11000042$, the master wizard, has concocted a spell that can track the lumarigon magic used to create the blackshard. Her expertise is vital in the mission at hand, but she's stubbornly refusing to do any field work. 

Perhaps her mind can be changed?

50100420-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Where Ice Meets Fire
50100420-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: $npcName:11000042$ was persuaded into helping you. Meet her at $map:52000088$ to begin your search.

50100430-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Traces of Dragon Magic
50100430-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: $npcName:11000042$ senses lumarigon magic coming from the rune stones in $map:52000088$. Take a closer look at these stones.

50100440-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Bathed in Fire
50100440-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: $npcName:11000042$ is sure that the dragon you're tracking is in fact lumarigon—or at least related to the lumarigon in some way. Based on what you found, you should search for more evidence in $map:52000089$ at $map:02000268$.

50100450-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Wounded Dragon
50100450-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: $npcName:11000042$ says you can learn a lot about a dragon from its scales. Examine the scales in $map:52000089$.

50100460-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Teleportation Tag-along
50100460-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
The dragon scales in $map:52000089$ were tainted with dark magic. $npcName:11000042$'s tracking spell is now pointing her towards the Land of Darkness, but first she needs to visit the $map:02000146$ to get a more precise reading.

Speak with $npcName:11003089$ at the $map:02000146$.

50100470-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Oozing Darkness
50100470-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
After arriving at $map:02000146$, $npcName:11000042$'s tracking spell picked up significant amounts of lumarigon magic in $map:52000090$. She needs you to hurry there, and gather samples of darkness from the area for her to analyze.

Defeat $npcNamePlural:29000164$ in $map:52000090$, which can be found at $map:03000043$ in the Land of Darkness.

50100480-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Warped Space
50100480-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
$npcName:11000042$ has pinpointed the last known location of the lumarigon spellcaster, which was surprisingly close.

Meet her at the $map:52000092$ beneath the $map:02000146$.

50100490-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: De-Obfuscation
50100490-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
$npcName:11000042$ discovered a large stretch of distorted space where it seems something is being hidden by magic. She is preparing a counterspell to remove the cloak, but she needs your help to gather reagents.

Gather $item:30000726$ in $map:52000093$.

50100500-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Essence of Darkness
50100500-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: To continue the plan to reveal whatever is hidden here, gather $item:30000727$ in $map:52000094$.

50100510-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Lifting the Veil
50100510-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: To complete the counterspell, place rune stones on the edges of the magic seal. You can get rune stones in the $map:52000092$.
50100510-LapentaFrontierQuest-.manual: Place rune stones on the magic seal in $map:52000092$

50100520-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Finally, Suddenly
50100520-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: The counterspell is ready! Overload the phase distortion with $npc:11000042$.

50100540-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Turn Back the Dark
50100540-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
With $npcName:11004033$'s aid, you discovered a fortress built by Madria hidden at the former site of the spatial distortion. 

Together, you faced an endless horde of $npcName:11001698$'s minions. Luckily, $npcName:11004032$ had grown concerned during your absence and organized a rescue party who arrived just in time to assist you.

Alongside $npcName:11004052$ and $npcName:11004033$, you crushed Madria's forces.

50100550-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Lumiknights on the Scene
50100550-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: Thanks to $npcName:11004034$'s mass-teleportation spell, Captain Allon and his Lumiknights arrived just in time to help you take down the enemy army.

50100560-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Rear Guard
50100560-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: $npcName:11003094$ and his Dark Wind agents are dominating the battlefield, thanks to their teleportation-enabled surprise attack.

50100570-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Cutting off the Escape
50100570-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: $npcName:11001585$ and her Green Hoods cut off the retreat of $npcName:11001698$'s army, sealing the alliance's victory.

50100580-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Revealed Stronghold
50100580-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
After all this time, you finally stand before $npcName:11001698$'s stronghold. It was hidden in a pocket dimension outside the Shadow Gate this whole time!

With $npcName:11001698$'s forces routed, the Alliance plans to push its advantage and go on the offensive. Speak with $npcName:11003089$ about your next steps.

50100590-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Siege of Madrakan
50100590-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: The Alliance's assault against $npcName:11001698$'s stronghold "Madrakan" is about to begin. The fortress is sure to crumble under the combined might of the Maple Alliance. Ride to the front line and prepare for the battle ahead.

50100600-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Seal and the Spire
50100600-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc:
The Alliance has finally started striking back at the forces of darkness. Madrakan is on the brink of falling, but one obstacle stands in the way.

A powerful seal surrounds the last holdout, $map:52100042$, Captain $npcName:11003679$ has tasked you with returning to the Frontier Foundation to speak with an expert about undoing the seal.

50100610-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Girl's Past
50100610-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: After telling $npcName:11003883$ about the seal on $map:52100042$ and everything else that had happened, she told you about Madria's past.

50100620-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: A Grudge from Long Ago
50100620-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: It seems that the seal's power source lies in a grudge from Madria's past.. $npcName:11004035$ and $npcName:11004034$ devise a plan to break the seal, but they need your help.

50100630-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Raze the Spire
50100630-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: After traveling to the $map:52100041$ and destroying the source of its power, the seal blocking entry to $map:52100042$ collapsed. Speak with $npcName:11003569$ in $map:02000402$ to determine your next steps.

50100640-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: The Final Battle for Madrakan
50100640-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: It's time to conquer Madrakan once and for all. Travel to $map:52100042$ and deal a critical blow to the forces of darkness.
50100640-LapentaFrontierQuest-.manual:
|Conquer $map:52100042$
<font color="#909090">(If you leave by mistake, talk to $npc:11003096$ in $map:52000091$ to return.)</font>

50100650-LapentaFrontierQuest-.name: Return to Ground Zero
50100650-LapentaFrontierQuest-.desc: After regaining consciousness several days after the dark crystal's explosion, you travel to the $map:52010068$ to speak with $npc:11003883$. $npc:11003883$ feels responsible for the disappearance of the leaders of Terrun Calibre, and wants to turbo-charge the search effort by mobilizing the full resources of the Frontier Foundation.

50100660-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.name: Search and Rescue
50100660-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.desc: $npcName:11004106$ summons you to the $map:02000496$ to investigate the site of the dark crystal's explosion and assist in the search effort for the missing Runeblades.

50100670-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.name: The Giant Lapenshard
50100670-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.desc: After traveling to help out the Foundation at the $map:02000496$, $npcName:11004108$ requested your help researching the anomaly at the center of the blast site.

50100680-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.name: Through the Looking Glass
50100680-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.desc: $npcName:11004108$ asked you to investigate the powerful anomaly surrounding the large lapenshard at the center of the crater. Upon arriving there you heard a familiar voice, before suddenly finding yourself inside the anomaly. While exploring your newfound surroundings, you encountered the missing Runeblades. However, they seemed different than you remembered...

50100690-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.name: Critical Mass
50100690-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.desc: You were flung out of the abyss from $map:02000496$ and reported to $npcName:11004106$ on what you experienced in ground zero. $npcName:11004106$ said their objective would not change even if the Runeblades have changed. You said you will enter the abyss of $map:02000496$ once more but $npcName:11004108$ blocked you.

50100700-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.name: The Mysterious Bladesman Returns
50100700-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.desc: After $npcName:11004108$'s warning that the new dark crystal that has formed in the $map:02000496$ is building towards an apocalyptic explosion, you resolve to re-enter the anomaly in the hopes of finding a solution. Once inside, you encounter an unexpected face...

50100710-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.name: An Unlikely Partnership
50100710-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.desc: You were surprised to encounter the $npcName:11004112$ within the anomaly. Arguing that your goals were aligned, he convinced you that the two of you should work together to rescue the missing Runeblades.

50100720-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.name: Emerald Dreams
50100720-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.desc:
Using the power of rune magic, the $npcName:11004112$ managed to track down the missing Runeblades. It turns out they're right here—albeit in a parallel region of spacetime. Using his powers and the unique properties of his blade, the $npcName:11004112$ carved a rift leading to the first of four such pocket dimensions where he believed the Runeblades dwelled. Enter the rift and rescue the lost Runeblades!

This solo dungeon can only be entered when you have the related quest.
Either click the [Enter Alone] button or go through the entrance created in $map:52010069$.

50100730-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.name: Corrupted Runeblades
50100730-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.desc: After battling with a twisted version of $npcName:11004130$ within the pocket dimension, you told the $npcName:11004112$ everything that happened. The $npcName:11004112$ believes that $npcName:11004130$'s true self has been suppressed by the dark crystal, and that the only way to save the Runeblades is by dispersing the energy within the dark crystal.

50100740-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.name: Altered Space
50100740-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.desc:
$npcName:11004112$ opened a rift to the next dimensional pocket and urged you to step inside. Your mission is clear.

This solo dungeon can only be entered when you have the related quest.
Either click the [Enter Alone] button or go through the entrance created in $map:52010069$.

50100750-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.name: The Rune's Toll
50100750-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.desc: After confronting $npcName:11004129$ in his altered state, you emerged from the pocket dimension to find the $npcName:11004112$ looking exhausted. Nevertheless, he carved open a rift to the next realm and urged you to investigate.

50100760-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.name: Twisted Time
50100760-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.desc:
The repeated opening of dimensional rifts seems to have taken a serious toll on the $npcName:11004112$'s body, yet he urges you to keep going. After demanding you promise to find a way to save the missing Runeblades, he reluctantly agrees to seek treatment—but not before opening a rift to $npcName:11004128$'s domain.

This solo dungeon can only be entered when you have the related quest.
Either click the [Enter Alone] button or go through the entrance created in $map:52010069$.

50100770-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.name: Save Terrun Calibre, Save the World
50100770-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.desc: You defeated $npc:11004128$ in his corrupted state, and he fled, just like the others. After returning from your expedition, you find $npcName:11004112$ at the Foundation base camp. He has some ideas about how to save the leaders of Terrun Calibre and prevent the end of the world, but he says you'll need help to do it. Thankfully, $npcName:11004108$ is uniquely qualified in the subject of lapenshards.

50100780-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.name: All In
50100780-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.desc:
$npcName:11004108$ says that the only way to stop the new dark crystal from exploding is to extract the corrupted Runeblades from the anomaly. She also said that fighting them will burn off the power accumulated by the crystal, restoring the Runeblades to their former selves, and eliminating the threat posed by the blackshard. For the sake of your friends, and all of Maple World, it's time to enter the $map:02020130$.

This solo dungeon can only be entered when you have the related quest.
Either click the [Enter Alone] button or go through the entrance created in $map:02000496$.

50100790-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.name: The Runeblades Return
50100790-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.desc: The leaders of Terrun Calibre have been rescued, and you survived the ordeal relatively unscathed—yet the Runeblades have failed to awaken despite their apparent healthy state. The $npcName:11004112$ hypothesized that residual blackshard energy within their bodies was preventing them from awakening. Thankfully, $npcName:11004108$ has devised a plan to help them.

50100800-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.name: A Venomous Truth
50100800-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.desc:
With the Runeblades' awakening came a joyful reunion which proved short-lived when the $npcName:11004112$ was identified as $npcName:11004115$, an alleged traitor to Terrun Calibre. But according to $npcName:11004115$, it was not he who was the traitor, but their former master Arazaad. $npcName:11004115$ says that Master Arazaad intended to hand Terrun Calibre over to the $npcName:11003894$ in the interest of self-preservation in the sight of the approaching tide of darkness.

$npcName:11004115$ claims that when he tried to convince Arazaad of the error of his ways, his master attacked him, and he was forced to end Arazaad's life. While you are having a difficult time swallowing such an outlandish tale, Ishura doesn't seem so certain...

50100810-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.name: An End to the Blackshard Threat
50100810-EyeOfLapentaQuest-.desc:
$npcName:11004128$ is reluctant to accept the visions of the future he witnessed within the anomaly—but he is not quite ready to dismiss them either. In the end, he decided to let $npcName:11004115$ leave of his own volition. 

The future may be uncertain, but one thing is not: thanks to your actions, the leaders of Terrun Calibre are safe, and the threat of the blackshards seems to be ended. You return to the Frontier Foundation to celebrate a job well done, and officially conclude your investigation into the lapenshard crises.

With catastrophe averted, Terrun Calibre and Guidance, and the visiting alliance leaders all make their way home to their respective bases of operation. For now, Maple World is a calmer place. And as for you, it seems the best course of action is to ensure that whenever the next dark threat rears its ugly head, you're ready for it.

50100820-Kritias_Epic01-.name: Convening the World Security Council
50100820-Kritias_Epic01-.desc: Empress $npcName:11004390$ has called you to an emergency meeting. Go to $map:52020037$ and discover what's happened.

50100830-Kritias_Epic01-.name: An Uncharted Continent
50100830-Kritias_Epic01-.desc: An unidentified continent has appeared in the skies of Maple World from parts unknown. According to Captain $npcName:11004312$, Sky Fortress's instruments detected the presence of lapenshards. $npcName:11004316$ believes they may have arrived there as a result of the dark crystal's latest detonation. $npcName:11004312$ suggested Sky Fortress investigate the mysterious new land immediately, and the Empress gave her approval.

50100840-Kritias_Epic01-.name: First Contact
50100840-Kritias_Epic01-.desc: You arrived in $map:02020029$ by way of one of Sky Fortress's dropships, where you detected a nearby lifeform. If it is intelligent, it might provide you with some useful information.
50100840-Kritias_Epic01-.complete: Ask $npcName:11004387$ for information about this new land

50100850-Kritias_Epic01-.name: Survival of the Fittest
50100850-Kritias_Epic01-.desc:
While investigating $map:02020029$, you encountered an individual named $npcName:11004387$—the alliance's first contact with a denizen of this strange new continent. $npcName:11004387$ agrees to tell you what he knows about the missile fired against Sky Fortress in exchange for your aid. He wants you to harvest a substance called "aetherine" from the nearby fauna to power his rifle. 

Time to go hunting.

50100860-Kritias_Epic01-.name: Mysterious Assailants
50100860-Kritias_Epic01-.desc: As thanks for your help, $npcName:11004387$ told you that the missile targeting Sky Fortress was fired from a base in the north operated by an unknown and hostile force he believes originated in Maple World. The unidentified foe landed on the unidentified continent several days ago and have been terrorizing the "Kidel" region in search of something. You decide to travel into enemy territory to track down the missile's launch site.
50100860-Kritias_Epic01-.manual: Defeat $npcNamePlural:25020001$ on the hill to the north.

50100870-Kritias_Epic01-.name: The Woman in the Rubble
50100870-Kritias_Epic01-.desc: You discover an unidentified woman in the rubble of the Dark Army's camp to the north of $map:02020029$. She appears to be disoriented and hungry. You decide to harvest fruit from the nearby trees for her.

50100880-Kritias_Epic01-.name: The Enemy of Your Enemy
50100880-Kritias_Epic01-.desc: After learning that the Daemon Army's airship landed somewhere in the outskirts of $map:02020029$, you returned to the forest in search of clues.
50100880-Kritias_Epic01-.complete: Explore the east end of the $map:02020029$

50100890-Kritias_Epic01-.name: A New Assignment
50100890-Kritias_Epic01-.desc: $npcName:11004393$ said that the rest of his squad was captured by the Dark Army. After pursuing them to their camp, he witnessed a terrible scene and had no choice but to flee.

50100900-Kritias_Epic01-.name: The Kindness of Strangers
50100900-Kritias_Epic01-.desc: $npcName:11004393$ says he needs the medicinal herbs which grow in aetherine-infused soil nearby to get his comrades well enough to travel. You decide to help him.

50100910-Kritias_Epic01-.name: Onward to Richmonde
50100910-Kritias_Epic01-.desc: $npcName:11004393$ told you about the history of Humanitas and their conflict with Tairen. On the subject of your own investigation into the Dark Army's search for an unknown woman, he suggested you visit Humanitas's headquarters in $map:02020030$ and ask around.
50100910-Kritias_Epic01-.manual: Travel to the Humanitas base in $map:02020030$

50100920-Kritias_Epic01-.name: A Bloody Gesture
50100920-Kritias_Epic01-.desc: $map:02020030$ finds itself under siege by soldiers of the Dark Army—or the Daemon Army, as they are known by Kritians. Hoping to endear yourself to Humanitas's leader, you decide to follow $npcName:11004388$'s advice and engage the Daemon Army soldiers.

50100930-Kritias_Epic01-.name: New Acquaintances
50100930-Kritias_Epic01-.desc:
You met with $npcName:11004395$, leader of Humanitas, and learned that Kritias's arrival in Maple World was as much a surprise to its denizens as to you. 

With the arrival of the Daemon Army in Kritias, Humanitas—who were already under regular siege from Tairen—are now waging a war on two fronts. Despite having a shared foe, $npcName:11004395$ had no interest in working together, as she blamed the Maple Alliance for the Daemon Army's invasion of Kritias. She then issued an ultimatum: Sky Fortress must withdraw from Kritias within ten days, or be fired upon.

The woman you met at the missile site advocated on your behalf to little success. When you asked $npcName:11004395$ what the woman was doing in here office, she kicked you out. If $npcName:11004395$ isn't willing to listen to reason, perhaps her adjutant will be?

50100940-Kritias_Epic01-.name: Behind Enemy Lines
50100940-Kritias_Epic01-.desc:
You spoke with $npc:11004395$'s adjutant $npcName:11004396$, who thanked you for helping his brother and apologized for his superiors curtness.

$npcName:11004396$ revealed that Humanitas were once citizens of Tairen who revolted against the AI who governed them when she began exiling people to bring her "utopia" to fruition.

During his explanation, $npcName:11004396$ receives an urgent call for reinforcements. It seems that Daemon Army soldiers are on the verge of overrunning the guard post in the west. Luckily for them, you have volunteered to aid them.

50100950-Kritias_Epic01-.name: Proof of Death
50100950-Kritias_Epic01-.desc:
$npc:11004397$ thanks you for coming to his aid. He tells you that one of his soldiers was separated from the group during the fighting, and requests that you search for him.

Find the missing soldier. If he is alive, escort him back to $map:02020030$ for medical attention. If he is dead, collect his identification tag and deliver it to $npcName:11004395$.

50100960-Kritias_Epic01-.name: The Child of Vanheim
50100960-Kritias_Epic01-.desc:
$npcName:11004395$ revealed that the identification tag belonged to the first exile she had rescued after founding Humanitas. In light of your actions to aid Humanitas, she seems more receptive to discussion.

Through your dialogue, you both come to realize the exile standing before you is $npcName:11004400$, the daughter of Maple World's sage $npcName:11004431[gender:0]$ and the individual responsible for sealing Kritias away so many years ago.

It was then that $npcName:11004430$ and his minions arrived.

50100970-Kritias_Epic01-.name: Transmission Troubles
50100970-Kritias_Epic01-.desc:
$npcName:11004400$, the woman whose power sealed Kritias away, has been captured by $npcName:11004430$. If the forces of darkness were to use her power for evil, the results would be devastating.

Thankfully, it seems Humanitas placed a tracker on $npcName:11004400$ as a precautionary measure. There's one small catch however—$map:02020030$'s signal repeater was damaged by the Daemon Army's recent attacks. In order to repair it and locate $npcName:11004400$, you'll have to harvest the necessary part from one of the mechanical soldiers on the floating islands nearby.

50100980-Kritias_Epic01-.name: Can't Stop the Signal
50100980-Kritias_Epic01-.desc:
Using the technical manual $npcName:11004396$ gave you and the part you harvested, you managed to repair $map:02020030$'s signal repeater. 

$npcName:11004395$'s tracking device should be online now. Go find out.

50100990-Kritias_Epic01-.name: A Desperate Search
50100990-Kritias_Epic01-.desc:
$npcName:11004395$'s tracking device placed $npcName:11004400$ within the vicinity of $map:02020031$, a Tairen resource extraction operation. 

$npcName:11004395$ suggested you speak with the Humanitas agent on site in the hopes they saw where $npcName:11004400$ was taken.

50101000-Kritias_Epic01-.name: Forging a Path
50101000-Kritias_Epic01-.desc:
You arrived at the Tairen resource extracting operation in $map:02020031$, and spoke with $npcName:11004398$, a Humanitas agent. $npcName:11004398$ recounted what he witnessed, including $npcName:11004430$'s takeover of $map:02020031$ wherein he somehow took control of the numerous mechanized soldiers nearby.

If you want to break into the fusion reactor where $npcName:11004400[gender:1]$ is allegedly being held, you're going to have to carve a path through enemy lines.

50101010-Kritias_Epic01-.name: These Blasted Doors
50101010-Kritias_Epic01-.desc:
According to $npcName:11004399$, the room where $npcName:11004400$ is being held has been sealed off by the facility's blast doors, which do not seem to budge.

Try to break through the blast door inside the $map:52100105$.
50101010-Kritias_Epic01-.manual: Attempt to open the blast door

50101020-Kritias_Epic01-.name: Extreme Measures
50101020-Kritias_Epic01-.desc:
With time short and entry into the reactor blocked, $npcName:11004395$ suggests a variety of well-meaning but dangerous ideas to break inside. Formulating a plan based on the intel you received from a Humanitas agent, you call Sky Fortress to request they fire on the spire that feeds aetherine into the reactor facility.

If what you've been told is true, destroying the spire will cause all of the reactor's blast doors to open. After much persuading, $npcName:11004312$ agreed to your plan. You travel back to the $map:52100104$ in the hopes the operation was a success.

50101030-Kritias_Epic01-.name: The Daring Rescue
50101030-Kritias_Epic01-.desc:
You arrived at the $map:52100105$ and spoke with the Humanitas agent on site. It seems the plan was a success: the spire is destroyed, and the blast door is open.

Now comes the moment of truth. Enter the $map:52100105$ and rescue $npcName:11004400[gender:1]$.

50101040-Kritias_Epic01-.name: The Power Within
50101040-Kritias_Epic01-.desc:
In an unexpected turn of events, $npcName:11004400$ utilized $npcName:11004430$'s plan to extract the Blue Lapenta from her body to instead awaken its power inside her.
Summoning the lapenta's power, she attacked $npcName:11004430$, who had no other choice but to retreat from the $map:52100105$.

50101050-Kritias_Epic01-.name: A Link Between Worlds
50101050-Kritias_Epic01-.desc:
$npcName:11004430$ may have retreated for now, but he'll be back with another plan to capture $npcName:11004400$ and steal her power. $npcName:11004400$ however seems unconcerned about this, and has left on a mission of her own. 

You should travel to $map:02020041$ and formulate a new course of action.

60100000-null-.name: The Caravan
60100000-null-.desc: You met a guardsman, $npcName:11003180$, in $map:02000062$. He says you should go into the $map:52000116$ to sign up as a caravan guard.

60100001-null-.name: A Natural Hero
60100001-null-.desc: You're all signed up to escort the caravan to Tria! According to $npcName:11003163$, they're waiting on one last guard. Who could it be?

60100005-null-.name: A Simple Job
60100005-null-.desc: $npcName:11003164$ is probably the weakest guard you've ever met. This is supposed to be an easy job, but the fact that your partner on the caravan escort isn't strong enough to defeat a small puppy doesn't fill you with confidence...
60100005-null-.manual: Escort the caravan through the $map:63000041$, northwest of $map:02000062$|Make your report at $map:02000001$

60100010-null-.name: An Imperial Audience
60100010-null-.desc: After the disastrous caravan attack, you woke up in Tria with $npc:11003165$ watching over you. He's asked you to come to the $map:52000033$. Her Imperial Highness wants to see you.

60100015-null-.name: The Investigation
60100015-null-.desc: At $npc:11003165$'s request, you are investigating the attack on the caravan. Begin by seeking the advice of $npc:11003163$, who had intimate knowledge of the caravan schedule and route.

60100020-null-.name: The Masked Figure
60100020-null-.desc:
$npcName:11003166$ encountered a $npcName:11003167$ at $map:52000118$. Instead of taking the suspicious character in for questioning, he let them go. Now you have no suspects and no leads.

Little matter! Take $npcName:11003166$'s special brand of incompetence in stride and follow the $npcName:11003167$, who seems to be headed for $map:02000092$!

60100022-null-.name: Chasing the Mask
60100022-null-.desc: $npcName:11000170$ spotted the $npcName:11003167$ heading northeast of $map:02000092$. That road leads to $map:02000083$.

60100025-null-.name: A Mess of Masks
60100025-null-.desc: Your pursuit of the  $npcName:11003167[gender:0]$ has led you to the $map:02000083$, where you met $npcName:11000394$. According to her, there is a whole mess of masked figures making a ruckus in the $map:02000121$...

60100030-null-.name: Joddy in Distress
60100030-null-.desc:
While you were investigating the masked thugs attacking the $map:02000121$, their allies nabbed $npcName:11003166$. If you want to save him, you'll have to lock horns with $npcName:11003334$, the kingpin of $map:02000083$.

You should do this even if you don't want to save $npcName:11003166$.

60100035-null-.name: Informative Ivan
60100035-null-.desc: You saved $npcName:11003247$ from $npcName:11003334$'s sleazy clutches. Now that you've roughed up $npcName:11003334$'s henchmen, he's eager to give you all the information he has on the mysterious figure you're chasing.

60100040-null-.name: An Unreasonable Refusal
60100040-null-.desc: $npcName:11003194$'s man $npcName:11000396$ doesn't seem keen to talk to you. Maybe $npcName:11000171$ can tell you what's going on.

60100045-null-.name: Ralph's Wrongdoings
60100045-null-.desc:
It seems like $npcName:11000396$ has been left out in the cold since he crossed $npcName:11000173$. $npcName:11000171$ believes that the poor man will talk to you if you help him—and the best way to help is by doing his old job for $npcName:11000171$.

You don't quite grasp $npcName:11000171$'s raccoon logic, but he's a king, so he probably knows what he's talking about.

60100050-null-.name: For Ivan
60100050-null-.desc: You are busy completing menial labor for $npcName:11000171$ in the hopes that it will get $npcName:11000396$ to talk.
60100050-null-.manual: Collect Scrap Iron in $map:2000084$ |Defeat $npcName:11000173$'s men in $map:2000084$

60100055-null-.name: Job Well Done
60100055-null-.desc: In exchange for your help, $npcName:11000171$ put in a good word for you with $npcName:11000396$. Maybe he'll be willing to speak with you now.

60100060-null-.name: A Dead End
60100060-null-.desc: $npcName:11000396$ is finally talking, but it turns out he hasn't seen the $npcName:11003167$. Was $npcName:11003194$ giving you the runaround this whole time? It's time to return to $map:52000119$ and let $npcName:11003194$ know how you feel about being played for a fool.

60100065-null-.name: Ralph's Lead
60100065-null-.desc:
$npcName:11000173$ tried to double-cross you. It didn't end well for him.

However, now he claims that he knows where $npcName:11003163$ is...

60100070-null-.name: The End of Nelph
60100070-null-.desc: You found $npcName:11003163$ in $map:52000037$, but you were too late. Somebody else got here first and ended his life.

60100075-null-.name: Ralph's Last Go
60100075-null-.desc: The $npcName:11003167$ may have slipped through your fingers, but not before dropping a $item:30000023$. This seems like the sort of thing $npcName:11003334$ would know a lot about.

60100080-null-.name: Barrota Port
60100080-null-.desc:
After a final attempt to defeat you, $npcName:11000173$ has finally given up. He promises to do everything he can to help your investigation—and he's started by identifying the $npcName:11003167$'s notepad as belonging to the Barrota Trading Company.

Head to $map:02000139$ and see what you can find out.
60100080-null-.complete: Talk to a member of the Barrota Trading Company in $map:02000139$

60100085-null-.name: A Card in the Chaos
60100085-null-.desc: In $map:02000139$, you met a trader named $npcName:11000117$. He says that the crest on the notebook belongs to the president of the Barrota Trading Company. Take the elevator from the $map:02000225$ to reach $map:02000226$ and speak with the Barrota chief face-to-face.

60100090-null-.name: Ripert
60100090-null-.desc: The $map:02000226$ is in a state of disarray and the Barrota chief is missing. The only clue you could find is $item:30000773$. Apparently this $npcName:11003193$ person is an information broker based out of $map:02000139$. Find him at the $map:52000020$.

60100095-null-.name: The Cost of Information
60100095-null-.desc: You saved $npcName:11001262$ from Blackstar thugs, and he's thanking you by calling you names and generally being unpleasant. It seems this information broker will keep his lips sealed unless you can guarantee his safety from the mob.

60100100-null-.name: Dark Wind
60100100-null-.desc: Even though you saved his life twice, $npcName:11001262$ won't just give you the answers you want. While he refuses to tell you anything about the $npcName:11003167$, he's happy to refer you to someone who might. Seek out help at the $map:02000153$ in $map:02000100$.
60100100-null-.complete: Speak with a Dark Wind agent in the $map:02000153$ in $map:02000100$

60100105-null-.name: To Meet the Boss
60100105-null-.desc: You're in $map:02000153$ to dig up clues on the $npcName:11003167$, but Dark Wind's boss is out. A particularly helpful agent named $npcName:11000215$ thinks you can find him in $map:52000124$.
60100105-null-.complete: Meet the Dark Wind boss at $map:52000124$ in $map:02000147$

60100110-null-.name: Behind the Mask
60100110-null-.desc: $npcName:11000044$ already knows about the caravan ambush and why you came to see him. But there are still some things even he does not know, so meet him in the $map:52000073$ to discuss things in detail.

60100115-null-.name: The Great Winn Stilton
60100115-null-.desc: The captain of Dark Wind was the great hero, Winn Stilton. However, you've arrived in Kerning City to find a man named $npcName:11000044$ in charge. Find out what became of the previous captain.
60100115-null-.manual: Learn about the leader of Dark Wind

60100120-null-.name: A Welcome Friend
60100120-null-.desc:
$npcName:11000044$ is convinced that $npcName:11000064$ is the $npcName:11003167$ you've been after this whole time. He promises to put Dark Wind's considerable resources behind your investigation.

But wait—who's that cowering against the wall?

60100125-null-.name: Missing Person's Person
60100125-null-.desc: Your trusty ally $npcName:11003202$ has come to the $map:52000055$ to deliver bad news. When he went to $map:52000037$ to look for more clues, $npcName:11003163$'s body was no longer there. Return to $map:52000037$ with $npcName:11003202$ and check it out.

60100130-null-.name: Cherry Blossom Forest
60100130-null-.desc:
