While investigating $map:52000037$, a frantic sprite appeared and begged for your help. This sprite, $npcName:11003204$, claims that monsters are threatening his people's kingdom. Investigating the caravan attack is important, but helping fairfolk is important, too.

Head to $map:02000290$ and see what you can do.

60100135-null-.name: A Semi-clue
60100135-null-.desc: After saving the $map:02000290$ from destruction, $npcName:11003204$ mentioned an encounter with a powerful blond human. Could it be $npcName:11003216$? If $npcName:11003204$ is right, then he's headed back to $map:52000073$ to finish what he started!

60100140-null-.name: Homebody
60100140-null-.desc: You have pressing information for your investigation, but $npcName:11000044$ isn't at the $map:2000153$. Maybe he went back to $map:52000124$.
60100140-null-.complete: Go to $map:52000124$ in $map:02000147$ and talk to $npcName:11000044$

60100145-null-.name: Katvan's Wrath
60100145-null-.desc:
$npcName:11000044$ isn't at $map:52000124$ this time. $npcName:11000069$ took the opportunity to warn you against trusting $npcName:11000044$ too quickly, but a couple of suspicious men interrupted the conversation.

That's pretty rude. You should rough them up. (Also, they're trying to kill $npcName:11000069$.)

60100150-null-.name: Hard Heart
60100150-null-.desc: $npcName:11000044$ is in a rage after $npcPlural:11003304$ tried to ambush $npcName:11000069$. Once he calms his nerves, meet him at $map:02000153$.

60100155-null-.name: A Tempting Lead
60100155-null-.desc: $npcName:11000215$ interrupted your conversation with $npcName:11000044$. It seems someone in $map:02000167$ reported spotting a person matching $npcName:11000064$'s description. Go question $npcName:11001116$, the witness.

60100160-null-.name: Masked Motives
60100160-null-.desc:
$npcName:11001116$ was keeping an eye on the pollution spreading through $map:02000167$'s garden when she spotted a masked man go inside. Thinking it was the infamous $npcName:11001111$, she reported him to Dark Wind.

You may still be able to catch him if you enter the $map:02000328$ right away.

60100165-null-.name: A Trip in Vain
60100165-null-.desc: The $map:02000328$ was a bust, but $npcName:11001116$ heard a rumor that might interest you. It seems $npcName:11000543$ over in $map:02000148$ saw someone awfully suspicious.

60100170-null-.name: A Report from the Wastes
60100170-null-.desc: $npcName:11000543$ says that he actually heard the rumor about $npcName:11001108$ from $npcName:11000533$. Head to the center of $map:02000148$ and pay this $npcName:11000533$ a visit.

60100175-null-.name: Exchange of Labor
60100175-null-.desc: $npcName:11000533$ says he saw someone matching $npcName:11001111$'s description, but he won't say anything else—not without getting something in return, at least. You'd better do what he says.
60100175-null-.manual: Defeat monsters in $map:02000148$ |Clean rusty pipes in $map:02000148$

60100180-null-.name: In Your Grasp
60100180-null-.desc: $npcName:11000533$ says he spotted $npcName:11001111$ head towards $map:02000139$. If you hurry, you may be able to catch him.

60100185-null-.name: After That Blond
60100185-null-.desc:
You ran through the streets of $map:02000139$ in pursuit of $npcName:11001111$. Luckily, your dear old treacherous friend $npcName:11000173$ was there to point you in the right direction.

$npcName:11003207$ in $map:02000138$ says he spotted a blond guy head into the $map:52000125$.

60100190-null-.name: A Lie of Omission
60100190-null-.desc: The blond guy in the warehouse was actually $npcName:11003206$, $npcName:11000211$'s little brother. It seems you were tricked into saving $npcName:11003206$ from a gang of muggers.

60100195-null-.name: A Reliable Witness
60100195-null-.desc: $npcName:11003206$ claims that he really did see a blond man matching Lennon's description. Since you saved $npcName:11003206$'s brother, it's his turn to help you. Seek out $npcName:11000867$ in $map:02000138$.

60100200-null-.name: Memory Trade
60100200-null-.desc: $npcName:11000867$ insists that nothing happens in $map:02000138$ without him knowing it, and yet he can't recall where the blond man went. You may have to do something to jog his memory.

60100205-null-.name: Merchant's Sighting
60100205-null-.desc: $npcName:11000867$ conveniently remembered where the blond man went after you helped him. Head to $map:52000126$.

60100210-null-.name: Lennon Lost
60100210-null-.desc: The blond man in $map:52000126$ wasn't $npcName:11001111$, but an $npcName:11000213$. The man doesn't seem to have his wits about him. Just as you are about to give up on him, some thugs in familiar masks ambush you...

60100215-null-.name: The Awaited Meeting
60100215-null-.desc: $npcName:11000211$ and $npcName:11003206$ tracked down the blond man in order to thank you. Your search takes you to the $map:52000046$.

60100220-null-.name: Glimpse of the Truth
60100220-null-.desc: $npcName:11003215$ claims that he didn't kill $npcName:11003219$. Whatever the case, you need to bring $npcName:11003215$ in for questioning.

60100225-null-.name: Hidden Truth
60100225-null-.desc:
You've woken up in Kerning City's finest hospital. This is not your day.

Head back to the command office at $map:02000153$ and bring the others up to date.

60100230-null-.name: Regroup
60100230-null-.desc: $npcName:11000044$ is very understanding of your failure to capture $npcName:11003215$. Now it's time to regroup and come up with a new plan. Head down to the $map:52000055$ ground floor.

60100235-null-.name: Black Mushroom
60100235-null-.desc: The radars are picking up something strange. Monsters are invading $map:02000100$! $npc:11000044$ is initiating the Black Mushroom... whatever that is.

60100240-null-.name: End of the Investigation
60100240-null-.desc: $npcName:11000044$ thanks you for saving $map:02000100$, but he won't be able to offer you any more help until the city is back on its feet. It's time to return to $map:02000001$ and let them know everything that's happened.

60100245-null-.name: Shock after Shock
60100245-null-.desc:
The empress is shocked by the death of $npcName:11003219$, who was one of the Seven Heroes. 

Your conversation was interrupted by a guard reporting in to $npc:11001666$. What is this about?

80010000-null-null.name: Find the Duckling
80010000-null-null.desc:
Find the Duckling Balloons all over Maple World and investigate them!
If you investigate 10 a day, you can receive '$item:30000888$ from $npc:11001002$, which can be used as a Festival Cutout.

* Duckling Balloons appear on all fields every hour and remain for 5 minutes.

80010001-null-null.name: Find the Star Balloon
80010001-null-null.desc:
Find the Star Balloons all over Maple World and investigate them!
If you investigate 10 a day, you can receive 10 delicious '$item:20000311$' and '$item:20301037$' from $npc:11001002$.

* Star Balloons appear on all fields every hour and remain for five minutes.

80010010-null-null.desc:
$npc:11003471$'s riddle!
Go find the subject of the riddle and say hello!

80010016-null-null.name: Gather information on plant monsters
80010016-null-null.desc: Let's defeat plant monsters and gather information on them to help fulfill $npc:11003471$'s dream of creating a monster compendium.
80010016-null-null.manual: Battle plant monsters to learn more about them

80010017-null-null.name: Gather information on beast monsters
80010017-null-null.desc: Let's defeat beast monsters and gather information on them to help fulfill $npc:11003471$'s dream of creating a monster compendium.

80010018-null-null.desc: Let's defeat fairfolk monsters and gather information on them to help fulfill $npc:11003471$'s dream of creating a monster compendium.

80010019-null-null.name: Gather information on humanoid foes
80010019-null-null.desc: Let's defeat humanoid monsters and gather information on them to help fulfill $npc:11003471$'s dream of creating a monster compendium.

80010021-null-null.name: Run like the Wind!
80010021-null-null.desc:
Another way to share $npc:11003471$'s tastes!
Let's run without a care and enjoy the cool, refreshing wind!

80010022-null-null.name: Might as Well Jump!
80010022-null-null.desc:
Another way to share $npc:11003471$'s tastes!
Let's leap towards to big blue sky!

80010023-null-null.name: Mount Up!
80010023-null-null.desc:
Another way to share $npc:11003471$'s tastes!
Let's travel around Maple World riding a mount!

80010024-null-null.name: Swimming Towards a Goal!
80010024-null-null.desc:
Another way to share $npc:11003471$'s tastes!
Let's splash around in the refreshing water!

89010003-null-null.name: Participate in the "Dance Dance Stop" Guild Event 1 time
89010003-null-null.manual:

* It doesn't get checked if you win or lose by default.
The goal will only be reached when the game starts and the competition is played.

91000000-FameContents-.name: After the Attack on Tria
91000000-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:11000006$ has requested your help with an urgent matter. Speak with him in $map:02000153$ to find out what it is.

91000001-FameContents-.name: Project Aegis
91000001-FameContents-.desc:
$npcName:11000006$ tells you about 'Sky Fortress,' a secret project undertaken by the Dark Wind under Katvan's direction. The flying aircraft carrier is to become the headquarters of the Maple Alliance, which was formed after the attack on Tria.

Apparently, there's one thing missing before Sky Fortress is operational. Speak with $npcName:11000006$ to learn more!

91000002-FameContents-.name: Defender of the Alliance
91000002-FameContents-.desc: According to $npcName:11000006$, you are the missing ingredient for the Sky Fortress operation. He's asked you to serve as a liaison between the factions of the Maple Alliance. Once you've given the offer some thought, speak with $npcName:11000006$.

91000003-FameContents-.name: A Fortress in the Skies
91000003-FameContents-.desc: You agreed to join the Maple Alliance's defensive task force, and followed $npcName:11000006$ and the other leaders to a secret hangar where the Sky Fortress was docked. Speak with $npcName:11000119$ when you arrive.

91000004-FameContents-.name: The New Commander
91000004-FameContents-.desc: It turns out the Sky Fortress was being stored in a secret base under $map:02000092$. There you met Captain Veliche the new captain of Sky Fortress... You tried to introduce yourself, but it seems she has better things to do. In the mean time, you might as well listen to tactical officer Nairin's briefing.

91000005-FameContents-.name: The Tactical Officer's Briefing
91000005-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:11003585$ is the tactical officer and representative of the Green Hoods. She attempted to brief everyone on the operation, but it seems $npcName:11000006$ had already covered the basics. Speak with $npcName:11003585$ again.

91000006-FameContents-.name: Shadows in the Wind
91000006-FameContents-.desc: Due to Guard Captain $npcName:11000119$'s ardent interest, $npcName:11003585$ has excitedly resumed her briefing. As this might take a while, $npcName:11000006$ has suggested that you take this time to meet the other faction representatives. Start with the officer from Dark Wind, behind the cargo container.

91000007-FameContents-.name: The Imperial Vanguard
91000007-FameContents-.desc: You should speak with Imperial Vanguard officer $npcName:11003583$ next.

91000008-FameContents-.name: The Order of the Eclipse
91000008-FameContents-.desc: The representative of the Order of the Eclipse is on the central gangway admiring the airship. You should go and introduce yourself.

91000009-FameContents-.name: Captain of the Skies
91000009-FameContents-.desc: Finish off your introduction tour by speaking with Captain $npcName:11003582$ on the right side of the hangar.

91000010-FameContents-.name: This Is Not a Test
91000010-FameContents-.desc: Numerous unidentified radar contacts appeared during $npcName:11003536$'s demonstration of the system. Given the secret nature of the base, that can only mean one thing... Speak with $npcName:11003536$.

91000011-FameContents-.name: Securing the $map:02000011$
91000011-FameContents-.desc: After many twists and turns, Sky Fortress's launch was a success. However, before the alliance trusts with any serious tasks, you'll undergo an assessment. Your first mission is to secure the $map:02000011$. Follow $npcName:11003536$'s instructions and carry out the mission.
91000011-FameContents-.descFameUI: Pyrros Fard dwells within the Lava Crest. If he is disturbed, it would place the surrounding areas in danger.

91000012-FameContents-.name: The First Assignment
91000012-FameContents-.desc: Officer $npcName:11003584$ of Dark Wind has sent you on a field mission. Follow her orders, and get the job done!
91000012-FameContents-.complete: Speak with Dark Wind officer Schatten on Sky Fortress

91000013-FameContents-.name: Emergency Launch
91000013-FameContents-.desc: The Rooks have launched a surprise attack on the hangar. No doubt, their objective is to hijack the Sky Fortress. Keep them at bay until the ship is ready to launch!
91000013-FameContents-.complete: Speak with Alliance Captain Veliche aboard Sky Fortress

91000014-FameContents-.name: Provisions for the Proven
91000014-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:11003583$ told you about the unique items carried by faction-exclusive shops. The higher your reputation with the faction, the more items you'll be able to buy.

91000015-FameContents-.name: Setting Sail for the Skies
91000015-FameContents-.desc: The Sky Fortress's mission has finally commenced. Follow Captain $npcName:11003582$'s orders and serve as the winged guardian of Maple World!

91000016-FameContents-.name: Rampaging Robots
91000016-FameContents-.desc: The $npcName:21000135$ is a combat drone created at the $map:02000187$, which has gone rogue and started attacking people. Destroy the $npcNamePlural:21000135$ so they can't hurt anyone else.

91000017-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: A New Mission
91000017-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: Captain $npcName:11003533$ of the Sky Fortress has ordered an officer's meeting to discuss an important matter. Speak with $npcName:11003533$ to learn more.

91000018-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: The Lost Air Vendors
91000018-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: Flying merchant ships, once the crowning achievement of Maple World, have resumed operation since the Sky Fortress became active. However, it seemse some have begun disappearing. Speak with $npcName:11003533$ to learn more.

91000019-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: The Alliance Investigates
91000019-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: Captain $npcName:11003533$ gave an assignment to each representative of the Maple Alliance. Yours is to assist them in their investigations.

91000020-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: Whispers from Lith Harbor
91000020-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: Tasked with digging up information about the missing airships, Vanguard Captain $npcName:11003534$ has asked you to talk to the people of $map:02000062$. Go and see what you can learn!
91000020-FameContents_EP1_01-.manual: Gather intel from $npcName:11000024$|Gather intel from $npcName:11000025$|Gather intel from $npcName:11000106$

91000021-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: Whispers from Tria
91000021-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: $npcName:11003534$'s informant gave him a tip about unsettling rumors circulating in $map:02000001$. Go to there and speak with the citizenry to see what you can learn.
91000021-FameContents_EP1_01-.manual: Ask $npcName:11000160$ about the rumors|Ask $npcName:11000003$ about the rumors|Ask $npcName:11000373$ about the rumors

91000022-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: Whispers from the Royal Court
91000022-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: Surely the royal court knows more about the rumors circulating $map:02000001$ than the public. $npcName:11003534$ has asked you to speak with them and see what they know.
91000022-FameContents_EP1_01-.manual: Ask $npcName:11000119$ about the rumors|Ask $npcName:11000601$ about the rumors|Ask $npcName:11000074$ about the rumors

91000023-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: Hacking $map:02000145$
91000023-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: Dark Wind was tasked with tracking down the routes of the missing airships, but Barrota's refusing to hand over their records. According to $npcName:11003535$, the only choice left is to hack in and steal the data. Go to $map:02000145$ and hack into the communication relay's data cache.
91000023-FameContents_EP1_01-.manual: Activate the generators at $map:02000145$|Hack the communications array

91000024-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: Hacking $map:02000162$
91000024-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: It turns out Barrota's split the data delivery pertaining to their airship routes across multiple communications relays. Go to $map:02000162$, to hack the next one, and defeat any $npcNamePlural:21000134$ interfering with the signal.
91000024-FameContents_EP1_01-.manual: Activate the generators at $map:02000162$|Hack the communications array|Defeat $npcNamePlural:21000134$

91000025-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: Hacking $map:02000277$
91000025-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: It turns out Barrota's split the data delivery pertaining to their airship routes across multiple communications relays. Hurry to $map:02000277$ and secure the next data cache.
91000025-FameContents_EP1_01-.manual: Hack the communications array nodes at $map:02000277$

91000026-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: Hacking $map:02000269$
91000026-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: It turns out Barrota's split the data delivery pertaining to their airship routes across multiple communications relays. Go to $map:02000269$ and hack the final data cache.
91000026-FameContents_EP1_01-.manual: Hack the Comms Control Terminal in $map:02000269$| Defeat $npcNamePlural:21000121$ or $npcNamePlural:21000122$

91000027-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: A Mysterious President
91000027-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: The Green Hoods were tasked with identifying the cargo of Barrota's merchant airships. $npcName:11003536$ says an asset within the company is willing to provide you with the secret ledger. Go to $map:02000139$ and meet the informant.

91000028-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: Unsealing the Secret Ledger
91000028-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: You secured Barrota's secret ledger, but some kind of protective charm is keeping you from opening it. $npcName:11003536$ asks if you know any high ranking wizards that might be able to help. Sounds like a good time to take a trip to $map:02000023$ and speak with $npcName:11000033$.

91000029-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: Ellinel's Class President
91000029-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: $npcName:11000033$ is no expert in protective magics, fortunately he's pointed you in the direction of someone who is. Speak with your old acquaintance in $map:02000023$.

91000030-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: The Waters of Recollection
91000030-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: $npcName:11003146$ agreed to help you unseal the ledger, but she'll need a few things first. Start by collecting $itemPlural:30001033$ from $map:02000090$.

91000031-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: Unvanishing Ink
91000031-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: $npcName:11003146$ says the second thing she'll need to unseal the ledger is $item:30001034$ from $map:02000019$. Time to visit the library!

91000032-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: One More Thing
91000032-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: $npcName:11003146$ says there's one last thing she needs before she can help you: $itemPlural:30000232$. Gather some and bring them back to her.

91000033-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: The Ledger's Secrets
91000033-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: $npcName:11003146$ has finally managed to remove the protective charm keeping the ledger locked tight. Hurry and bring it back to the Sky Fortress.

91000034-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: Securing the Crash Site
91000034-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: The Lumiknights have been tasked with investigating the $map:52010053$, and $npcName:11003537$ wants you to accompany him. Travel to the crash site and search for anomalies.
91000034-FameContents_EP1_01-.manual: Defeat monsters at the crash site

91000035-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: Traces of Darkness
91000035-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: $npcName:11003537$ says the crash site has been tainted with darkness. He's asked you to bring him debris that might be affected by the darkness so he can analyze it.

91000036-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: Investigating the Darkness
91000036-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: $npcName:11003537$ said the airship debris contained traces of a terrible darkness. What was the source of this evil energy? Listen to $npcName:11003537$'s explanation.

91000037-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: Officers' Briefing
91000037-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: Captain $npcName:11003533$ has convened an officers' meeting of commanders to review the results of everyones' investigations. Meet her in the $map:52010052$.

91000038-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: The Secret of the Black Box
91000038-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: Sky Fortress's team of analysts have finished repairing the black box of the crashed trading airship. Speak with $npcName:11003533$ to learn what the device recorded.

91000039-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: The Big Reveal
91000039-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: After seeing the winged creatures recorded by the black box, the information everyone has gathered is beginning to make a lot more sense.

91000040-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: Tracking the Enemy
91000040-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: Using all the clues everyone has gathered, $npcName:11003533$the is programming the scanners to determine where the enemy will go next. Speak to $npcName:11003533$ and $npcName:11003536$ to learn more.

91000041-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: Perion in Peril
91000041-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: Hundreds of radar contacts have been detected near the $map:02000049$ in $map:02000051$. It must be the Crimson Balrogs! Hurry and defend Perion.

91000042-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: An Unexpected Ally
91000042-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: Someone named $npcName:11003790$ arrived in Perion just as the invasion was thwarted. He seems to be an acquaintance of $npcName:11003534$. Perhaps he knows something about what's going on? Speak with him back on the Sky Fortress.

91000043-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: Know Thine Enemy
91000043-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: $npcName:11003789$ provided some much-needed context regarding the Crimson Balrogs' raid on the $map:02000049$. There's still a great deal more to discuss.

91000044-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: The Darkness Gathers
91000044-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: A top priority mission has been delivered to Sky Fortress, and Captain Veliche has called an officers' meeting. Elsewhere, dark forces conspire against the alliance.

91000045-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: Looming Catastrophe
91000045-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: A dark deal is being brokered between Balrog and the Black Mage. This can only mean bad news for Maple World.

91000046-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: A Dark Alliance
91000046-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: Balrog and the Black Mage have reached an accord. Only time will tell what terrible consequences this dark alliance will reap.

91000047-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: Defending Perion
91000047-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: The Crimson Balrogs have launched devastating assault on the $map:52020036$. Fight along side $npcName:11003778$ and $npcName:11003779$ to protect the people of Perion by defeating $npcNamePlural:29000366$, $npcNamePlural:29000367$, and $npcNamePlural:29000368$.

91000048-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: Aiding the Injured
91000048-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: Many were injured in the Crimson Balrogs' attack. Take them to $npcName:11003780$ for treatment.

91000049-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: Air Support
91000049-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: A horde of Crimson Balrog troops are approaching. Use the crossbow delivered by Nairin to defeat them.

91000050-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: An Urgent Summons
91000050-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc: Captain $npc:11003533$ has issued an urgent summons. Speak with her in the $map:52010052$.

91000051-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: An Immortal Threat
91000051-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc: $npc:11000144$, the man you met at the $map:52010052$ and sworn enemy of Balrog, says he has felt an unusual aura that could only mean the return of the immortal demon lord, $npc:11003795$. What does this mean for Maple World?

91000052-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: The Immortal Awakens
91000052-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc: The crew of the Sky Fortress was shocked to learn of $npc:11003795$'s return. But $npc:11000144$ says things are not as bad as they seem... What is going on?

91000053-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: Into the Balrog's Den
91000053-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc: $npc:11000144$ went to $map:52010056$ to protect $npc:11003818$ from the Crimson Balrogs, and prevent $npc:11003795$'s revival.
91000053-FameContents_EP1_02-.complete: Listen to $npcName:11000144$'s tale of what happened in $map:52010056$

91000054-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: Whatever Works
91000054-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc: In an effort to prevent Infernog's revival, $npc:11000144$ set out to secure $npc:11003818$. Cornered and with no other choice, he consumed it. The consequences of this decision remain to be seen.
91000054-FameContents_EP1_02-.manual: Listen to $npcName:11000144$'s tale of what happened in $map:52010056$

91000055-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: The Opportunity of the Millennia
91000055-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc: So long as half of $npc:11003795$'s blood remains in $npc:11000144$'s possession, the demon lord is only at half strength. In theory, this changes everything...

91000056-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: A Clear and Present Danger
91000056-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc: $npc:11000144$ says that in his vulnerable state, $npc:11003795$ can be slain.  $npc:11000144$ is ecstatic at the opportunity to bring his family's ancient duty to completion, and urges Captain Veliche to order an attack on the demon lord immediately.

91000057-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: Caution and Impulse
91000057-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc: Unlike $npc:11000144$, $npc:11003533$ is cautious and calculating. Seeing the threat to her crew in rushing blindly into battle, she advocates a more measured approach.

91000058-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: A Change in Behavior
91000058-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc: Frustrated with the Alliance's plan to deal with Infernog, $npc:11000144$ stormed off on his own. Is there something more at work behind his growing impatience?

91000059-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: The Green Hoods' Ingenuity
91000059-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc: With Tristan's whereabouts unknown, the best course of action is to track the $npcPlural:11003781$. Start by investigating the $map:52010060$.

91000060-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: Hot Logic
91000060-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc: A message carved in a cave wall hints at the site of $npc:11003795$'s return. But more work will be needed to narrow down the precise location.

91000061-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: The Hottest Gossip
91000061-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc:
$npc:11003534$ suggests you speak with two guards near $map:02000001$ who might have heard something about the place you're looking for. 

Go there and speak with $npc:11000157$ and $npcName:11000158$.
91000061-FameContents_EP1_02-.manual: Speak with $npc:11000157$ in $map:02000118$|Speak with $npc:11000158$ in $map:02000118$|Speak with $npc:11000005$ in $map:02000031$

91000062-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: Extreme Survival Training
91000062-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc:
Given the latest information, $npc:11003534$ is eager to travel to Orbis in the hopes of confronting Infernog. However, $npc:11003535$ believes you need to undergo special training in order to beat the heat of the fiery ruins of Orbis. 

Go to $map:02000268$ and defeat monsters without succumbing to the heat.
91000062-FameContents_EP1_02-.manual: Defeat monsters while enduring the heat of $map:02000268$

91000063-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: Every Little Bit Helps
91000063-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc: Judging from his persistent staring, $npc:11003537$ has something to discuss with you before you depart for Orbis. Head over and speak with him.

91000064-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: Finding Tristan
91000064-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc:
After traveling to Orbis in a souped-up escape pod, you found $npc:11000144$ in peril. It seems $npc:11003795$ is trying to absorb the blood that was stolen from him. You can't let that happen.

Defeat all of $npc:11003795$'s minions in $map:52010063$ and rescue $npc:11000144$ from harm. (If you leave by mistake, speak with $npc:11003533$ in $map:02000422$ to return.)

91000065-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: Boiling Blood
91000065-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc:
$npc:11000144$ apologizes for his behavior under the influence of $npc:11003818$. Now, he seems completely defeated. Are things really as gloomy as they appear?

 (If you leave by mistake, talk to $npc:11003533$ in $map:52010052$ to return.)

91000066-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: A Place Beyond Hope
91000066-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc:
$npc:11000144$ reveals that $npc:11003795$ has recovered the rest of his blood, and therefore his power and immortality. He blames himself for all of this, and fears for the future in the face of this undying foe.

(If you leave the area by mistake, talk to $npc:11003533$ in $map:52010052$ to return.)

91000067-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: The Big Gun
91000067-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc:
After your safe return from Orbis with $npc:11000144$, plans are hatch to address the threat of the immortal demon lord. 

Perhaps he is not so unstoppable as everyone once feared. Speak with the officers of the Sky Fortress.

91000068-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: Completing the Weapon
91000068-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc:
An urgent frenzy has begun to complete the Alliance's last best hope of dealing with Infernog: the Ultra-High-Density Magitron Accelerator Cannon. Surely if everyone gives their all, it will be completed in time.

While $npc:11003536$ researches how to process $itemPlural:30001056$, travel to $map:02000104$ and collect several loads.

91000069-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: Technical Difficulties
91000069-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc: $npc:11003535$ is having a hard time following Nairin's instructions to process the magical ore. If this cannon is ever to be ready on time, it seems like the job falls to you. Process the ore in $npc:11003535$'s place.

91000070-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: Put Your Back Into It
91000070-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc: $npc:11003534$'s only task in assembling the Big Gun is transporting cargo from one place to the next. The problem is, he seems to have injured himself. Nevertheless, those crates aren't going to move themselves. Move the cargo to the loading platform.
91000070-FameContents_EP1_02-.manual: Move the cargo to the loading platform in $map:52010036$

91000071-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: Uncorking the Darkness
91000071-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc:
According to $npc:11003537$, the Big Gun is powered by stones full of dark magic, which can only be unsealed by a high-ranking member of the Lumiknights such as himself. 

If his word is to be believed, you may have to take drastic measures to avert a horrible accident.

91000072-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: Some Assembly Required
91000072-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc: The weapon is finally complete, but a new crisis has arisen. Sky Fortress is under assault by the $npcPlural:11003781$. Defend the carrier at all costs!

91000073-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: 15 Minutes to Midnight
91000073-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc:
Just as a new plan was being hatched to dispatch the immortal demon lord Infernog, $npc:11000144$ set off alone again in a small vessel. Here we go again...

Speak with $npc:11003533$.
91000073-FameContents_EP1_02-.manual: Review the footage of $npc:11000144$ setting out on the $map:52010064$

91000074-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: Battle for the Skies
91000074-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc:
$dungeonTitle:24090004$
This is a solo dungeon. It can only be entered by pressing the [Enter Alone] button while you have the related quest.

Your mission is to engage the immortal demon lord $npc:11003795$ and keep him distracted long enough for Sky Fortress's secret weapon to charge up and blast him into space.

91000074-FameContents_EP1_02-NA.name: Battle for the Skies
91000074-FameContents_EP1_02-NA.desc:
$dungeonTitle:24090004$
This is a solo dungeon. It can only be entered by pressing the [Enter Alone] button while you have the related quest.

Your mission is to engage the immortal demon lord $npc:11003795$ and keep him distracted long enough for Sky Fortress's secret weapon to charge up and blast him into space.

91000075-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: The Shape of Things to Come
91000075-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc: $npc:11000144$ expressed his deep gratitude for everyone's aid in banishing $npc:11003795$, but warns that there may be other threats on the horizon...

91000076-FameContents_EP1_02-.name: The Looming Darkness
91000076-FameContents_EP1_02-.desc: While the demon $npc:11003792$ licks his wounds in the $map:52010065$, he is visited by the great and powerful $npc:11001811$, who comes to collect his due. What grim tidings does this meeting foretell?

91000080-Kritias_2018_12-.name: They Are Legion
91000080-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: Now that the Alliance has a foothold in Kritias, there is much work to be done. $npcName:11004312$ has tasked you with finding the Daemon Army, gauging their forces, and combating them in any way possible. Humanitas has reported possible Daemon Army activity in $map:02020029$. Go there and investigate.
91000080-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Veliche has a special mission with your name written on it.

91000090-Kritias_2018_12-.name: They Are Legion
91000090-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: You arrived in $map:02020029$ but have yet to pick up the Daemon Army's trail. Perhaps if you make a lot of noise, the Daemon Army will find you?
91000090-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Make a scene in the hopes of drawing the Daemon Army's attention.

91000100-Kritias_2018_12-.name: They Are Legion
91000100-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: You caused a scene in hopes of drawing the Daemon Army's attention, but to no avail. Luckily, $npcName:11004312$ notified you that enemy movement had been detected near $map:02020030$. Go there and investigate.
91000100-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Troop movements have been detected near $map:02020030$. It could be the Daemon Army! Go and find out.

91000110-Kritias_2018_12-.name: They Are Legion
91000110-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: You arrived in $map:02020030$ and verified the presence of Daemon Army soldiers. If you drive them out, perhaps they'll lead you to their stronghold? Defeat $npcNamePlural:25020104$ and $npcNamePlural:25020105$ in the area.
91000110-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Daemon Army soldiers attacking $map:02020030$? Not on your watch!

91000120-Kritias_2018_12-.name: They Are Legion
91000120-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
The Daemon Army is amassing a large number of troops for an attack at two different strategic locations. Deliver a preemptive strike at either location in the hopes of reducing their numbers in one fell swoop.

<font color="#00aaef">★ Completing this quest requires that you win one Legion Battle. While exploring the Kritias continent, invitations to participate in Legion Battles will appear as periodic pop-up notifications warning that a region is under siege. When minimized, this notification displays as a red radar screen.

(In order to participate in a legion battle, you must unlock Tier 1 of the $achieve:22200490$ trophy.)</font>
91000120-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: The Daemon Army is amassing for an attack. Defeat them in a Legion Battle to deal a serious blow against their forces.

91000130-Kritias_2018_12-.name: They Are Legion
91000130-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: Your preemptive attack against the amassed troops of the Daemon Army has dealt a solid blow against their ranks. Report back to $npcName:11004312$ in $map:02020041$ to discuss the battle.
91000130-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Your preemptive attack against the troops of the Daemon Army has dealt a solid blow to their ranks. Report back to $npcName:11004312$.

91000140-Kritias_2018_12-.name: The Supply Run
91000140-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004312$ says Humanitas has requested help with a mission. What could it be? Go to $map:02020030$ and speak with $npcName:11004401$.
91000140-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Humanitas has requested the aid of the Maple Alliance. Speak with their leader and see what she needs.

91000150-Kritias_2018_12-.name: The Supply Run
91000150-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
According to $npcName:11004395$, Humanitas has made efforts to seize the nearby Tairen base of $map:02020004$ for the resources stockpiled there. However, they had no choice but to retreat when Tairen reinforcements arrived. $npcName:11004395$ wants you to secure the base on their behalf, and has offered to share any liberated supplies.

Aid your allies by traveling to $map:02020004$ and carrying out your mission.
91000150-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Help Humanitas take a nearby Tairen base to liberate the much-needed supplies inside.

91000160-Kritias_2018_12-.name: The Supply Run
91000160-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
You arrived in $map:02020004$ and were greeted by a horde of mechanical Tairen soldiers. They must be dismantled before Humanitas can claim their much needed supplies.

Defeat $npcNamePlural:25020401$ and $npcNamePlural:25020402$.
91000160-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Capture the Tairen warehouse in $map:02020004$ by defeating the mechanized soldiers guarding the area.

91000170-Kritias_2018_12-.name: The Supply Run
91000170-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: While you were speaking with $npcName:11004395$ in $map:02020004$, the Tairen were regrouping to counter your assault. Defeat them and secure your victory.
91000170-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: You defeated a group of Tairen mechanized soldiers in your efforts to capture the enemy's supplies, but they are regrouping. Deal with the enemy reinforcements.

91000180-Kritias_2018_12-.name: The Supply Run
91000180-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: In your efforts to capture the Tairen supply warehouse, you seem to have poked the bear. Now the commander on site is out for your blood. Defeat the $npcName:25020405$ and show the enemy that the Alliance doesn't retreat.
91000180-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: An enemy commander has arrived. Crush them, and secure the area for Humanitas.

91000190-Kritias_2018_12-.name: The Supply Run
91000190-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
You defeated the mechanized Tairen soldiers and the commander stationed in $map:02020041$ and secured some much-needed supplies for Humanitas.

Return to $map:02020041$ and report in.
91000190-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: You defeated the mechanized Tairen soldiers and the commander stationed in $map:02020041$. Now it's time to report in.

91000200-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Bal-Busting
91000200-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
$npcName:11004314$ told you about a worrisome rumor she confirmed to be true. However, rather than just tell you what the rumor was, she wants you to see for yourself.

Play along and go to $map:02020013$.
91000200-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: A troublesome rumor is circulating among Sky Fortress's crew. This warrants an investigation.

91000210-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Bal-Busting
91000210-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: According to $npcName:11004314$, the rumors that $npcName:23090006$ has come to Kritias are true. It's up to you to find out why. Search $map:02020013$ and for traces Balrog or his lackeys.
91000210-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: What is $npcName:23090006$ doing in Kritias? It's up to you to find out.

91000220-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Bal-Busting
91000220-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
It seems $npcName:23090006$ has come to Kritias, and he brought the $npcNamePlural:25020906$ with him. $npcName:11004315$ ran a sensor sweep and tracked him to $map:02020017$. $npcName:11004312$ orders you to track down $npcName:23090006$ and deal with him while she warns Humanitas.

Go to $map:02020017$ in search of $npcName:23090006$.
91000220-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: $npcName:23090006$ is in Kritias. The Alliance has pinpointed his location, and now it's up to you to track him down.

91000230-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Bal-Busting
91000230-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:23090006$ came to Kritias seeking new power in the form of aetherine and lapenshards. If this were allowed to happen, $npcName:23090006$ would become a great threat to the Alliance and Kritias alike. Travel to $dungeonTitle:23038002$ and defeat $npcName:23090006$!
91000230-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: The time has come to confront an old foe. Will you finally be able to end this battle once and for all?

91000240-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Bal-Busting
91000240-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
If $npcName:23090006$ obtains the power he seeks, he could become a greater threat than Tairen or the Daemon Army combined. He must be stopped.

Travel to $map:02020097$, enter the $dungeonTitle:23038002$, and defeat $npcName:23090006$!
91000240-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Play time is over! It's time to truly crush $npcName:23090006$!

91000250-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Bal-Busting
91000250-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: You tried to contact the Captain to tell her that $npcName:23090006$ had been defeated, but there's something wrong with your radio. Go to $map:02020041$ and deliver the news in person.
91000250-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: $npcName:23090006$ has finally been defeated. Return to base and deliver the good news..

91000260-Kritias_Inferno01-.name: Nothing Is Forever
91000260-Kritias_Inferno01-.desc:
$npcName:11004555$ was summoned to $map:02020041$ to investigate the possibility that $npcName:23000150$ had come to Kritias. He suspected this was true, though he found himself unable to pick out $npcName:23000150$'s aura from the energies of this alien land.

Speak with your allies and formulate a plan to locate $npcName:23000150$.
91000260-Kritias_Inferno01-.descFameUI: Has $npcName:23000150$ the immortal demon lord come to Kritias? You should probably find out.

91000270-Kritias_Inferno01-.name: Nothing Is Forever
91000270-Kritias_Inferno01-.desc: $npcName:11004555$ rambled on about a book passed down by his family which seemed to evidence the sage $npcName:11004431$'s arrival in Maple World. Perhaps eventually he'll loop around to the matter you were originally discussing—$npcName:23000150$'s presence in Kritias.
91000270-Kritias_Inferno01-.descFameUI: What began as an effort to track down Infernog has ended in $npcName:11004555$'s predictable rambling.

91000280-Kritias_Inferno01-.name: Nothing Is Forever
91000280-Kritias_Inferno01-.desc:
$npcName:11004555$ is fairly sure $npcName:23000150$ has come to Kritias, but needs catch the demon lord's trail. In the mean time, $npcName:11004315$ has developed a detector that just might be able to track him down.

Follow the detector's signal to $map:02020003$.
91000280-Kritias_Inferno01-.descFameUI: Take your handy new detector device and pick up $npcName:23000150$'s trail.

91000290-Kritias_Inferno01-.name: Nothing Is Forever
91000290-Kritias_Inferno01-.desc: $npcName:11004315$ says the aetherine signatures of the nearby $npcNamePlural:25021504$, $npcNamePlural:25021505$, and $npcNamePlural:25021502$ are confusing her detector. Purge $map:02020003$ of these foes so she can recalibrate her device.
91000290-Kritias_Inferno01-.descFameUI: The aetherine signatures of nearby foes are interfering with your search for Infernog. Eliminate the source of the problem.

91000300-Kritias_Inferno01-.name: Nothing Is Forever
91000300-Kritias_Inferno01-.desc:
After locating $npcName:23000150$, you were contacted by $npcName:11004555$ who said he had discovered a way to end the demon lord for good using the power of aetherine. If his hypothesis proves true, you can bring this immortal villains story to its ultimate conclusion.

(Defeat $npcName:23000150$ in the chaos raid $dungeonTitle:23043003$ or $dungeonTitle:23042003$.)
91000300-Kritias_Inferno01-.manual: Defeat $npcName:23000150$ in the chaos raid $dungeonTitle:23043003$ or $dungeonTitle:23042003$.
91000300-Kritias_Inferno01-.descFameUI: Harness the power of a new land to put an end to an immortal threat.

91000310-Kritias_Inferno01-.name: Nothing Is Forever
91000310-Kritias_Inferno01-.desc: At long last, $npcName:23000150$ is defeated! Return to $map:02020041$ and tell $npcName:11004312$ everything.
91000310-Kritias_Inferno01-.descFameUI: Your battle against $npcName:23000150$ is finally over. It's time to spread the word.

91000320-Kritias_Inferno01-.name: The Counter-Offensive
91000320-Kritias_Inferno01-.desc:
The threat posed by $npcName:23090006$ and $npcName:23000150$ is finally ended, but other threats to the exploration of Kritias remain—such as the presence of hostile Tairen and Kharon forces. 

To begin to address the matter, $npcName:11004312$ has asked you to lead a joint mission on behalf of Humanitas and the Maple Alliance. Go to $map:02020009$ and carry out your orders.
91000320-Kritias_Inferno01-.descFameUI: Obstacles remain which inhibit the further exploration of Kritias. It's up to you to deal with them.

91000330-Kritias_Inferno01-.name: The Counter-Offensive
91000330-Kritias_Inferno01-.desc:
$npcName:11004395$ says Kharon, the notorious lackeys of Tairen, operate a base in the $map:02020009$. Attacking it would deal a devastating blow to both groups alike.

Unleash your wrath on the $npcNamePlural:25021601$, $npcNamePlural:25021602$, and $npcNamePlural:25021603$ stationed there.
91000330-Kritias_Inferno01-.descFameUI: Both Kharon and Tairen are constantly conspiring to destroy Humanitas. It's time for a counter-offensive.

91000340-Kritias_Inferno01-.name: The Counter-Offensive
91000340-Kritias_Inferno01-.desc:
The huge drill in $map:02020009$ appears to be remotely operated by Tairen. By hacking into its software, Humanitas hopes to acquire Tairen's access code. This code could be used against the Tairen for all sorts of espionage or sabotage.

Acquire the code.
91000340-Kritias_Inferno01-.manual: Hack into the drill in $map:02020009$ and decrypt the access code.
91000340-Kritias_Inferno01-.descFameUI: The huge drill in $map:02020009$ appears to be remotely operated by Tairen. Hack into its software and acquire their access code.

91000350-Kritias_Inferno01-.name: The Counter-Offensive
91000350-Kritias_Inferno01-.desc:
$npcName:11004395$ has tasked you with seizing the $itemPlural:30001257$ in the position of $npcNamePlural:25021604$ in the area to cripple Kharon's ability to strike at Humanitas.

Get to work.
91000350-Kritias_Inferno01-.descFameUI: The Kharon have been a nuisance to Humanitas for long enough. Strike back by stealing vital supplies.

91000360-Kritias_Inferno01-.name: The Counter-Offensive
91000360-Kritias_Inferno01-.desc: Before you return to base, $npcName:11004312$ has one final task for you. Take advantage of Kharon's weakened state by breaking into the control room below $map:02020009$ and redirecting the primary controls to Humanitas computers.
91000360-Kritias_Inferno01-.manual: Gain access to the primary controls in $map:52100108$
91000360-Kritias_Inferno01-.descFameUI: Break into the underground control room and redirect the facility's primary controls to Humanitas.

91000370-Kritias_Inferno01-.name: The Counter-Offensive
91000370-Kritias_Inferno01-.desc: You have completed your mission. All that remains is return to $map:02020041$ and give your report.
91000370-Kritias_Inferno01-.descFameUI: Your latest mission is over, but a new frontier awaits.

91000380-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Evil Evolved
91000380-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004316$ has asked you to investigate a strange darkness in $map:02020030$. Make it happen.
91000380-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: $npcName:11004316$ claims to have felt a strange aura of darkness in Kritias, and wants you to investigate.

91000390-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Evil Evolved
91000390-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: Sky Fortress's R&D team has designed a series of devices capable of detecting the power of darkness. Set up detectors throughout the area and then report in.

91000400-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Evil Evolved
91000400-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: The machines in $map:02020031$ have been hijacked by an unusual darkness. Search for the cause of the corruption by dismantling $npcNamePlural:25020203$ and $npcNamePlural:25020204$.
91000400-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: A dark power has corrupted these mechanical soldiers. Perform a robo-topsy to learn how.

91000410-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Evil Evolved
91000410-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
Dismantling the machines did nothing to reveal the means by which they were corrupted. It's time to call in an expert.

Talk to $npcName:11004315$.
91000410-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Dismantling the machines did nothing to reveal the means by which they were corrupted. It's time to call in an expert.

91000420-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Evil Evolved
91000420-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
The darkness that $npcName:11004316$ felt is actually an ongoing data transmission. It seems some sort of neural network has co-opted all of the mechanical soldiers in the area.

This warrants further investigation.
91000420-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: It seems some sort of neural network has co-opted all of the mechanical soldiers in the area. This warrants further investigation.

91000430-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Evil Evolved
91000430-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
According to Humanitas, Tairen possess highly advanced magic and technology and have their very own AI. Perhaps they possess other knowledge that could be of use here.

Meet up with $npcName:11004316$ in $map:02020041$ and contact $npcName:11004395$.
91000430-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Return to $map:02020041$ and have the Sky Fortress crew contact $npcName:11004395$.

91000440-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Seeing Ghosts
91000440-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004316$ says he's felt a new surge of darkness that must be investigated coming from $map:02020001$. Go there and look into it.
91000440-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: A dark presence has been detected in $map:02020001$. Go and investigate.

91000450-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Seeing Ghosts
91000450-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: You arrived in $map:02020001$, but found no obvious signs of a dark force at work. Talk with $npcName:11004458$ to see if she saw anything out of the ordinary.
91000450-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Speak with the individuals in $map:02020001$ to see what they know about dark forces operating in the area.

91000460-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Seeing Ghosts
91000460-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
You heard accounts of a black-garbed "ghost" sighted in $map:02020001$ mumbling about sacrificing a "soul" for power. According to $npcName:11004436$ this "ghost" was last seen near $map:02020006$. 

Go to $map:02020006$ and beat up the cloaked, wraith-like $npcNamePlural:25020306$ and $npcNamePlural:25020307$ for answers.
91000460-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: According to $npcName:11004436$ the "ghost" you are tracking was last seen in $map:02020006$. Go there and investigate.

91000470-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Seeing Ghosts
91000470-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: You didn't learn anything of value by beating up Daemon Army lackeys. Perhaps a higher ranking Daemon will be able to provide valuable intel? Pay a $npcName:25020308$ a visit.
91000470-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: The search for your "ghost" is at an impasse. Interrogate a $npcName:25020308$ for answers.

91000480-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Seeing Ghosts
91000480-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
You learned of the Daemon lieutenant $npcName:23000301$ through the orders you recovered from a $npcName:25020308$. It seems $npcName:23000301$ is the source of the dark power $npcName:11004316$ spoke of.

Contact Alliance HQ with what you've learned.
91000480-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: You learned of the Daemon lieutenant $npcName:23000301$ from some orders you recovered. The search is on.

91000490-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Seeing Ghosts
91000490-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: Until you have identified your new foe's capabilities, it's too risky to go in swinging. Return to Alliance HQ to discuss your next mission.
91000490-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Return to $map:02020041$ and discuss your options

91000500-Kritias_2018_12-.name: The Price of Power
91000500-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
$npcName:11004316$ says he called upon the Eye of Providence to determine $npcName:23000301$'s location. 

It looks like you're headed to $map:02020032$.
91000500-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI:
$npcName:11004316$ says he called upon the Eye of Providence to determine $npcName:23000301$'s location. 

It looks like you're headed to $map:02020032$.

91000510-Kritias_2018_12-.name: The Price of Power
91000510-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
You brought Nairin's "Darkwave Analyzer" to $map:02020032$ in the hopes of picking up $npcName:23000301$'s trail, but it seems the device was broken. While you wait for them to repair it, thin the Daemon Army's ranks.

Defeat $npcNamePlural:25020701$, $npcNamePlural:25020702$, and $npcNamePlural:25020703$ in $map:02020032$.
91000510-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: While you wait to hear from $npcName:11004316$, reduce the number of Daemon Forces in the area.

91000520-Kritias_2018_12-.name: The Price of Power
91000520-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
With the Darkwave Analyzer damaged beyond repair, $npcName:11004316$ once more called upon the Eye of Providence to locate $npcName:23000301$. 

It seems your next destination is $map:02020016$.
91000520-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: $npcName:23000130$ has been tracked to $map:02020016$. Move out immediately.

91000530-Kritias_2018_12-.name: The Price of Power
91000530-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: Upon arriving in $map:02020016$, you felt the presence of a powerful darkness. To safeguard you in your upcoming battle against its source, $npcName:11004316$ allegedly created a protective sigil outside of $dungeonTitle:23037002$. Receive its power (if it exists).

91000540-Kritias_2018_12-.name: The Price of Power
91000540-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: The time has come to enter $map:02020200$ and put an end to $npcName:23000301$'s schemes. Go forth and conquer!

91000550-Kritias_2018_12-.name: The Price of Power
91000550-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:23000301$ has been defeated. Return to $map:02020041$ for a debriefing.
91000550-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: $npcName:23000301$ has been defeated. Return to $map:02020041$ for a debriefing.

91000560-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Plots and Ploys
91000560-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
Attempts to locate $npcName:11004430$ have proven fruitless. Perhaps you can track him down using the machines he's controlling?

Go to $map:02020017$.
91000560-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Go to $map:02020017$ to destroy Turka's hacked sentries.

91000570-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Plots and Ploys
91000570-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: Go to $map:02020017$ for now and destroy $npcNamePlural:25021202$ while Nairin analyses their data transmissions.
91000570-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Destroy $npcNamePlural:25021202$ to while Nairin analyses their data transmissions.

91000580-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Plots and Ploys
91000580-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004315$ needs more data to track down the source of the signal. Defeat $npcNamePlural:25021205$ while she analyses the data.
91000580-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: $npcName:11004315$ needs more data to track down the source of the signal. Defeat $npcNamePlural:25021205$ while she analyses the data.

91000590-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Plots and Ploys
91000590-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
$npcName:11004315$ says the source of the signal is on the move. She's managed to calculate its trajectory, but that could change in an instant. Hurry and intercept it at the coordinates she provided!

(To return to the map, press the "Resume Dungeon" button.)
91000590-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: The dark signal is on the move, but $npcName:11004315$ has mapped out its trajectory. Intercept its source!

91000600-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Plots and Ploys
91000600-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: You encountered $npcName:11004430$ at $map:52020039$. He said some very odd things, and then vanished—but not before leaving behind some Daemon Army soldiers hell-bent on your demise. Deal with them, before they deal with you.
91000600-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Defeat $npcName:11004430$'s lackeys and resume your efforts to find him.

91000610-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Plots and Ploys
91000610-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: By the time you defeated the attacking $npcNamePlural:25021308$, $npcName:11004430$ was long gone. There's nothing to do now but return to $map:02020041$ and tell $npcName:11004316$ what happened.
91000610-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Return to $map:02020041$ to tell $npcName:11004316$ everything that's happened.

91000620-Kritias_Zakum01-.name: The Stone God
91000620-Kritias_Zakum01-.desc:
The Lumiknights' investigation revealed that $npcName:23000073$ is an ancient demon sealed away alongside Kritias. $npcName:23000073$ had been summoned before in Maple World, and the team was able to track him down after analyzing the site of the ancient ritual.

Go to $map:02020034$, and find $npcName:23000073$.

91000630-Kritias_Zakum01-.name: The Stone God
91000630-Kritias_Zakum01-.desc:
The path to Zakum is filled with enemies. 

Defeat the $npcNamePlural:25020801$, $npcNamePlural:25020803$, and $npcNamePlural:25020805$ who stand in your way.
91000630-Kritias_Zakum01-.descFameUI: Clear a path to $npcName:23000073$ by culling the nearby mechanized soldiers.

91000640-Kritias_Zakum01-.name: The Stone God
91000640-Kritias_Zakum01-.desc:
Your best chance at defeating $npcName:23000073$ lies in destroying the totems that grant him his power.

$MyPCName$ smash!
91000640-Kritias_Zakum01-.descFameUI: Destroy the totems used to summon $npcName:23000073$ to weaken him.

91000650-Kritias_Zakum01-.name: The Stone God
91000650-Kritias_Zakum01-.desc: The time has come to take on $npcName:23000073$.
91000650-Kritias_Zakum01-.descFameUI: With his totems destroyed, $npcName:23000073$ is weakened. Now is the time to strike!

91000660-Kritias_Zakum01-.name: The Stone God
91000660-Kritias_Zakum01-.desc:
You encountered $npcName:11004430$ on your way to defeat $npcName:23000073$. He said a few odd things before vanishing, but that's something to worry about later. 

Go to $map:02000426$ and defeat $npcName:23000073$.

(Defeat Zakum in the $dungeonTitle:230410031$ chaos raid.)

91000670-Kritias_Zakum01-.name: The Stone God
91000670-Kritias_Zakum01-.desc: $npcName:23000073$ has been defeated. Return to $map:02020041$ to discuss what comes next.

91000680-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Kritian Pioneers
91000680-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
Since the appearance of Kritias in Maple World, many pioneers have traveled to see the new continent for all manner of reasons. As their assistance may one day prove vital to Alliance operations on the continent, the Green Hoods have elected to help these individuals with anything they should need.

Do your part by greeting the latest batch of arrivals!
91000680-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: It seems a number of familiar faces are visiting Kritias. Go and say hello.

91000690-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Kritian Pioneers
91000690-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: It's been a while since you last saw $npcName:11004319$, $npcName:11004320$, $npcName:11004321$, and $npcName:11004322$, but they all seem well—and invested in a brand new adventure! It seems $npcName:11004324$ and $npcName:11004323$ are here too. Why not go say hello?
91000690-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: It seems like $npcName:11004324$ and $npcName:11004323$ never go anywhere unless they're together—even to the wild unknown of Kritias!

91000700-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Kritian Pioneers
91000700-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
$npcName:11004323$ is worried over something $npcName:11000044$ once said, and came to Kritias in hopes of finding answers. $npcName:11004324$ seems to have followed her here out of a sense of duty.

It seems $npcName:11004331$ and $npcName:11004332$ are also here, and causing no end of trouble for the Green Hoods. You should stop by and check in with them.
91000700-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: After catching up with a number of old friends, Lanemone and Orde ask you about a special request. See what they have to say.

91000710-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Kritian Pioneers
91000710-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
$npcName:11004331$ and $npcName:11004332$ seem extremely eager to study aetherine, an abundant power source unique to Kritias. They ask you to bring them some aetherine crystals to research.

Well, Nairin did say to help the new arrivals any way you could...
91000710-Kritias_2018_12-.manual: Take the Aetherine Crystal from the Aetherine Device
91000710-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Orde and Lanemone need your help gathering an aetherine crystal for their studies.

91000720-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Kritian Pioneers
91000720-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
You had intended to help $npcName:11004332$ with her request, but then you got a talking-to about misappropriating resources. Since $npcName:11004315$ outranks you, and tends to get scary when she's being serious, it's best to do as she says.

With that episode behind you, it's time to say hello to $npcName:11004330$ and $npcName:11004329$.
91000720-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: $npcName:11004330$ and $npcName:11004329$ are here too. You should pay them a visit.

91000730-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Kritian Pioneers
91000730-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004329$ is very excited with the progress of his research into the magic of Kritias. $npcName:11004330$, has not found the remedy to $npcName:11000032$'s condition she was hoping to by coming here. Now that you've greeted the newest arrivals, you should return to $npcName:11004315$ with that Aetherine Crystal.
91000730-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Return to $npcName:11004315$ with the Aetherine Crystal.

91000740-Kritias_2018_12-.name: The Puppetmasters
91000740-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: With Humanitas under siege from Tairen and Kharon alike, $npcName:11004315$ has asked you to provide whatever support you can in an unofficial capacity.
91000740-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Humanitas is struggling to wage a battle on multiple fronts. Assist them by reducing Kharon's numbers.

91000750-Kritias_2018_12-.name: The Puppetmasters
91000750-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: Kharon soldiers have expanded their territory into $map:02020001$, hampering Humanitas efforts in the area. Defeat $npcNamePlural:25020506$ and $npcNamePlural:25020507$ to buy Humanitas some breathing room.

91000760-Kritias_2018_12-.name: The Puppetmasters
91000760-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: The Kharon's incursion into $map:02020001$ has interrupted a vital Humanitas mining operation. Assist Humanitas by recovering the unusual green ore that's been unearthed nearby.
91000760-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Kharon's incursion into $map:02020001$ has interrupted a vital Humanitas mining operation. Assist Humanitas by recovering the unusual green ore that's been unearthed nearby.

91000770-Kritias_2018_12-.name: The Puppetmasters
91000770-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: Tairen is using Kharon to attack Humanitas. Deal a blow to their operation at $map:02020004$ by destroying the supplies they've prepared for Kharon.
91000770-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Tairen provides supplies to Kharon to aid them in their fight with Humanitas. It's time to fight back against this evil alliance.

91000780-Kritias_2018_12-.name: The Puppetmasters
91000780-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: You went to $map:02020004$ in the hopes of crippling Tairen's efforts to supply Kharon in their fight against Humanitas. Destroy the supply crates!
91000780-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Destroy the supply crates Tairen has prepared for Kharon.

91000790-Kritias_2018_12-.name: The Puppetmasters
91000790-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: Before you could finish destroying all of the supply crates the Tairen had prepared for Kharon, Sky Fortress detected the approach of additional Tairen forces. It seems there's no choice but to retreat from $map:02020004$ for now.
91000790-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Tairen reinforcements are approaching $map:02020004$. You have no choice but to retreat.

91000800-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Digging for Answers
91000800-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: The Green Hoods are ready to start their study of the Kritian continent with a survey of plant life. Travel to $map:02020013$ and collect some plant samples.
91000800-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: The Green Hoods have begun exploring Kritias. Assist them by collecting samples of local flora.

91000810-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Digging for Answers
91000810-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: You discovered an odd plant bearing fruits that smell similar to ones found in Maple World. You should collect some and investigate.
91000810-Kritias_2018_12-.manual: Collect a sample of the local flora
91000810-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: You've discovered plants in Kritias that seem similar to ones found in Maple World. This warrants further investigation.

91000820-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Digging for Answers
91000820-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
The fruit you tasted on your investigation of Kritias's flora tasted just like $item:30000232$. How such a thing is possible remains a mystery, but it could suggest some kind of link between Maple World and Kritias. 
Your next task is to investigate the soil at the $map:02020051$. Get started!
91000820-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: After investigating the flora of $map:02020013$, it's time to sample the soil at the $map:02020051$.

91000830-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Digging for Answers
91000830-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
The Green Hoods have reprogrammed the giant soil-analysis drill in $map:02020051$ to transmit its analysis data to Sky Fortress so they can study soil conditions in the area. Activate the Gigantic Drill so that Nairin can study the data it produces!

★ You need a $item:30001278$ in order to operate the Gigantic Drill. $itemPlural:30001278$ can be purchased from the faction shops in $map:02020041$.
91000830-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Use the Gigantic Drill in $map:02020051$ to analyze the properties of the local soil for the Green Hoods.

91000840-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Digging for Answers
91000840-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: When you activated the Gigantic Drill, a giant mechanical worm shot out of the earth and began wreaking havoc. You should defeat it before it hurts someone.
91000840-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Operating the Gigantic Drill has caused a huge monster to appear. Defeat the creature and put an end to its rampage.

91000850-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Digging for Answers
91000850-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: After you defeated the giant mechanical worm creature, $npcName:11004315$ contacted you seeking answers. Return to $map:02020041$ and explain what happened.

91000860-Kritias_2018_12-.name: A Link to the Past
91000860-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: According to $npcName:11004315$, some of Kritias's oldest structures bear a striking resemblance to ancient ruins found on Victoria Island. She wants you to go to $map:02020003$ to investigate.
91000860-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Some of Kritias's oldest structures bear a striking resemblance to ancient ruins found on Victoria Island. This warrants investigation.

91000870-Kritias_2018_12-.name: A Link to the Past
91000870-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: You traveled to $map:02020003$ to investigate an ancient structure, but found the area crawling with Tairen soldiers. Drive them out so you can continue your mission.
91000870-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Defeat the $npcNamePlural:25021504$ and $npcNamePlural:25021505$ interfering with your investigation in $map:02020003$.

91000880-Kritias_2018_12-.name: A Link to the Past
91000880-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: You've driven out many of the Tairen soldiers in the area. Now you should be able to take photos of the ancient structure for $npcName:11004315$ using a camera already set up on site.
91000880-Kritias_2018_12-.manual: Take a picture of the ancient structure using the camera
91000880-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Take a picture of the ancient structure in $map:02020003$ and send it to $npcName:11004315$.

91000890-Kritias_2018_12-.name: A Link to the Past
91000890-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004315$ examined the photos you sent her of the structure in $map:02020003$ and was blown away by the similarities to some of Maple World's ancient ruins. Eager to know more, she has tasked you with exploring the underground passage into the structure that can be found nearby.
91000890-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Enter $map:52100106$ to investigate the structure's interior

91000900-Kritias_2018_12-.name: A Link to the Past
91000900-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: You entered the $map:52100106$ to investigate the structure's interior, ended up triggering some kind of alarm. $npcName:11004315$ suggests you hide in the large chamber at the end of the corridor ahead.
91000900-Kritias_2018_12-.manual: Search for answers and get to safety
91000900-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: An alarm triggered while you were investigating the $map:52100107$. Search for any clues you can about the purpose of the structure and get out of there.

91000910-Kritias_2018_12-.name: A Link to the Past
91000910-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: You found some old books in the old building that may be of particular interest. Bring them to $npcName:11004315$ in $map:02020041$.
91000910-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Deliver the mysterious books you found in $map:52100107$ to $npcName:11004315$ in $map:02020041$.

91000920-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Ancient History
91000920-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004315$ analyzed the books you brought her. She revealed them to be a personal journal chronicling events in Kritias. Eager to determine whether the tomes were fact or fiction, she dispatched you to $map:02020018$, a location mentioned numerous times in the books. Travel to $map:02020018$ and continue your investigation.
91000920-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: $npcName:11004315$ wants to determine whether the old books you brought her are fact or fiction. Help her validate their authenticity.

91000930-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Ancient History
91000930-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: You traveled to $map:02020018$, a location mentioned frequently in the old journals. It seems a perfect match to its descriptions. See what else you can discover by reading the books!
91000930-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: $map:02020018$ seems a perfect match to its descriptions in $npcName:11004315$'s old books. See what else you can discover!

91000940-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Ancient History
91000940-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004315$ says that some of the books' pages appear to have been deliberately torn out. Luckily, through some impressive work, she has determined that the missing $itemPlural:30001289$ are still on site. Search $map:02020018$ for the missing pages.

91000950-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Ancient History
91000950-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
$npcName:11004315$ discovered the journal's author was none other than the sage $npcName:11004431$. As she continued her analysis of the books, she realized that there were more missing pages. Using Sky Fortress's sensors, she determined the missing pages were in the possession of $npcNamePlural:25021703$ or $npcNamePlural:25021704$ nearby.

Retrieve the missing pages by force!
91000950-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Defeat $npcNamePlural:25021703$ and $npcName:25021704$ in $map:02020018$ to recover the missing journal pages.

91000960-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Ancient History
91000960-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: You located the remaining missing pages of $npcName:11004431$'s journal and sent them to $npcName:11004315$ for analysis. Now, to see what new information they contain!
91000960-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Wait for Nairin to finish translating $npcName:11004431$'s journal.

91000970-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Ancient History
91000970-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004431$'s writings revealed that he was deeply upset by some kind of social upheaval, and left Kritias for another world. Talk to $npcName:11004315$ and see what other new information the journal brings to light.

92000010-FameContents-.name: Cry of the Wildflower
92000010-FameContents-.desc:
$npcNamePlural:21000013$ are trampling the rare, beautiful flowers of $map:02000147$. If this continues, this tourist attraction will become a hideous eyesore! 

Wipe out the $npcNamePlural:21000013$ before they do any more harm.

92000030-FameContents-.name: Resource Robbers
92000030-FameContents-.desc:
The $npcName:21000068$ population of the $map:02000148$ has been devouring the area's crude oil. This essential resource has countless uses, and must be preserved at any cost.

Exterminate the $npcNamePlural:21000068$ to protect the local cache of crude.

92000050-FameContents-.name: Hacked By Who?
92000050-FameContents-.desc: The androids of $map:02000265$ have become inexplicably violent. It's time to decommission them. Eliminate $npcNamePlural:21000240$, $npcNamePlural:21000243$, and $npcNamePlural:21000246$!

92000060-FameContents-.name: The Case of the Missing Plungers
92000060-FameContents-.desc: Drive the $npcNamePlural:21000161$ out of $map:02000138$ so the people there can use their bathrooms in peace.

92000080-FameContents-.name: Barrota Port Panic
92000080-FameContents-.desc: Thugs have invaded $map:02000139$, looting cargo, commandeering ships, and terrorizing people. Drive out the thugs at $map:02000139$ to restore order.

92000090-FameContents-.name: The Station Situation
92000090-FameContents-.desc:
$npcNamePlural:21000124$ have taken control of the $map:02000279$, putting all of Victoria Island's passenger and supply trains in jeopardy. 

Eliminate the $npcNamePlural:21000124$ and restore order to the station

92000100-FameContents-.name: Taking Over the Airwaves
92000100-FameContents-.desc:
$npcNamePlural:21000385$ have taken over the communication tower in $map:02000266$ in an attempt to gain followers and fix pickled radish prices. 

The local $npcNamePlural:21000240$ have already fallen under their control. Defeat the $npcNamePlural:21000240$ and drive out the $npcNamePlural:21000385$!

92000110-FameContents-.name: Concert Catastrophe
92000110-FameContents-.desc: A crime wave in $map:02000137$ is threatening to cancel Blake's next concert. $npcName:11003536$'s heart would probably break if this happened, so it's up to you to put an end to the $npcNamePlural:21099049$ and $npcNamePlural:21000282$'s scheming.

92000120-FameContents-.name: Junk Hoarders
92000120-FameContents-.desc: The residents of $map:02000084$ make a living by collecting scrap metal to recycle or sell, but recently, a large group of masked thugs have started hoarding it all to sell to Blackstar. Drive out the masked thugs to bring the local economy back to life.

92000140-FameContents-.name: Barrota Shore Shakedown
92000140-FameContents-.desc: The $npcNamePlural:21000083$ of $map:02000110$ have joined forces with their rivals, the $npcNamePlural:21000085$ to shake down the locals for money. It's time someone taught them both a lesson!

92000150-FameContents-.name: Double-Dealing
92000150-FameContents-.desc:
The $npcNamePlural:99990016$ running the furnace at the $map:02000086$ have started selling weapons meant for the Alliance to Blackstar gangsters. 

It's time somebody taught them a lesson. That somebody is you.

92000160-FameContents-.name: Masked Exploitation
92000160-FameContents-.desc: $map:02000111$, a popular vacation spot, has been overrun by $npcNamePlural:21000101$ trying to make a buck. Drive the $npcNamePlural:21000101$ out of the area and help keep $map:02000111$ the vacationer's paradise it's always been.

92000170-FameContents-.name: A Violent Compromise
92000170-FameContents-.desc:
Construction of Fellowstone Tower has been delayed by a hostage situation. $npcNamePlural:21099049$ and $npcNamePlural:21000282$ thugs are demanding a ransom for the safe release of the construction workers, but $npcName:11003535$ has no intent of paying up. 

Teach the $npcNamePlural:21099049$ and $npcNamePlural:21000282$ to leave their lives of crime behind forever.

92000180-FameContents-.name: The Lonely Cafe
92000180-FameContents-.desc: $map:02000135$ is famous for its scenery and cable car tours, but the $npcNamePlural:21000084$ are driving away tourists. Without tourists, a lot of businesses will have to close down, including $npcName:11003535$'s favorite cafe. She wants you to deal with the $npcNamePlural:21000084$ to ensure that never happens.

92000200-FameContents-.name: Gene Therapy
92000200-FameContents-.desc: The bunnies being used as test subjects at the $map:02000145$ have turned into horrible monsters. Exterminate the $npcNamePlural:21090184$ and $npcNamePlural:21090185$, and stop them from further harming the researchers or their facility.

92000210-FameContents-.name: Masked Pain
92000210-FameContents-.desc:
The masked thugs that terrorize $map:02000083$ don't work for Ralph anymore. Now they've graduated to terrorizing civilians for Blackstar.

It's time someone gave those thugs a taste of their own medicine!

92000220-FameContents-.name: Consult Your Pharmacist
92000220-FameContents-.desc:
Violent, mutant bunnies have taken over $map:02000134$! If they're not driven out, Maple World will lose access to one of its greatest sources of life-saving drugs. 

Drive the $npcNamePlural:21090186$ and $npcNamePlural:21090184$ from $map:02000134$ and restore the factory to normal operations.

92000230-FameContents-.name: Robots Running Amuck
92000230-FameContents-.desc: Robots have taken over the $map:02000187$! If things continue down this path, they'll create a massive robot army... Exterminate the $npcNamePlural:21000242$, $npcNamePlural:21000245$, and $npcNamePlural:21000248$ at the $map:02000187$!

92000240-FameContents-.name: All We Wanna Do Is Eat Your Brains
92000240-FameContents-.desc: The zombie situation at $map:02000276$. is getting out of hand. Put those corpses back in the ground.

92000250-FameContents-.name: Daily Production Quotas
92000250-FameContents-.desc:
Androids have taken over the $map:02000277$, disrupting industries across Maple World. 

Take out the $npcNamePlural:21000242$, $npcNamePlural:21000245$, and $npcNamePlural:21000247$, and return $map:02000277$ so things can get back to normal.

92000260-FameContents-.name: Robo-terror
92000260-FameContents-.desc:
Machines have taken over $map:02000163$ and are forcing the researchers there to create new parts for them. 

Take out the $npcNamePlural:21000242$, $npcNamePlural:21000245$, and $npcNamePlural:21000247$, before they become a bigger threat.

92000270-FameContents-.name: The Android Offensive
92000270-FameContents-.desc:
The ripples of the ongoing android crisis can be felt around the world. Now they've attacked and taken control of the $map:02000274$ near Taliskar, a source of drinking water for millions of people.

Take out the androids and their pets before the situation escalates.

92000280-FameContents-.name: Toxic Explosion
92000280-FameContents-.desc:
Androids have taken over the $map:02000269$, which is full of tanks of toxic gas. If the androids decide to blow them up, the damage could devastate the entire region. 

Destroy the $npcNamePlural:21000121$ and $npcNamePlural:21000122$ before that can happen!

92000290-FameContents-.name: G-g-ghosts!?
92000290-FameContents-.desc: Strange spirits have taken over machines at the $map:02000275$. Take care of the $npcNamePlural:21000196$, $npcNamePlural:21000296$, and $npcNamePlural:29000062$ while $npcName:11003535$ takes real good care of Nairin.

92000300-FameContents-.name: The Android Alliance
