92000300-FameContents-.desc: The rogue androids of $map:02000273$ are forging alliances with those who share their aims. They've become a serious threat, and it's up to you to wipe them out!

92000310-FameContents-.name: A Powerful Source of Energy
92000310-FameContents-.desc: Robots have taken over the $map:02000162$. Wipe them out before they learn how to harness the station's geothermal energy!

92000320-FameContents-.name: Evil on the Road
92000320-FameContents-.desc: Evil encroaches on one of the few passable roads in the Land of Darkness. Advance to $map:03000118$ and eliminate the dark forces that threaten the area.

92000330-FameContents-.name: Risen from the Depths
92000330-FameContents-.desc: A great darkness calls souls lost at sea long ago back from the depths as horrible revenants. Purge them from $map:03000117$ so these lost souls may finally know peace.

92000340-FameContents-.name: The Forgotten Toys
92000340-FameContents-.desc: Long ago, $map:03000057$ was used as a dumping ground for unwanted toys. Since the town was lost to the darkness, those toys have taken on a new life, and now they seek to take revenge on the humans who abandoned them.

92000350-FameContents-.name: Livid Livestock
92000350-FameContents-.desc:
Before the darkness came, $map:03000143$ was the largest ranch on Victoria island. In the years since the Land of Darkness was formed, the livestock have transformed into monsters. 

Now they crave the flesh of man. Put the twisted creatures out of their misery.

92000360-FameContents-.name: The Savage Wilds
92000360-FameContents-.desc:
The deadly beasts dwelling within the $map:03000003$ were once ordinary creatures, before they were twisted by darkness.

Now they are beyond redemption, and a threat to all around them. End their misery.

92000370-FameContents-.name: An Accursed Ritual
92000370-FameContents-.desc:
The $map:03000130$ were once a sacred site to the wizards of Victoria Island. However, dark forces have taken over the area, and now they're using the latent magic within the ruins to perform an evil ritual of their own.

Put an end to their plans.

92000380-FameContents-.name: Shadow and Flame
92000380-FameContents-.desc:
$map:03000022$ was once a crystal-clear river, but when the darkness swept over it, it erupted into flame. So too were the animals who lived there transformed into blazing beasts.

Defeat the beasts that dwell there and strike back against the darkness.

92000390-FameContents-.name: Hungering Darkness
92000390-FameContents-.desc:
$npcNamePlural:40000018$ haunt $map:03000146$, feeding on the magical traces left behind by a powerful demon. Let unhindered, they could grow extremely dangerous.

Make sure that never happens.

92000400-FameContents-.name: Armor of Darkness
92000400-FameContents-.desc:
The pigs who dwell on $map:03000115$ have somehow acquired their own armor, making them a special menace to those who dare brave the Land of Darkness.

Put an end to this threat.

92000410-FameContents-.name: A Town Reclaimed
92000410-FameContents-.desc:
Long ago, $map:03000165$ was a peaceful town. It was abandoned when the land of darkness was sealed away, but it remains surprisingly intact. 

If it were cleansed of monsters, it might one day be reclaimed.

92000420-FameContents-.name: Sweet Vengeance
92000420-FameContents-.desc: $map:03000185$ is home to a host of fetid confections, which the crazed $npcNamePlural:40000081$ intend to use to unleash havoc on Tria's famed bake sale. Stop them, and save our snacks!

92000430-FameContents-.name: A Cleansing Wind
92000430-FameContents-.desc:
Like many locations in the Land of Darkness, $map:03000007$ was once a beautiful place. Now it is tainted, and it gives rise to such horrors as $npcNamePlural:40000083$ and $npcNamePlural:40000084$. 

These beasts endanger one of the Land of Darkness's precious few shelters. Dispatch them.

92000440-FameContents-.name: The Storm in the Hills
92000440-FameContents-.desc: The $map:03000009$ were a popular vacation spot in another age. Perhaps it can be once again... but not while malodorous $npcNamePlural:40000085$ infest the area. Deal with them.

92000450-FameContents-.name: To Drink of the Spring
92000450-FameContents-.desc:
$map:03000089$ was once a source of pristine waters, but now it is tainted with dark magic. $npcNamePlural:40000122$ have been kidnapping adventurers and unfortunate wanderers on this land, and forcing them to drink from the corrupted spring, twisting their minds and poisoning their bodies.

Put a stop to these mad games.

92000460-FameContents-.name: An Axe to Grind
92000460-FameContents-.desc:
The $map:03000006$ used to be a major logging site for the empire. But after the darkness fell, it became a haunting ground for vengeful spirits who gave life to the fallen logs and stumps of the forest. These wooden monstrosities now stalk the forest in search of revenge.

Cut them down.

92000470-FameContents-.name: Make Way for Science
92000470-FameContents-.desc:
The Alliance wants to dispatch a team to $map:03000101$ in an ongoing investigation of how to purify the Land of Darkness, but the local monster populace is a problem.

Reduce their numbers.

92000480-FameContents-.name: The Rotting Forest
92000480-FameContents-.desc: When the sun was blotted out over the Land of Darkness, the forest of $map:03000024$ began to die. When the $npcNamePlural:40000127$ moved in to feast on the decay, they became a host to the tree-killing diseases. Destroy these creatures so their disease never spreads beyond the Land of Darkness.

92000490-FameContents-.name: Sleep-Deprived Sentries
92000490-FameContents-.desc: The increasing number of creatures at the $map:02000091$ have put the Green Hood sentries there on edge. Help ease their burden by reducing the monster population a bit.

92000500-FameContents-.name: Beefing Up Security
92000500-FameContents-.desc: Additional defenses are being built at $map:02000057$ to protect against future attacks. However, $npcNamePlural:21000300$ are making the work difficult, so they must be driven away.

92000510-FameContents-.name: A Tasty Morale-Booster
92000510-FameContents-.desc:
$npcName:11003536$ wants to bake some sweet combat rations to boost ship morale, but the $map:02000186$, the best source of fresh ingredient, is crawling with monsters. 

Take care of them, for the good of desserts!

92000520-FameContents-.name: Gemstone Thieves
92000520-FameContents-.desc: Ever since Henesys was attacked, the Green Hoods have been short on equipment. After a critical shipment of gemstones was stolen by beauty-seeking Toogas, you have no choice but to reclaim them by force.

92000530-FameContents-.name: A Sticky Situation
92000530-FameContents-.desc:
The Green Hoods have plans to refurbish the $map:02000013$ and use it as an outpost. In order to complete repairs, they'll need a ton of snail slime.

Your job? Hunt a ton of $npcNamePlural:21000353$!

92000540-FameContents-.name: Not the Bees!
92000540-FameContents-.desc:
To improve morale in the Green Hoods, $npcName:11003536$ wants to hold a friendly hunting competition at $map:02000054$, followed by a feast at. Unfortunately, the area is swarming with venomous $npcNamePlural:21000098$!

Take care of them so the Green Hoods can still have their party.

92000550-FameContents-.name: The Farmers' Tears
92000550-FameContents-.desc:
The attack on Henesys has driven wild animals living deep in the mountains down into the fields of the unsuspecting farmers of $map:02000056$.

Now, they're devouring vital crops. Deal with the plundering $npcNamePlural:21000225$ before it's too late!

92000560-FameContents-.name: The Stirge Scourge
92000560-FameContents-.desc:
Farming in the bitter cold of $map:02000085$ is tough enough without  $npcNamePlural:21099190$ biting at your neck. 

Drive them out so that the humble farmers of the region can work in peace!

92000570-FameContents-.name: The Lumbering Menace
92000570-FameContents-.desc: Henesys cannot be rebuilt without wood, and $map:02000059$ is a major source of wood. However, the monsters near there make it hard to gather the wood. Thin them out!

92000580-FameContents-.name: Un-gogging the Drain
92000580-FameContents-.desc: In the past, the crystal-clear waters of $map:02000022$ were a treasured source of drinking water for the surrounding areas. But with the unchecked expansion of the local monster populace, the river has become polluted with litter and waste. Drive the monsters out so that the river can recover.

92000590-FameContents-.name: Cries of the Forest
92000590-FameContents-.desc:
The androids dispatched to protect the $map:02000128$ have gone haywire and started chopping it down to establish their own base. 

Destroy them before they can do any more harm!

92000600-FameContents-.name: Cannibalistic Trees
92000600-FameContents-.desc: In a strange turn of events, $npcNamePlural:21000044$ have begun devouring other trees, threatening the ecosystem of $map:02000215$. Defeat the $npcNamePlural:21000044$ laying waste to the forest!

92000610-FameContents-.name: Onio-truders
92000610-FameContents-.desc:
$npcNamePlural:21000262$ and $npcNamePlural:21000264$ displaced by human development, have made their new home in $map:02000089$. Unfortunately, they're uprooting precious Torhara's flowers to plant their own seeds. 

If the balance of the spring is to be preserved, you must chase the $npcNamePlural:21000262$ and $npcNamePlural:21000264$ out.

92000620-FameContents-.name: The Root Cause
92000620-FameContents-.desc:
$npcNamePlural:21000252$ primarily eat soft roots, which has become a problem since their numbers have soared in recent years. 

Reduce their numbers before there's nothing left of $map:02000006$ to save.

92000630-FameContents-.name: Protecting the Trees
92000630-FameContents-.desc:
Ecological disturbances have created a surge in the $npcNamePlural:21000249$ population at $map:02000024$. The problem is, $npcNamePlural:21000249$ feed on trees. 

Reduce their numbers before there are no trees left in $map:02000024$.

92000640-FameContents-.name: Mechanical Miscreants
92000640-FameContents-.desc:
The $npcNamePlural:21000132$ deployed to stop the $npcNamePlural:21000289$ corrupting the forest have gone rogue and started attacking humans!

It's up to you to salvage the situation by destroying them both!

92000650-FameContents-.name: Spore No More
92000650-FameContents-.desc:
$map:02000113$ is a source of drinking water for all of Ellinia, but the $npcNamePlural:21000341$ are polluting it with their... toxins. 

Eradicate the $npcNamePlural:21000341$ from $map:02000113$ to give the falls a chance to purify itself.

92000660-FameContents-.name: The Snack That Bites Back
92000660-FameContents-.desc:
To unsuspecting travelers passing through $map:02000129$, the forest seems like a goldmine of edible mushrooms. Little do they know, the $npcNamePlural:21000006$ pack a dangerous bite. 

Wipe out the $npcNamePlural:21000006$ to keep these hungry, uneducated people from maiming themselves.

92000670-FameContents-.name: A Squishy Contaminant
92000670-FameContents-.desc:
The $npcNamePlural:21000030$ at the $map:02000112$ are causing all manner of problems. Not only are they merging to form King Slimes, their waste is polluting the water! 

Cull the $npcNamePlural:21000030$ and save the forest!

92000680-FameContents-.name: Beat Them Because You Care
92000680-FameContents-.desc: The hideous $npcNamePlural:21000109$ of $map:02000053$ were once beautiful unicorns. They can be again, with the help of Sky Fortress's experimental darkness neutralization ray. All you have to do is beat the $npcNamePlural:21000109$ back into their senses.

92000690-FameContents-.name: Forest-Melting Spores
92000690-FameContents-.desc: In a healthy ecosystem, $npcNamePlural:21000339$ perform the valuable service of breaking down fallen trees. However, a hormonal imbalance has caused them to breed to problematic extents. The only solution is to slash their population.

92000700-FameContents-.name: Tree-on-Tree Violence
92000700-FameContents-.desc:
Twisted by dark influence, the $npcNamePlural:21090182$ of $map:02000090$ have grown jealous of the neighboring trees, and started stripping their bark. 

You need to put an end to this arboreal atrocity by wiping out the $npcNamePlural:21090182$, and save the forest.

92000710-FameContents-.name: A Coherent Crisis
92000710-FameContents-.desc:
The number of $npcNamePlural:21000029$ at $map:02000041$ has exploded, and $npcName:11003534$ fears they'll clump together to wreak havoc as King Slimes.

Your job is to cull their population before that happens.

92000720-FameContents-.name: Siege of the Sprites
92000720-FameContents-.desc: $npcNamePlural:21000078$ are gathering in the $map:02000043$ to lay siege to nearby human settlements. Drive them off and foil their plans.

92000730-FameContents-.name: A Stumpy Grudge
92000730-FameContents-.desc:
Illegal logging in the enchanted woods of the $map:02000017$ has created a horde of angry $npcNamePlural:21000041$ in search of vengeance! 

These vermin are a threat to kneecaps everywhere, and must be destroyed.

92000740-FameContents-.name: The Canyon Conundrum
92000740-FameContents-.desc: The feral $npcName:21000062$ population at the $map:02000117$ has gotten out of hand. Thin their numbers before any more unsuspecting travelers go missing.

92000750-FameContents-.name: An Imminent Threat
92000750-FameContents-.desc: A large number of $npcNamePlural:21000079$ and $npcNamePlural:21000080$ have gathered at $map:02000118$ and they're trying to break into Tria. Help the Royal Guard stop them!

92000760-FameContents-.name: The Highwaybears
92000760-FameContents-.desc:
A group of mischievous $npcNamePlural:21000234$ have set up camp at $map:02000088$ and are robbing travelers. 

It's time to teach them that crime doesn't pay!

92000770-FameContents-.name: Threat from Beyond
92000770-FameContents-.desc: Zombies are attacking the researchers conducting a geological survey at $map:02000087$. Secure the area by whacking any zombies you see at $map:02000087$.

92000780-FameContents-.name: Forest Thieves
92000780-FameContents-.desc: The $npcNamePlural:21000077$ are using vines to catch and mug anyone passing through $map:02000116$, including important delivery people bring supplies to Tria. Go to $map:02000116$ and stop the $npcNamePlural:21000077$!

92000790-FameContents-.name: Horned Hunters
92000790-FameContents-.desc:
Ever since that earthquake at the $map:02000115$, the royal guard has had difficulty controlling monster populations in the surrounding area.

The $npcNamePlural:21000007$ have become a serious threat to travelers. It's time someone thinned their numbers.

92000800-FameContents-.name: A Slippery Road
92000800-FameContents-.desc:
$map:02000114$ is part of the major trade route linking $map:02000062$ and $map:02000001$. 

But with their population unchecked, the slimy trails of the $npcNamePlural:21000351$ has become a real problem, and a leading cause of wagon crashes. 

It's time to knock the slime out of those slippery $npcNamePlural:21000351$!

92000840-FameContents-.name: Bucktoothed Menace
92000840-FameContents-.desc: The $npcNamePlural:21000111$ at $map:02000097$ are a serious menace to travelers. You've been conscripted to do something about the problem.

92000900-FameContents-.name: Some Like It Only Lukewarm
92000900-FameContents-.desc:
A unique balance has been reached within the volcano at the $map:02000039$, allowing for its slow and measured flow. However, the burrowing $npcNamePlural:21000255$ threaten a full-scale eruption. 

Cull their population so that never occurs!

92000930-FameContents-.name: Rage of the Forgotten
92000930-FameContents-.desc:
The forgotten $npcNamePlural:21000088$ at the $map:02000010$ have suddenly grown aware that they were forgotten. In their anger and sorrow, they've started attacking civilians. 

You'll have to end their tantrum by force.

92000940-FameContents-.name: Venom and Fang
92000940-FameContents-.desc: The slithering masses of venomous $npcNamePlural:21000076$ at the $map:02000048$ have become a serious hazard. It's up to you to do something about them.

92000950-FameContents-.name: The Thermal Threat
92000950-FameContents-.desc:
The geothermal energy plant at $map:02000268$ is in danger thanks to the growing number of $npcNamePlural:21000250$ and $npcNamePlural:21000253$. 

Reduce their numbers so that the technicians can access the plant.

92000960-FameContents-.name: Dug Too Deep
92000960-FameContents-.desc: $npcNamePlural:21091021$ and $npcNamePlural:21091023$ are mining $map:02000175$ for precious gemstones. Unfortunately, their greed has blinded them to the dangers, and they're close to awakening the dormant volcano under their mines. If they won't stop on their own, then you'll have to stop them by force.

92000970-FameContents-.name: Attack of the Plushies
92000970-FameContents-.desc:
Forgotten toys everywhere have come to life and found a new home in $map:02000262$. In their bitterness and rage, they've barred humans from entering their territory, and the $npcNamePlural:21000171$ have even gone out of their way to hunt down and attack innocent passers-by.

Put these toys away.

92000980-FameContents-.name: Igloo Invaders
92000980-FameContents-.desc:
The humble tribespeople of $map:02000264$ have had their igloos invaded but an unexpected pest that is damaging their homes and eating their food.

Defeat the $npcName:21000258$ before anyone starves or freezes to death.

92000990-FameContents-.name: Curse Quarantine
92000990-FameContents-.desc:
A powerful curse was cast upon the $map:03000090$, which is why the forest was sealed in the first place. Unfortunately, the curse has taken hold of the $npcNamePlural:40000151$ of the forest, and they're threatening to spill out into the surrounding areas. 

Thin their numbers to reduce this threat.

92001000-FameContents-.name: Cunning and Malice
92001000-FameContents-.desc:
$npcNamePlural:40000205$ have begun raising an army in $map:03000136$ to carry out their dark schemes.

Drive out the $npcNamePlural:40000205$ before they become a serious problem.

92001010-FameContents-.name: Contagion
92001010-FameContents-.desc: A virus stored in the dilapidated labs of the $map:03000145$ has somehow escaped containment. Now $npcNamePlural:40000074$ are wandering the lab, spreading the virus to those unfortunate enough to pass through. Contain the disease by destroying its carriers.

92001020-FameContents-.name: Urban Warfare
92001020-FameContents-.desc:
The $map:03000135$ is a valuable strategic location in the Alliance's long-term plans to restore the Land of Darkness. As such, the hordes of violent $npcNamePlural:40000169$ and $npcNamePlural:40000032$ infesting the area need to be addressed.

Thin their ranks.

92001030-FameContents-.name: A Toxic Matter
92001030-FameContents-.desc: $npcNamePlural:40000023$ have taken over $map:03000134$ and are preparing a massive batch of chemical weapons. Drive them out before they have a chance to put these weapons to use.

92001040-FameContents-.name: Shadow's Edge
92001040-FameContents-.desc: In the Land of Darkness, even the wildlife is twisted and monstrous. The $npcNamePlural:40000024$ and $npcNamePlural:40000132$ of $map:03000014$ present a danger to the Maple Alliance's reconnaissance teams. Thin the herd a little to make things easier for your fellow soldiers.

92001050-FameContents-.name: The Carrot Monopoly
92001050-FameContents-.desc:
$map:02000280$ is one of the leading producers of carrots in Victoria Island, but lately the local farms have been threatened by feral rabbit-monsters. 

Drive these monsters from $map:02000280$ and restore the peace for the gentle Moon Bunny farmers.

93000000-FameContents-.name: Recon: Undead Nelph
93000000-FameContents-.desc:
A mysterious caped man is loitering awkwardly along trade routes through the mountains. He shows up without warning, attacks, and then vanishes. Because he's most frequently spotted in the $map:02000043$, $npcName:11003535$ thinks it might be $npcName:11000492$ risen from the dead.

Head to the $map:02000043$ and get a report from the undercover Dark Wind agent.
93000000-FameContents-.descFameUI: Someone matching Nelph's description has been spotted in the Boulderwhite Mountains...

93000001-FameContents-.name: Recon: Frequency Unknown
93000001-FameContents-.desc: A few days ago, an unusual signal was detected at the $map:02000146$. Where did it come from? Who is responsible for this? Head to the $map:02000146$ and get a coded message from the Dark Wind agent.
93000001-FameContents-.descFameUI: Unidentified signal detected at Shadow Gate! Frequency associated with ancient kingdom of [REDACTED]

93000002-FameContents-.name: Recon: The Resistance
93000002-FameContents-.desc: Dark Wind tailed a member of the anti-magic Resistance to $map:02000270$, but couldn't pinpoint who he reported to. $npcName:11003535$ won't give up that easily! Head to $map:02000270$ and receive coded messages from her agents.
93000002-FameContents-.descFameUI: Dark Wind is in pursuit of the Resistance. They are a slippery bunch...

93000003-FameContents-.name: Recon: The Brains behind Blackstar
93000003-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:11000251$ is the infamous godfather of Blackstar. But is this brash don truly responsible for the brilliant strategy that's allowed him to avoid backlash from the law? Rumor has it that he's secretly being guided by an advisor in the shadows. Head to $map:02000131$ and get a coded message about this mystery man from one of Dark Wind's agents...
93000003-FameContents-.descFameUI: Everyone knows that Wei Hong is the boss of Blackstar. But is someone else pulling the strings from the shadows?

93000004-FameContents-.name: Recon: Ladin's Shady Dealings
93000004-FameContents-.desc: While keeping an eye on Blackstar, a Dark Wind agent saw $npcName:11000264$ pass through the $map:52010010$, which seems really fishy. Head to $map:02010020$ and get in touch with the agents there.
93000004-FameContents-.manual: Meet the $npcName:11000259$ at the $map:02010020$|Meet another $npcName:11000259$|Meet another $npcName:11000259$
93000004-FameContents-.descFameUI: Ladin has been spotted visiting suspicious locations. What is he up to?

93000005-FameContents-.name: Recon: Revealing the Rooks
93000005-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:11003535$ wants to know more about the mysterious assassins who ambushed the Sky Fortress. Every time she's tried to capture one of these Rooks, they've managed to slip her grasp. Head to $map:02000083$ and gather reports from the undercover Dark Wind agents there.
93000005-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Rooks are growing bold! You need information to prepare for their next move.

93000006-FameContents-.name: Recon: Unethical Experiments
93000006-FameContents-.desc:
Rumor has it a company in the Land of Darkness is performing inhumane experiments in an attempt to create superhuman soldiers. The empire needs to know everything it can about this group if it's to put an end to such evil.

Go to $map:03000145$ and meet with Dark Wind's undercover agents.
93000006-FameContents-.manual: Meet the $npcName:11000259$ at the $map:03000145$|Meet another $npcName:11000259$|Meet another $npcName:11000259$
93000006-FameContents-.descFameUI: BeyondLink is up to no good in the Land of Darkness.

93000007-FameContents-.name: Recon: Tria Confidential
93000007-FameContents-.desc: Dark Wind collects info on enemies as well as allies. $npcName:11003535$ has given you a top secret mission to collect high-level intel from $map:02000001$. How exciting! Find the secret agent in $map:02000001$ and get the passphrase.
93000007-FameContents-.descFameUI: A man. A woman. A mystery. A game of intrigue is afoot in the city of Tria...

93000008-FameContents-.name: Recon: The Wounded Dragon
93000008-FameContents-.desc: A dragon-man has been spotted on Karkar Island. Even though he's injured, he's still managed to leave behind a swath of destruction in his rage. Head to the $map:02010029$ and gather intel from Dark Wind's undercover agents.
93000008-FameContents-.manual: Meet the $npcName:11000259$ at the $map:02010029$|Meet another $npcName:11000259$|Meet another $npcName:11000259$
93000008-FameContents-.descFameUI: A dragon-man has been spotted in Karkar. Verify the accuracy of these rumors.

93000009-FameContents-.name: Bad Bad Baba
93000009-FameContents-.desc: Criminals are taking advantage of the chaos in the empire to smuggle $item:30000986$ through $map:02000139$. Intercept their merchandise and bring it in for proper disposal.
93000009-FameContents-.descFameUI: Baba powder is being smuggled through a major port. Intercept the goods before they reach their destination.

93000010-FameContents-.name: The Great Gummy Plot
93000010-FameContents-.desc: Everyone loves $itemPlural:20000015$, but they're also pretty darn sticky. Someone is trying to turn that stickiness into a weapon! Confiscate $itemPlural:30000987$ before they cause some real damage.
93000010-FameContents-.descFameUI: Dubi Gummies: Fruity! Delicious! And... deadly? It's time to enact a product retail on some contraband fruit snacks.

93000011-FameContents-.name: Bad Chemistry
93000011-FameContents-.desc:
Change a single ingredient, and a formula can go from medicinal to explosive. This is exactly what happened at $map:02000134$, when someone thought it would be a good idea to add $itemPlural:20000055$ to one of their experimental drugs.

Now the culprit is selling these $itemPlural:30000988$ on the streets as a new kind of weapon. It's time for you to intervene.
93000011-FameContents-.descFameUI: A dash of slime glob, and this potion becomes a paralyzing stink bomb. It's time to clean up the streets.

93000012-FameContents-.name: More Harm than Good
93000012-FameContents-.desc: In an increasingly dangerous world, average citizens are turning to the black market to defend themselves. Unfortunately, many of the weapons available for sale are in such poor condition that they'd do more harm than good. It's up to you to take these $itemPlural:30000989$ off the market for good.
93000012-FameContents-.descFameUI: As panic grips the empire, more and more people are looking to poorly-made swords for their defense.

93000013-FameContents-.name: Baba Powder Bootleggers
93000013-FameContents-.desc: As it's become harder to smuggle $item:20000046$ from the Land of Darkness, certain shady characters are trying to create their own. Head to $map:02000129$ and search the barrels for $item:30000990$.
93000013-FameContents-.descFameUI: Shady baba dealers are trying to make baba powder inside the empire's borders. Shut down their operation.

93000014-FameContents-.name: A Haven for Dirty Money
93000014-FameContents-.desc: Rumors has it that the forces of darkness are using Blackstar to launder their ill-gotten funds. Head to $map:02010010$ and confiscate their $itemPlural:30000991$.
93000014-FameContents-.descFameUI: Blackstar is using innocent videogame consoles to hide their illegal cash. They must be punished!

93000015-FameContents-.name: Eyes Everywhere
93000015-FameContents-.desc: Dark Wind is everywhere and nowhere, but they've had a few issues with manpower after the invasion on $map:02000001$. They've resorted to watching some placed via security cameras. Hack the system and secure the $item:30000992$.
93000015-FameContents-.descFameUI: Dark Wind is stretched too thin to keep tabs on everything. It's time to get a little boost from technology.

93000016-FameContents-.name: Criminal Numbers
93000016-FameContents-.desc: Blackstar controls the darker elements of Maple World's society. However, no matter how closely Dark Wind watches them, Blackstar is careful to always cover its tracks. You'll need to track down Blackstar's secret accounts if you want to bring them to justice.
93000016-FameContents-.descFameUI: Blackstar is an infamous gang, but they never leave behind any physical evidence. Maybe you can change that.

93000017-FameContents-.name: Manhunt: Flora Avenue
93000017-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:11000044$'s forces were spotted on $map:02000147$. Are they trying to keep an eye on $npcName:11000069$? Head there and look for him.
93000017-FameContents-.descFameUI: Katvan's traitorous lackeys have been spotted on Flora Avenue! Find their hideout and root them out.

93000018-FameContents-.name: Manhunt: Auto Bridge
93000018-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:11000044$'s forces were spotted at the $map:02010039$ in Karkar. There are plenty of places for him and his men to hide out in a place like that. Head there and look for them.
93000018-FameContents-.descFameUI: Katvan's traitorous lackeys have been spotted at the Auto Bridge! Find their hideout and root them out.

93000019-FameContents-.name: Manhunt: Infernal Tree
93000019-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:11000044$'s forces were spotted near the $map:03000103$. This is the last place he was seen alive—are they searching for their boss? Head there and find him first.
93000019-FameContents-.descFameUI: Katvan's traitorous lackeys have been spotted at the Infernal Tree! Find their hideout and root them out.

93000020-FameContents-.name: Manhunt: Ant Tunnel Entrance
93000020-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:11000044$'s forces were spotted near the $map:02000173$. Rumors of a killer mushroom have scared most people from heading out that way—it's the perfect hiding place for $npcName:11000044$. Head there and look for him.
93000020-FameContents-.descFameUI: Katvan's traitorous lackeys have been spotted at the Ant Tunnel Entrance! Find their hideout and root them out.

93000021-FameContents-.name: Manhunt: Hushwood Vale
93000021-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:11000044$'s forces were spotted in $map:02000116$. Since the roads there are too dangerous even for merchant caravans, it's the perfect hiding spot. Head there and look for him.
93000021-FameContents-.descFameUI: Katvan's traitorous lackeys have been spotted in Hushwood Vale! Find their hideout and root them out.

93000022-FameContents-.name: Manhunt: Forsaken Fields
93000022-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:11000044$'s forces were spotted in the $map:02000414$. Before they could be apprehended, they fled deep into the dangerous fields. Head there and find them.
93000022-FameContents-.descFameUI: Katvan's traitorous lackeys have been spotted at the Forsaken Fields! Find their hideout and root them out.

93000023-FameContents-.name: Manhunt: Lavaluna Cave
93000023-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:11000044$'s forces were spotted near $map:02000040$. He may be looking to recruit the prison laborers who work the caverns. Head there and look for him.
93000023-FameContents-.descFameUI: Katvan's traitorous lackeys have been spotted in Lavaluna Cave! Find their hideout and root them out.

93000024-FameContents-.name: Manhunt: Cave of Eternity
93000024-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:11000044$'s forces were spotted in the $map:02000192$. Before he went into hiding, $npcName:11000044$ had plans to turn the cave into a major outpost. Head there and look for him.
93000024-FameContents-.descFameUI: Katvan's traitorous lackeys have been spotted in the Cave of Eternity! Find their hideout and root them out.

93000025-FameContents-.name: Manhunt: Black Forest
93000025-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:11000044$'s forces were spotted in the $map:03000006$. It's possible that the shifty denizens of that dark place are giving them sanctuary. Head there and look for him.
93000025-FameContents-.descFameUI: Katvan's traitorous lackeys have been spotted in the Black Forest! Find their hideout and root them out.

93000026-FameContents-.name: Manhunt: Forgotten Keep
93000026-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:11000044$'s forces were spotted in the $map:02000013$. If his men manage to take control of the fortress, it'll be impossible to get them out again. Head there and look for him.
93000026-FameContents-.descFameUI: Katvan's traitorous lackeys have been spotted at the Forgotten Keep! Find their hideout and root them out.

93000027-FameContents-.name: Protect New Kerningdom
93000027-FameContents-.desc: The Rooks have set their sights on $map:02000271$, where outstanding mechanical engineers reside. The knowledge of those engineers is an important asset to Victoria Island. Hurry over to $map:02000271$ and defeat the Rooks!

93000028-FameContents-.name: Kerning Junkyard Defense
93000028-FameContents-.desc: The Rooks have set their sights on the $map:02000084$, where all of Victoria Island's wastewater and trash are processed. The citizens of the empire will take a huge hit to their hygiene if the Rooks are successful.
93000028-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Rooks are targeting major strategic sites around Maple World.

93000029-FameContents-.name: Stone Quarry Defense
93000029-FameContents-.desc: The Rooks have set their sights on the $map:02000058$, where all of Victoria Island's stone is processed. Infrastructure and construction will ground to a halt if the Rooks are successful.
93000029-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Rooks are targeting major strategic sites around Maple World.

93000030-FameContents-.name: Water Supply Center Defense
93000030-FameContents-.desc: The Rooks have set their sights on the $map:02000274$, which manages all of Victoria Island's water. The residents of Victoria Island won't last even a week if the Rooks are successful.
93000030-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Rooks are targeting major strategic sites around Maple World.

93000031-FameContents-.name: Kernel Energy Research Defense
93000031-FameContents-.desc: The Rooks have set their sights on $map:02000276$, where many dangerous materials and chemicals are stored. If the Rooks are successful, they could trigger a massive explosion.
93000031-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Rooks are targeting major strategic sites around Maple World.

93000032-FameContents-.name: Lavaworks Defense
93000032-FameContents-.desc: The Rooks have set their sights on the $map:02000086$, which is an important part of Victoria Island's weapons manufacturing industry. If the Rooks are successful, the empire won't be able to keep its military armed and armored.
93000032-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Rooks are targeting major strategic sites around Maple World.

93000033-FameContents-.name: Aurora Laboratory Defense
93000033-FameContents-.desc: The Rooks have set their sights on $map:02000412$, which is a hub of the empire's top secret research. If the Rooks are successful, who knows what valuable technology will fall into their hands?
93000033-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Rooks are targeting major strategic sites around Maple World.

93000043-FameContents-.name: Research: Pim's Lantern
93000043-FameContents-.desc: $npcNamePlural:40000018$, which often appear in $map:03000146$ , are never found without their green lanterns. For these lanterns to emit light through the intense miasma of the Land of Darkness... They must possess tremendous energy.
93000043-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Lumiknights need your help with some delicate research.

93000044-FameContents-.name: Research: Writhing Straw
93000044-FameContents-.desc: The $npcNamePlural:40000136$ wandering the $map:03000130$ are always filled with rage. Apparently the $itemPlural:30000995$ from which they are made are filled with dark power. Gather some so that the Lumiknights can learn more about these unusual foes.
93000044-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Lumiknights need your help with some delicate research.

93000045-FameContents-.name: Research: Broken Staves
93000045-FameContents-.desc: Defeat the cursed $npcNamePlural:40000055$ and retrieve the crystal balls from their staves.
93000045-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Lumiknights need your help with some delicate research.

93000046-FameContents-.name: Research: Savage Waters
93000046-FameContents-.desc:
The $npcNamePlural:40000071$ are savage, but once they drink the water at $map:03000143$, their savagery grows exponentially.

Defeat the $npcNamePlural:40000071$ and collect their drinking water.
93000046-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Lumiknights need your help with some delicate research.

93000047-FameContents-.name: Research: Mushroom Shock
93000047-FameContents-.desc: The $npcNamePlural:40000134$ receive a constant IV drip of medicine, and yet they're unable to recover from the $itemPlural:30000998$ they've eaten. It seems that, once ingested, these $itemPlural:30000998$ doom them to total corruption sooner or later. Defeat the $npcNamePlural:40000134$ tainted by darkness and retrieve the $itemPlural:30000998$.
93000047-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Lumiknights need your help with some delicate research.

93000048-FameContents-.name: Research: Muddy Motives
93000048-FameContents-.desc: The $npcNamePlural:40000080$ once valued cleanliness above all else, but now they spend their days rolling in the dirt. Could the $item:30000999$ be behind this sudden transformation? Gather some to find out.
93000048-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Lumiknights need your help with some delicate research.

93000049-FameContents-.name: Research: Darkstones
93000049-FameContents-.desc: As their names suggest, $npcNamePlural:40000122$ just love to steal. After stealing a stockpile of $itemPlural:30001000$, however, they've switched from petty theft to violent crime. Gather the $itemPlural:30001000$ in order to learn more about their strange powers.
93000049-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Lumiknights need your help with some delicate research.

93000050-FameContents-.name: Research: Mushrooms and Apples
93000050-FameContents-.desc: $npcNamePlural:40000109$ use $itemPlural:30001001$ to make poisoned apples. That's a lot of poison! Gather some of these mushrooms for analysis.
93000050-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Lumiknights need your help with some delicate research.

93000051-FameContents-.name: Divine Remains: Midden
93000051-FameContents-.desc:
The Lumiknights believe that the Land of Darkness is fueled by the remains of the goddess of darkness herself. If this is true, then her remains might be located near hot spots of dark magic.

The shadow energy in the $map:03000089$ has been unusually high lately. Go there and investigate.
93000051-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Lumiknights are researching the goddess of darkness and her remains...

93000052-FameContents-.name: Divine Remains: Ena
93000052-FameContents-.desc:
The Lumiknights believe that the Land of Darkness is fueled by the remains of the goddess of darkness herself. If this is true, then her remains might be located near hot spots of dark magic.

In $map:03000057$, there stands an ominous pyramid. Is it somehow connected to one of the goddess's cults? Investigate it for yourself.
93000052-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Lumiknights are researching the goddess of darkness and her remains...

93000053-FameContents-.name: Divine Remains: Dio
93000053-FameContents-.desc:
The Lumiknights believe that the Land of Darkness is fueled by the remains of the goddess of darkness herself. If this is true, then her remains might be located near hot spots of dark magic.

There are the remnants of an ancient cult on $map:03000115$. Perhaps this is related to the goddess somehow.
93000053-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Lumiknights are researching the goddess of darkness and her remains...

93000054-FameContents-.name: Divine Remains: Tria
93000054-FameContents-.desc:
The Lumiknights believe that the Land of Darkness is fueled by the remains of the goddess of darkness herself. If this is true, then her remains might be located near hot spots of dark magic.

$map:03000118$ was once a busy trade route, but the shadows have grown treacherously thick. Could a remnant of the goddess be hidden there?
93000054-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Lumiknights are researching the goddess of darkness and her remains...

93000055-FameContents-.name: Divine Remains: Tesera
93000055-FameContents-.desc:
The Lumiknights believe that the Land of Darkness is fueled by the remains of the goddess of darkness herself. If this is true, then her remains might be located near hot spots of dark magic.

$map:03000022$  has become inundated with off-putting blinking plants. Were they fertilized by the remains of a dark divine?
93000055-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Lumiknights are researching the goddess of darkness and her remains...

93000056-FameContents-.name: Divine Remains: Thea
93000056-FameContents-.desc:
The Lumiknights believe that the Land of Darkness is fueled by the remains of the goddess of darkness herself. If this is true, then her remains might be located near hot spots of dark magic.

$map:03000117$ has become inundated with off-putting blinking plants. Were they fertilized by the remains of a dark divine?
93000056-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Lumiknights are researching the goddess of darkness and her remains...

93000057-FameContents-.name: Divine Remains: Exi
93000057-FameContents-.desc:
The Lumiknights believe that the Land of Darkness is fueled by the remains of the goddess of darkness herself. If this is true, then her remains might be located near hot spots of dark magic.

The shadow energy in $map:03000101$ has been unusually high lately. Go there and investigate.
93000057-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Lumiknights are researching the goddess of darkness and her remains...

93000058-FameContents-.name: Divine Remains: Okto
93000058-FameContents-.desc:
The Lumiknights believe that the Land of Darkness is fueled by the remains of the goddess of darkness herself. If this is true, then her remains might be located near hot spots of dark magic.

There is an abandoned fortress at $map:03000007$ where it seems a great battle once took place. Go there and investigate.
93000058-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Lumiknights are researching the goddess of darkness and her remains...

93000059-FameContents-.name: Divine Remains: Enya
93000059-FameContents-.desc:
The Lumiknights believe that the Land of Darkness is fueled by the remains of the goddess of darkness herself. If this is true, then her remains might be located near hot spots of dark magic.

The once-pristine lake of $map:03000024$ has been reduced to putrid swamp. Go there and investigate.
93000059-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Lumiknights are researching the goddess of darkness and her remains...

93000060-FameContents-.name: Divine Remains: Deka
93000060-FameContents-.desc:
The Lumiknights believe that the Land of Darkness is fueled by the remains of the goddess of darkness herself. If this is true, then her remains might be located near hot spots of dark magic.

A deluge of evil has rendered $map:03000009$ uninhabitable. Search the area for divine remains.
93000060-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Lumiknights are researching the goddess of darkness and her remains...

93000061-FameContents-.name: World Stone: Shadow Gate
93000061-FameContents-.desc: The Lumiknights watch over the World Stones, magic relics throughout Maple World that exist to suppress the darkness. The World Stone at the $map:02000146$ has been broken, and now it falls to you to fix it.
93000061-FameContents-.manual: Return the World Stone Shard at the $map:02000146$|Repair the World Stone at the $map:02000146$
93000061-FameContents-.descFameUI: The World Stones stand as sentinels against the dark. But now, the World Stones are in danger...

93000062-FameContents-.name: World Stone: Cave of Eternity
93000062-FameContents-.desc: The Lumiknights watch over the World Stones, magic relics throughout Maple World that exist to suppress the darkness. The World Stone in the $map:02000192$ was cracked by an overzealous $npcName:21091023$, and now it falls to you to fix it.
93000062-FameContents-.manual: Return the World Stone Shard in the $map:02000192$|Repair the World Stone in the $map:02000192$
93000062-FameContents-.descFameUI: The World Stones stand as sentinels against the dark. But now, the World Stones are in danger...

93000063-FameContents-.name: World Stone: Caustic Garden
93000063-FameContents-.desc: The Lumiknights watch over the World Stones, magic relics throughout Maple World that exist to suppress the darkness. The World Stone in the $map:02000180$ was damaged, and now it falls to you to fix it.
93000063-FameContents-.manual: Return the World Stone Shard in the $map:02000180$|Repair the World Stone in the $map:02000180$
93000063-FameContents-.descFameUI: The World Stones stand as sentinels against the dark. But now, the World Stones are in danger...

93000064-FameContents-.name: Peppermint Root Examination
93000064-FameContents-.desc:
The Green Hoods are analyzing everyday items in search of new and more effective ways they can be utilized. $npcName:11003536$ says the current subject matter is $item:30000231$ and requests that you collect some for her.

(Collect them by defeating plant monsters, fairfolk enemies, or inanimate monsters level 15 or higher.)
93000064-FameContents-.descFameUI: Peppermint Root is a useful alchemical reagent. Researchers on Sky Fortress want samples of it for their work.

93000065-FameContents-.name: Black Pine Mushroom Composition Test
93000065-FameContents-.desc:
The Green Hoods are analyzing everyday items in search of new and more effective ways they can be utilized. $npcName:11003536$ says the current subject matter is $item:30000233$ and requests that you collect some for her.

(Collect them by defeating spirit monsters or undead monsters level 15 or higher.)
93000065-FameContents-.descFameUI: Black Pine Mushroom is a useful alchemical reagent. Researchers on Sky Fortress want samples of it for their work.

93000066-FameContents-.name: Cornelian Cherry Distillation Test
93000066-FameContents-.desc:
The Green Hoods are analyzing everyday items in search of new and more effective ways they can be utilized. $npcName:11003536$ says the current subject matter is $item:30000232$ and requests that you collect some for her.

(Obtained occasionally when defeating beast monsters or insect monsters level 15 or higher.)
93000066-FameContents-.descFameUI: Cornelian Cherries are believed to have many fantastic properties. But are the legends true?

93000067-FameContents-.name: Potion Solvent Distillation Test
93000067-FameContents-.desc:
The Green Hoods are analyzing everyday items in search of new and more effective ways they can be utilized. $npcName:11003536$ says the current subject matter is $item:30000230$ and requests that you collect some for her.

(Collect them by defeating divine monsters, humanoid foes, devil monsters, or machine monsters level 15 or higher.)
93000067-FameContents-.descFameUI: Potion Solvents are the foundation of modern potion-making. Gather some samples for the ship's research team.

93000068-FameContents-.name: Suspicious Sweetener Chemical Analysis
93000068-FameContents-.desc:
The Green Hoods are analyzing everyday items in search of new and more effective ways they can be utilized or to ensure they're safe for human usage. $npcName:11003536$ says the current subject matter is $item:30000242$ and requests that you collect some for her.

(Collect them by defeating plant, insect, humanoid, undead, or inanimate monsters level 15 or higher.)
93000068-FameContents-.descFameUI: Sky Fortress's scientists need a large sample of $item:30000242$ for their research.

93000069-FameContents-.name: Suspicious Meat Chemical Analysis
93000069-FameContents-.desc:
The Green Hoods are analyzing everyday items in search of new and more effective ways they can be utilized or to ensure they're safe for human usage. $npcName:11003536$ says the current subject matter is $item:30000240$ and requests that you collect some for her.

(Collect them by defeating beast, insect, undead, devil, or inanimate monsters level 15 or higher.)
93000069-FameContents-.descFameUI: Sky Fortress's scientists need a large sample of Suspicious Meat for their research.

93000070-FameContents-.name: Suspicious Seasoning Nanoscopic Scan
93000070-FameContents-.desc:
The Green Hoods are analyzing everyday items in search of new and more effective ways they can be utilized or to ensure they're safe for human usage. $npcName:11003536$ says the current subject matter is $item:30000241$ and requests that you collect some for her.

(Collect them by defeating divine, spirit, fairfolk, or machine monsters level 15 or higher.)
93000070-FameContents-.descFameUI: The ship's science team is performing an exhaustive study on Suspicious Seasoning.

93000071-FameContents-.name: Arming the Troops
93000071-FameContents-.desc: The soldiers of Sky Fortress are woefully underequipped. Donate some of your old gear to keep them in fighting shape.
93000071-FameContents-.descFameUI: The soldiers of Sky Fortress are woefully underequipped. Donate some of your old gear to keep them in fighting shape.

93000072-FameContents-.name: Arming the Platoon
93000072-FameContents-.desc: The soldiers of Sky Fortress are woefully underequipped. Donate some of your old gear to keep them in fighting shape.
93000072-FameContents-.descFameUI: The soldiers of Sky Fortress are woefully underequipped. Donate some of your old gear to keep them in fighting shape.

93000073-FameContents-.name: Regiment Funding
93000073-FameContents-.desc: Keeping Sky Fortress fully manned and supplied isn't cheap. Donate your "excess" mesos to $npcName:11003536$.
93000073-FameContents-.descFameUI: It costs a lot of mesos to keep an army supplied and fed. Can you make a donation to Sky Fortress's war fund?

93000074-FameContents-.name: Copper Ingot Collection
93000074-FameContents-.desc: $map:02000001$ and the areas nearby have suffered a lot of damage from $npcName:11001698$'s attacks, leading to a huge loss of resources, lives, and morale. Use your mining and smithing skills to collect $itemPlural:33000063$ to help with the city's reconstruction.
93000074-FameContents-.descFameUI: Take out your mining pick and anvil. Tria needs Copper Ingots!

93000075-FameContents-.name: Tin Ingot Collection
93000075-FameContents-.desc: $map:02000001$ and the areas nearby have suffered a lot of damage from $npcName:11001698$'s attacks, leading to a huge loss of resources, lives, and morale. Use your mining and smithing skills to collect $itemPlural:33000064$ to help with the city's reconstruction.
93000075-FameContents-.descFameUI: Take out your mining pick and anvil. Tria needs Tin Ingots!

93000076-FameContents-.name: Zinc Ingot Collection
93000076-FameContents-.desc: $map:02000001$ and the areas nearby have suffered a lot of damage from $npcName:11001698$'s attacks, leading to a huge loss of resources, lives, and morale. Use your mining and smithing skills to collect $itemPlural:33000065$ to help with the city's reconstruction.
93000076-FameContents-.descFameUI: Take out your mining pick and anvil. Tria needs Zinc Ingots!

93000077-FameContents-.name: Zinc Glove Requisition
93000077-FameContents-.desc: $map:02000001$ and the areas nearby have suffered a lot of damage from $npcName:11001698$'s attacks, leading to a huge loss of resources, lives, and morale. Use your mining and smithing skills to collect $itemPlural:20000352$ to help with the city's reconstruction.
93000077-FameContents-.descFameUI: The ranching industry is in shambles after Madria's attacks. Help them restock their equipment.

93000078-FameContents-.name: Silver Ingot Collection
93000078-FameContents-.desc: $map:02000001$ and the areas nearby have suffered a lot of damage from $npcName:11001698$'s attacks, leading to a huge loss of resources, lives, and morale. Use your mining and smithing skills to collect $itemPlural:33000066$ to help with the city's reconstruction.
93000078-FameContents-.descFameUI: Take out your mining pick and anvil. Tria needs Silver Ingots!

93000079-FameContents-.name: Sapphire Smithing Slate Collection
93000079-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:11003534$ says that blacksmiths and other volunteers working hard to repair $map:02000001$, but they're short on manpower. Get a $item:20000358$ for the volunteers to help get them up to speed.
93000079-FameContents-.descFameUI: Not all of the volunteers working in Tria are experienced craftsmen. Get them something to help them learn.

93000080-FameContents-.name: Iron Glove Requisition
93000080-FameContents-.desc: The ranching industry isn't recovering quickly enough. Supply some $itemPlural:20000353$ to aid productivity.
93000080-FameContents-.descFameUI: The ranching industry is in shambles after Madria's attacks. Help them restock their equipment.

93000081-FameContents-.name: Food for the Hungry
93000081-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:11001698$'s invasion damaged essential Victoria Island agricultural sectors, leading to food shortages all over. $item:33000147$ is easy to store and lasts a long time, so use your farming and cooking skills to craft some for the hungry.
93000081-FameContents-.descFameUI: The forces of darkness have razed the empire's bread basket. It's time to feed the hungry.

93000082-FameContents-.name: Soup for the Cold and Hungry
93000082-FameContents-.desc: In the wake of $npcName:11001698$'s attack, many of the empire's citizens are left cold and hungry. Address both issues at once by cooking some $item:20000431$.
93000082-FameContents-.descFameUI: When you're cold and hungry, nothing beats a hot bowl of soup.

93000083-FameContents-.name: An Apple a Day
93000083-FameContents-.desc: Some citizens have been consuming $item:30000242$ to curb their sweet tooth during the food shortage. $npcName:11003534$ doesn't approve, and wants to feed them the healthier option of $itemPlural:33000149$ instead.
93000083-FameContents-.descFameUI: The people of the empire need their sweets! Perhaps you can scrounge up something healthier for them.

93000084-FameContents-.name: Gone to Waste
93000084-FameContents-.desc: Refugees from the war against the darkness have been living on apple rations, but the apples have all gone bad. $npcName:11003534$ suggests providing $item:20000420$ instead.
93000084-FameContents-.descFameUI: The civilian apple rations have gone bad. Maybe they should be properly preserved this time.

93000085-FameContents-.name: Training on an Empty Tummy
93000085-FameContents-.desc: The Royal Guards are too busy to take care of their own health. Prepare some $itemPlural:33000150$ for $npcName:11003534$ to pass out to his men.
93000085-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Royal Guard is working tirelessly to look after the people, but who is looking after them?

93000086-FameContents-.name: Spice for the Weary
93000086-FameContents-.desc: Morale is low amongst the folks of Victoria Island. Perhaps something flavorful like $item:20000426$ will help cheer them up!
93000086-FameContents-.descFameUI: The food from the reserve supplies are bland, to say the least. Perhaps some seasoning could cheer people up...

93000087-FameContents-.name: Orange You Glad I Didn't Say...
93000087-FameContents-.desc: Everyone's been working so hard to rebuild $map:02000001$ that they've been skipping meals. Perhaps some $itemPlural:33000151$ will offer them refreshment.
93000087-FameContents-.descFameUI: Certain things must never be forgotten, no matter how busy or hopeless the situation: love, peace, and tasty snacks.

93000088-FameContents-.name: Medicine in a Pinch
93000088-FameContents-.desc: There isn't enough medicine to treat everyone who was injured in Madria's attack. Obtain some $item:33000132$ to offer relief to those who aren't critically wounded.
93000088-FameContents-.descFameUI: Help gather medicine for all of the people who were injured in the battle against the darkness.

93000089-FameContents-.name: Fragrant Relief
93000089-FameContents-.desc: Some of the guards are still in a lot of pain from wounds they received during the invasion, but there's not enough pain medication for everyone. $npcName:11003534$ suggests using $item:33000100$ in the form of $item:20000405$ as a holistic alternative instead.
93000089-FameContents-.descFameUI: Many guardsmen were hurt protecting Tria. There must be some way to ease their pain.

93000090-FameContents-.name: Itchin' a Scratch
93000090-FameContents-.desc: The squad of guards was bitten by monster bugs, and now they itch like crazy. Some $item:33000108$ Essence should do the trick!
93000090-FameContents-.descFameUI: A squad of soldiers got some monster bug bites. Can you help itch their scratch?

93000091-FameContents-.name: A Personal Request
93000091-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:11003534$ quietly requests for you to obtain some $item:20000408$, known to help with hair growth.
93000091-FameContents-.descFameUI: A special mission from the captain himself. Requires utmost discretion.

93000092-FameContents-.name: The Common Cold
93000092-FameContents-.desc: There's a cold going around. $npcName:11003534$ asked you to make $item:33000135$ to help combat the illness.
93000092-FameContents-.descFameUI: It's cold season. Time to whip up some medicine.

93000093-FameContents-.name: Poisoned Guards
93000093-FameContents-.desc: Some guards were poisoned in a recent battle. Obtain $item:20000414$, which you claim has detoxifying properties, to help them.
93000093-FameContents-.descFameUI: Antidotes were hard to find even when there was an abundance of supplies. Luckily, you have a few tricks up your sleeve.

93000094-FameContents-.name: The Cure-All
93000094-FameContents-.desc: Battle scars may be a mark of honor, but open wounds are a hazard. $npcName:11003534$ suggested obtaining some $itemPlural:33000136$ to use as a general cure-all.
93000094-FameContents-.descFameUI: There is a dire need for medicine right now. If only there was an All-cure Tonic, even just one would be enough.

93000095-FameContents-.name: A Sturdy-ish Replacement
93000095-FameContents-.desc: Many folks were displaced from their homes after $npcName:11001698$ attacked and had to set up temporary tents, but their tent fabric is starting to tear. Use your ranching and handicraft skills to make $item:33000076$ for people to use to repair their tents.
93000095-FameContents-.descFameUI: Daily necessities have been hard to obtain since Madria's invasion. But that's why we got you, isn't it?

93000096-FameContents-.name: Fresh Powdered Snail
93000096-FameContents-.desc: $item:33000077$ is a crucial ingredient for a lot of everyday items. Obtain some for the Royal Guard.
93000096-FameContents-.descFameUI: Help stem the tide of the snail shell shortage.

93000097-FameContents-.name: Chewing Pigskin
93000097-FameContents-.desc: $item:33000078$ is used to make all kinds of useful items, but there's been a shortage since the attack. Make some $item:33000078$ for $map:02000001$ to help ease the shortage.
93000097-FameContents-.descFameUI: When the people are hungry enough to eat pigskin, there isn't enough pigskin for the artisans to craft with...

93000098-FameContents-.name: Pigskin Power
93000098-FameContents-.desc: $itemPlural:20000345$ would speed along the process of fixing $map:02000001$'s city walls. Go obtain some.
93000098-FameContents-.descFameUI: The damage to Tria's city walls is immense. There must be some way you can help with the repairs.

93000099-FameContents-.name: For Strong Bones
93000099-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:11003534$ wants $item:33000079$ for his men because they're too scrawny. Go get some for him.
93000099-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Royal Guard must be strong for Tria to be strong. A healthy dosing of Milk Powder will put some meat on their bones.

93000100-FameContents-.name: Home Repair
93000100-FameContents-.desc: With so much damage to repair, $itemPlural:20000364$ would be really useful to help boost productivity. Use your ranching and handicraft skills to craft a $item:20000364$.
93000100-FameContents-.descFameUI: Most resources have been directed toward repairing the city's walls, but civilians need their homes repaired, too.

93000101-FameContents-.name: Working in the Cold
93000101-FameContents-.desc: Reality is cold, but the Royal Guards don't have to be cold while they work. Not if you bring them some $item:33000080$!
93000101-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Royal Guard isn't properly equipped for cold climates. Help them gear up.

93000102-FameContents-.name: Red Alert: Monty de Carro
93000102-FameContents-.desc:
A red alert was issued for the $map:02000262$. $npcName:22000045$ is summoning an army of monsters.

Go to $map:02000262$, wipe out the local monsters, and defeat $npcName:22000045$.
93000102-FameContents-.descFameUI: Ludition Carnival is on Red Alert! Multiple hostile targets detected.

93000103-FameContents-.name: Red Alert: Lerta
93000103-FameContents-.desc:
A red alert was issued for the $map:02000175$, where $npcName:22000052$'s dark influence is driving the nearby monsters into a frenzy.

Defeat $npcName:22000052$ and his minions.
93000103-FameContents-.descFameUI: Frostember Void is on red alert! Restore peace through force of arms.

93000104-FameContents-.name: Red Alert: Phantom Destroyer
93000104-FameContents-.desc:
A red alert was issued for the $map:02000275$. A group of monsters tried to hack into the $npcName:22090123$'s control chip, but ended up sending the robot into a frenzy, instead.

Go to the $map:02000275$ and defeat both $npcName:22090123$ and the nearby monsters.
93000104-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Phantoma Cyborg Center is on red alert! The robots are out of control.

93000105-FameContents-.name: Red Alert: Urska
93000105-FameContents-.desc:
A red alert was issued for $map:02000276$. The great bear, $npcName:22000023$, has gotten into the lab's electricity grid and is going on a powered-up rampage.

Go to $map:02000276$, wipe out the local monsters, and defeat $npcName:22000023$.
93000105-FameContents-.descFameUI: Kernel Energy Research is on red alert! An unauthorized bear has tapped into the power grid.

93000106-FameContents-.name: Red Alert: Molten Knight
93000106-FameContents-.desc:
A red alert was issued for $map:02000018$. The beast known as $npcName:22000034$ and his cohorts are eating the castle right up!

Go to $map:02000018$ and put an end to $npcName:22000034$'s illicit munchies.
93000106-FameContents-.descFameUI: Berrysweet Castle is on red alert! A monster with a monstrous sweet tooth is on the loose.

93000107-FameContents-.name: Red Alert: Ninecap Copper
93000107-FameContents-.desc:
A red alert was issued for $map:02000279$. $npcName:22000042$ has been hacked and is leading a small robot army.

Go to the $map:02000279$, wipe out the local monsters, and defeat $npcName:22000042$.
93000107-FameContents-.descFameUI: Chronoff Train Station is on red alert! Automated defenses have been compromised.

93000108-FameContents-.name: Red Alert: Trauros
93000108-FameContents-.desc:
A red alert was issued for $map:02000171$. $npcName:22000053$ and his band of unruly monsters are hurting the local tourism industry.

Go to $map:02000171$, wipe out the local monsters, and defeat $npcName:22000053$.
93000108-FameContents-.descFameUI: Kolopua Crag is on red alert! The tourism industry is in mortal danger.

93000109-FameContents-.name: Red Alert: Latun
93000109-FameContents-.desc:
A red alert was issued for $map:02000132$. $npcName:22090007$ is summoning monsters non-stop.

Go to $map:02000132$, wipe out the local monsters, and defeat $npcName:22090007$.
93000109-FameContents-.descFameUI: Rose Castle is on red alert! Unauthorized summoning detected.

93000110-FameContents-.name: Red Alert: Lapin
93000110-FameContents-.desc:
A red alert was issued for the $map:02000180$. $npcName:22000007$ is leading a small army of monsters to capture the area.

Go to the $map:02000180$, wipe out the local monsters, and defeat $npcName:22000007$.
93000110-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Caustic Garden is on red alert! Stop the monsters from rallying their forces.

93000111-FameContents-.name: Red Alert: Mano
93000111-FameContents-.desc:
A red alert was issued for $map:02000113$. The generally kind-hearted $npcName:22000059$ has been spotted cavorting with ne'er-do-wells, engaging in horseplay, and generally making a mess of the place.

Go to $map:02000113$, wipe out the local monsters, and defeat $npcName:22000059$.
93000111-FameContents-.descFameUI: Greenia Falls is on red alert! Bullying has reached catastrophic levels.

93000112-FameContents-.name: Red Alert: King Slime
93000112-FameContents-.desc:
A red alert was issued for the $map:02000112$. Agents on the ground report that $npcName:22090107$ is making moves to expand his kingdom and has recruited the local monsters to his cause.

Go to the $map:02000112$, wipe out the local monsters, and defeat $npcName:22090107$.
93000112-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Godspring is on red alert! The slimes are on the move.

93000113-FameContents-.name: Red Alert: Stumpy
93000113-FameContents-.desc:
A red alert was issued for $map:02000185$. The raging $npcName:22000001$ is spreading a dark disease, making nearby monsters feral.

Go to $map:02000185$, wipe out the local monsters, and defeat $npcName:22000001$.
93000113-FameContents-.descFameUI: Sweet Tooth Valley is on red alert! Fight the mysterious monster epidemic.

93000114-FameContents-.name: Red Alert: Zombie Mushmom
93000114-FameContents-.desc:
A red alert was issued for the $map:02000173$. $npcName:99000055$ is using her talisman to control the monsters in that area.

Go to the $map:02000173$, wipe out the local monsters, and defeat $npcName:99000055$.
93000114-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Ant Tunnel Entrance is on red alert! The dark fungal necromancy in the area is out of control.

93000115-FameContents-.name: Red Alert: Dark Girant
93000115-FameContents-.desc:
A red alert was issued for $map:02000089$. Radars indicate a spike in magical power coming from $npcName:22000038$.

Go to $map:02000089$, wipe out the local monsters, and defeat $npcName:22000038$.
93000115-FameContents-.descFameUI: Torhara Spring is on red alert! A dark energy cascade is sweeping through the area.

93000116-FameContents-.name: Red Alert: Varaha
93000116-FameContents-.desc:
A red alert was issued for the $map:02000087$. $npcName:22000002$ is throwing the area into chaos.

Go to $map:02000087$, wipe out the local monsters, and defeat $npcName:22000002$.
93000116-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Andrea Barony is on red alert! A rude, crude pig from the city is tearing up the countryside.

93000117-FameContents-.name: Red Alert: Madonette
93000117-FameContents-.desc:
A red alert was issued for $map:02000147$. A strange doll monster has appeared.

Go to $map:02000147$, wipe out the local monsters, and defeat $npcName:22090165$.
93000117-FameContents-.descFameUI: Flora Avenue is on red alert! The local convenience store is in danger.

93000118-FameContents-.name: Red Alert: Nyxie and Epi
93000118-FameContents-.desc:
A red alert was issued for $map:02000041$. $npcName:22000003$ and $npcName:22000004$ are driving nearby monsters into a frenzy with their bickering.

Go to $map:02000041$, wipe out the local monsters, and defeat $npcName:22000003$ and $npcName:22000004$.
93000118-FameContents-.descFameUI: Fairy Tree Lake is on Red Alert! A family squabble is spiraling out of control!

93000119-FameContents-.name: Red Alert: Chaw
93000119-FameContents-.desc:
A red alert was issued for $map:02000083$, where roving gangs of masked criminals have practically shut down the city.

Defeat the gangs of $map:02000083$.
93000119-FameContents-.descFameUI: Kerning Interchange is on red alert! Criminal activity has reached critical levels.

93000120-FameContents-.name: Red Alert: Urza
93000120-FameContents-.desc:
A red alert was issued for $map:02000117$. $npcName:22000022$ is in a frenzy after being denied her favorite honey treat.

Go to $map:02000117$, wipe out the local monsters, and defeat $npcName:22000022$.
93000120-FameContents-.descFameUI: Crooked Canyon is on red alert! Wild bear sightings reported.

93000121-FameContents-.name: Normal Adventure Assault
93000121-FameContents-.desc: There are threats to the peace hidden everywhere. Clear a normal adventure dungeon to help make Maple World a better place.
93000121-FameContents-.descFameUI: There's only so much that Sky Fortress can do. Walk the world and help those in need.

93000122-FameContents-.name: Hard Adventure Assault
93000122-FameContents-.desc:
Even though it's formidable, Sky Fortress isn't invincible. There are certain places that the ship can't go.

Captain $npcName:11003533$ has given you a directive to fight enemies beyond Sky Fortress's reach. Clear a hard adventure dungeon.
93000122-FameContents-.descFameUI: There are many places that Sky Fortress can't go. Take the fight to the enemy's greatest strongholds.

93000123-FameContents-.name: Maple Alliance Weapon Test
93000123-FameContents-.desc: Sky Fortress has developed a new weapon that provides supporting fire from on high by launching powerful artillery. Basic systems checks are complete, but the force of the bombs hasn't been measured yet. That's where you come in.
93000123-FameContents-.descFameUI: Help test the new Royal Guard weapon, the 150 mm Alliance Smoothbore.

93000124-FameContents-.name: Lumiknight Weapon Test
93000124-FameContents-.desc: Sky Fortress has developed a new weapon that provides supporting fire from on high by firing a laser cannon on the specified target. Basic systems checks are complete, but the force of the cannon hasn't been measured yet. That's where you come in.
93000124-FameContents-.descFameUI: Help test the new Lumiknight weapon, the Manastorm Cannon.

93000125-FameContents-.name: Dark Wind Weapon Test
93000125-FameContents-.desc: Sky Fortress has developed a new weapon that provides supporting fire from on high by dropping projectiles that continuously attack enemies. Basic systems checks are complete, but the force of the projectiles hasn't been measured yet. That's where you come in.
93000125-FameContents-.descFameUI: Help test the new Dark Wind weapon, the Shadow Mortar.

93000126-FameContents-.name: Royal Guard Weapon Test
93000126-FameContents-.desc: Sky Fortress has developed new technology that provides support from on high by shining a healing light in a target area. Basic systems checks are complete, but the power of the light hasn't been measured yet. That's where you come in.
93000126-FameContents-.descFameUI: Help test the new Royal Guard weapon, the Sanctuary Flare.

93000127-FameContents-.name: Green Hood Weapon Test
93000127-FameContents-.desc: Sky Fortress has developed new technology that provides support from on high by granting an attack buff to everyone in a target area. Basic systems checks are complete, but the power of the buff hasn't been measured yet. That's where you come in.
93000127-FameContents-.descFameUI: Help test the new Green Hood weapon, Nature's Call.

93000133-FameContents-.name: Dueling Horns
93000133-FameContents-.desc: $npcNamePlural:21000027$ are causing problems at the $map:02000044$. Head over there and clear some of them out.
93000133-FameContents-.descFameUI: After the battle with the Inakimo, Perion's warriors are weakened. Help them keep the peace.

93000134-FameContents-.name: Growing Hostilities
93000134-FameContents-.desc: Ever since the $npcNamePlural:21000312$ appeared in $map:02000093$, the nearby $npcNamePlural:21000311$ and $npcNamePlural:21000310$ have grown more aggressive. Defeat $npcNamePlural:21000312$ to halt this madness.
93000134-FameContents-.descFameUI: Perion needs your help! Join the Royal Guard's efforts to keep the peace.

93000135-FameContents-.name: Wolven Whispers
93000135-FameContents-.desc: $npcNamePlural:21000334$ have been siccing packs of $npcNamePlural:21000066$ on travelers through $map:02000169$!
93000135-FameContents-.descFameUI: Perion needs your help! Join the Royal Guard's efforts to keep the peace.

93000136-FameContents-.name: Water Crisis
93000136-FameContents-.desc: $npcNamePlural:21000069$ are causing problems at the $map:02000049$. Head over there and clear some of them out.
93000136-FameContents-.descFameUI: Perion needs your help! Join the Royal Guard's efforts to keep the peace.

93000137-FameContents-.name: Construction Disruption
93000137-FameContents-.desc: The bonebridge in the Perion region keeps falling apart because $npcNamePlural:21000267$ keep rolling into it when they get itchy. Defeat $npcNamePlural:21000267$ to stop them from disrupting the construction at the $map:02000045$.
93000137-FameContents-.descFameUI: Perion needs your help! Join the Royal Guard's efforts to keep the peace.

93000138-FameContents-.name: Lava Power

93000149-FameContents-.desc: The soldiers of Sky Fortress are woefully underequipped. Donate some of your old gear to keep them in fighting shape.
93000149-FameContents-.descFameUI: The soldiers of Sky Fortress are woefully underequipped. Donate some of your old gear to keep them in fighting shape.

93000150-FameContents-.name: Copper Ingot Stockpiling
93000150-FameContents-.desc: $map:02000001$ and the areas nearby have suffered a lot of damage from $npcName:11001698$'s attacks, leading to a huge loss of resources, lives, and morale. Use your mining and smithing skills to collect $itemPlural:33000063$ to help with the city's reconstruction.
93000150-FameContents-.descFameUI: Take out your mining pick and anvil. Tria needs Copper Ingots!

93000151-FameContents-.name: Copper Ingot Crisis

93000151-FameContents-.descFameUI: Take out your mining pick and anvil. Tria needs Copper Ingots!

93000152-FameContents-.name: Medicine for the Masses
93000152-FameContents-.desc: There isn't enough medicine to treat everyone who was injured in Madria's attack. Obtain some $item:33000132$ to offer relief to those who aren't critically wounded.
93000152-FameContents-.descFameUI: Help gather medicine for all of the people who were injured in the battle against the darkness.

93000153-FameContents-.name: Medicine for the World
93000153-FameContents-.desc: There isn't enough medicine to treat everyone who was injured in Madria's attack. Obtain some $item:33000132$ to offer relief to those who aren't critically wounded.
93000153-FameContents-.descFameUI: Help gather medicine for all of the people who were injured in the battle against the darkness.

93000154-FameContents-.name: Savage Instincts
93000154-FameContents-.desc: A pack of combat-trained $npcNamePlural:21000064$ escaped their cages and have been attacking civilians at $map:02000171$. It's up to you to save the day.
93000154-FameContents-.descFameUI: Packs of war-trained $npcNamePlural:11003523$ have been unleashed. Resolve the problem with force.

93000155-FameContents-.name: Sharp Fangs
93000155-FameContents-.desc: $npcNamePlural:21000301$ are causing problems at $map:02000133$. Head over there and clear some of them out.
93000155-FameContents-.descFameUI: Perion needs your help! Join the Royal Guard's efforts to keep the peace.

93000156-FameContents-.name: Boogie Brainwashed
