93000156-FameContents-.descFameUI: Perion needs your help! Join the Royal Guard's efforts to keep the peace.

93000157-FameContents-.name: Sorcery!
93000157-FameContents-.desc: The jawbreakers at the $map:02000094$ have fallen under the spells of the $npcNamePlural:21000334$. Drive the $npcNamePlural:21000334$ out of the $map:02000094$ to keep things from getting worse.
93000157-FameContents-.descFameUI: Perion needs your help! Join the Royal Guard's efforts to keep the peace.

93000158-FameContents_EP1_01-.name: The Resistance's Secret Weapon
93000158-FameContents_EP1_01-.desc: The Alliance has uncovered that the Resistance's secret weapon is a mech codenamed CHKY-002. Its sole purpose is to take down the Sky Fortress. Allow it to land on the deck, then take it down!
93000158-FameContents_EP1_01-.descFameUI: Reconnaissance has revealed that the Resistance has a new secret weapon: a high-powered assault mech!

93000159-FameContents-.name: Danger Unknown
93000159-FameContents-.desc:
Strange disturbances have been detected on the ground. Someone needs to check them out.

Find and complete a Maple Alliance field mission.
93000159-FameContents-.manual: Complete a Maple Alliance field mission
93000159-FameContents-.descFameUI: Strange disturbances have been detected on the ground. Someone needs to check them out.

93000160-FameContents-.name: Dark Wind Patrol
93000160-FameContents-.desc:
The areas under the Dark Wind tend to have a higher crime rate than others. That means someone needs to regularly go out on patrol to make sure everything is in order.

Find and complete a Dark Wind field mission.
93000160-FameContents-.manual: Complete a Dark Wind field mission
93000160-FameContents-.descFameUI: Dark Wind's jurisdiction has some of the highest crime rates in the empire. They depend on patrols to keep the peace.

93000161-FameContents-.name: Laying the Groundwork
93000161-FameContents-.desc:
The Lumiknights have long wished to reclaim the Land of Darkness. The first step to accomplishing their goal is to send someone out there to scout out the area firsthand.

Find and complete a Lumiknight field mission.
93000161-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Lumiknights have long wished to reclaim the Land of Darkness. But first, they need someone to scout out the area.

93000162-FameContents-.name: Green Hoods Patrol
93000162-FameContents-.desc: Patrolling is important work, according to $npcName:11003536$. She wants you to patrol the areas under the Green Hoods' protection. Find and complete a Green Hood field mission.
93000162-FameContents-.manual: Complete a Green Hood field mission
93000162-FameContents-.descFameUI: Patrolling is important work! Please patrol the areas under the Green Hoods' protection.

93000163-FameContents-.name: Under a Watchful Eye
93000163-FameContents-.desc:
Keeping people safe isn't hard... Just do exactly as $npcName:11003534$ says!

Find and complete a Royal Guard field mission.
93000163-FameContents-.manual: Complete a Royal Guard field mission
93000163-FameContents-.descFameUI: Keeping people safe isn't hard... Just do exactly as $npcName:11003534$ says!

93000164-FameContents-.name: All That Glitters
93000164-FameContents-.desc:
$npcName:23000013$ has become obsessed with all things shiny and has begun robbing, burglarizing, hijacking, and ambushing to increase his glittery collection. Something must be done!

Teach $npcName:23000013$, who appears at the $map:02000084$, that stealing doesn't pay.
93000164-FameContents-.descFameUI: Doondun's greed will lead to disaster! He must be stopped!

93000165-FameContents-.name: Hacking the Hacked
93000165-FameContents-.desc:
Uncover the truth behind $npcName:23000054$, the robot that's been attacking people, by disabling it while Dark Wind hacks its systems.

Defeat $npcName:23000054$ at the $map:02000145$.
93000165-FameContents-.descFameUI: It's time to uncover the mastermind behind the recent robot attacks!

93000166-FameContents-.name: A Big Pollution Problem
93000166-FameContents-.desc: Thanks to all the pollution out at sea, a $npcName:23000018$ has emerged from the waters and is wrecking havoc at $map:02000111$. Put an end to its madness.
93000166-FameContents-.descFameUI: It came from the deep! A massive, pollution-powered monster is attacking our shorelines, and we need you to stop it.

93000167-FameContents-.name: A Father's Rage
93000167-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:23000019$'s eggs were stolen, and he's furious, relentlessly attacking any who cross his path. Put your sympathy aside and defeat $npcName:23000019$ at $map:02000085$ to prevent further loss of life.
93000167-FameContents-.descFameUI: A bereaved father unleashes his wrath on the locals. Now it is your grim duty to end his rampage...

93000168-FameContents-.name: Creature of Darkness
93000168-FameContents-.desc: Darkness spreads at an alarming pace. Defeat $npcNamePlural:23000001$ at the $map:02000115$ to slow it down!
93000168-FameContents-.descFameUI: Darkness spreads. Foreboding fills the air. A creature who has breached the rift must be destroyed!

93000169-FameContents-.name: Dark Cerberus
93000169-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:23000047$, summoned by dark magic, has made $map:02000214$ his home. Destroy $npcName:23000047$ to stop him from sowing chaos and destruction upon the world.
93000169-FameContents-.descFameUI: A great beast has been summoned by dark forces. Send him back to the underworld!

93000170-FameContents-.name: Fixing the Forest
93000170-FameContents-.desc: Moomoo has fallen under Lo's evil influence. Regardless of the reason, they're attacking innocent people and wreaking havoc all over $map:02000103$. Head over there and stop $npcName:23000035$.
93000170-FameContents-.descFameUI: This destruction cannot be allowed to continue! It's time to slam down an iron first!

93000171-FameContents-.name: Holy Rage
93000171-FameContents-.desc: The $npcName:23000099$ has become angered by the trespassers trekking upon his land! He slumbers at the $map:02000021$, waking at intervals to wreak havoc before returning to rest. This can no longer be allowed! Defeat the $npcName:23000099$ at the $map:02000021$.
93000171-FameContents-.descFameUI: There must be a way to calm Vayar. It's time for the guardian to go back to sleep.

93000172-FameContents-.name: The Bitter Cold
93000172-FameContents-.desc: The Maple Alliance discovered that the source of the cold snap coming from $map:02000260$ is $npcName:23000026$. You know what you have to do!
93000172-FameContents-.descFameUI: Frozen toes and icy veins. Only silence can stop the cold.

93000173-FameContents-.name: A Captain's Request
93000173-FameContents-.desc: Captain $npcName:11003582$ is worried that she's out of practice with her swords, so she wants you to spar with her. Face her in the "Duel on the Deck" Fortress Rumble dungeon.
93000173-FameContents-.manual: Spar with $npcName:11003582$ in the "Duel on the Deck" Fortress Rumble

93000174-FameContents-.name: [Special] Sparring in the Skies
93000174-FameContents-.desc:
<font color="#00a2ed">Fortress Rumble Mission</font>
Spar with Captain Veliche atop Sky Fortress! You can face her in the "Duel on the Deck" Fortress Rumble.

(Once you accept this mission, you cannot begin any other weekly [Special] Fortress Rumble missions until the weekly reset.)
93000174-FameContents-.manual: Clear the "Duel on the Deck" Fortress Rumble
93000174-FameContents-.descFameUI:
<font color="#00a2ed">Fortress Rumble Mission</font>
Spar with Captain Veliche atop Sky Fortress!

93000175-FameContents-.name: A Shadow Walker Tradition
93000175-FameContents-.desc: To help you grow stronger, $npcName:11003584$ tells you about a secret Shadow Walker training method: "Kill or be killed." Face her in the "Close Quarters" Fortress Rumble dungeon.
93000175-FameContents-.manual: Spar with $npcName:11003584$ in the "Close Quarters" Fortress Rumble

93000176-FameContents-.descFameUI:
<font color="#00a2ed">Fortress Rumble Mission</font>

93000177-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:11003586$ wants to find out if you're really fated to become the guardian of the world. To prove that you're worthy of that destiny... you must spar with him. Face him in the "Trial by Ordeal" Fortress Rumble dungeon.
93000177-FameContents-.manual: Spar with $npcName:11003586$ in the "Trial by Ordeal" Fortress Rumble

93000178-FameContents-.descFameUI:
<font color="#00a2ed">Fortress Rumble Mission</font>
Mason seeks to help you reach destiny by violence.

93000179-FameContents-.desc: Nairin's Combat Simulator is almost complete. All it needs now is some additional combat data from a real battle. Face her simulation in the "Nairin's Combat Simulator" Fortress Rumble dungeon.

93000180-FameContents-.descFameUI:
<font color="#00a2ed">Fortress Rumble Mission</font>

93000181-FameContents-.name: The Ultimate Fight
93000181-FameContents-.desc: $npcName:11003583$ thinks a little sparring match will help kickstart your career. Face him in the "Training Yard Tussle" Fortress Rumble dungeon.

93000182-FameContents-.name: [Special] Royal Guard Workout

93000183-FameContents-.name: The Guardians Above
93000183-FameContents-.desc: You've received an urgent request from $map:02000255$. Robots have taken over! Head over there and get rid of the robots.
93000183-FameContents-.descFameUI: The Sky Fortress does not turn a blind eye to those on the ground. Enemies of the peace must be defeated!

93000184-FameContents-.name: The Only Good Hoodlum
93000184-FameContents-.desc: A group of masked figures have taken over the $map:02000083$, and $npcName:11003535$ will not allow that under her watch! Head over there and mop up the masked enemies!
93000184-FameContents-.manual: Go to $map:02000083$ and defeat the hoodlums
93000184-FameContents-.descFameUI: A gang of hoodlums are moving in on Dark Wind's turf. Time to show them the error of their ways, Shadow Walker style!

93000185-FameContents-.name: Engulfed in Shadows
93000185-FameContents-.desc: The $map:02000146$ swarms with enemies tainted by darkness. Head over there and cull their numbers.
93000185-FameContents-.descFameUI: If the monsters tainted by darkness are not dealt with... only destruction awaits! Diligence is the only way to keep the world from falling into shadow.

93000186-FameContents-.name: Overextended
93000186-FameContents-.desc: The Green Hoods suffer from insufficient personnel, making the management of $map:02000038$, which is rather far from $map:02000076$, difficult. $npcName:11003536$ has requested that you help monitor the area.
93000186-FameContents-.descFameUI: No matter how meaning the Green Hoods are, they can only do so much on their own.

93000187-FameContents-.name: The Burdens of Leadership
93000187-FameContents-.desc: The guards are busy defending $map:02000001$, but the monsters nearby sure aren't making it easy. Teach the monsters at $map:02000088$ to leave the guards alone!
93000187-FameContents-.descFameUI: As a leader, $npcName:11003534$ worries about the soldiers under him. Help ease some of his burdens.

94000000-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: The Sky Fortress crew and officers take routine tests to ensure they're still fit for service. Do what $npcName:11004312$ asks and prove you have what it takes.
94000000-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Sky Fortress's crew goes through regular testing to ensure they're fit for duty. Show everyone you've still got what it takes!

94000001-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Search and Destroy
94000001-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
Kritias is filled with hostile machines, and the only way to keep them from threatening the Alliance expedition is to thin their ranks.

Defeat $npcNamePlural:25020001$ in $map:02020029$, $npcNamePlural:25020101$ in $map:02020030$, and $npcNamePlural:25020201$ in $map:02020031$.
94000001-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Gather data about mechanical foes in $map:02020029$, $map:02020030$, and $map:02020031$ through combat.

94000002-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Perseverance of the Alliance
94000002-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: The Sky Fortress crew and officers take routine tests to ensure they're still fit for service. Do what $npcName:11004312$ asks and prove you have what it takes.
94000002-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Sky Fortress's crew goes through regular testing to ensure they're fit for duty. Show everyone you've still got what it takes!

94000003-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Dropship Defense
94000003-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
The dropship you used to land in $map:02020029$ is being slowly torn apart by the local wildlife. 

Defend the dropship by defeating $npcNamePlural:25020001$, $npcNamePlural:25020002$, $npcNamePlural:25020003$, $npcNamePlural:25020004$, and $npcNamePlural:25020005$ in $map:02020029$.
94000003-Kritias_2018_12-.manual: Defend the dropship in $map:02020029$ by defeating nearby monsters
94000003-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Defend the dropship in $map:02020029$ by defeating nearby monsters.

94000004-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Dissecting the Problem
94000004-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
All manner of lifeforms inhabit Kritias—but are they a threat to the Alliance's work on the continent? There's only one way to find out!

Defeat $npcNamePlural:25020005$ in $map:02020029$, $npcNamePlural:25020105$ in $map:02020030$, and $npcNamePlural:25020205$ in $map:02020031$.
94000004-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: All manner of lifeforms inhabit Kritias—but are they a threat to the Alliance's work on the continent? In order to find out, you'll have to get your hands dirty.

94000005-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Daemon Deleted
94000005-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: Reports indicate the Daemon Army is cutting down trees in $map:02020029$ to build a military base. That cannot be allowed to happen. Defeat the $npcNamePlural:25020001$.
94000005-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: The Daemon Army's mechanical soldiers are stirring up trouble in $map:02020029$. It's time to thin the herd.

94000006-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Fauna Analysis: $item:61000153$
94000006-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004312$ wants you to capture docile monsters for research. Today's mission: capture $itemPlural:61000153$ in $map:02020029$.
94000006-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Help the Alliance research Kritias's fauna by capturing $itemPlural:61000153$ in $map:02020029$.

94000007-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Allies in Peril
94000007-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: The Tairen Kingdom is making a play for $map:02020030$, and Humanitas desperately needs your help mounting a defensive. Go to $map:02020030$ and defeat $npcNamePlural:25020101$.
94000007-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: The Tairen Kingdom is in the midst of delivering a surprise attack on $map:02020030$. Go there and assist Humanitas by defeating $npcNamePlural:25020101$.

94000008-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Robotics Research
94000008-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: Sky Fortress's R&D team is researching mechanical soldiers of Kritias, and have requested a particular component for study. Defeat $npcNamePlural:25020201$ in $map:02020031$ and gather $item:30001218$.

94000009-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Daemon Defense: $map:02020029$
94000009-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: Reports indicate the Daemon Army is cutting down trees in $map:02020029$ to build a military base. That cannot be allowed to happen. Defeat the $npcNamePlural:25020002$.

94000010-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: The Tairen Kingdom's machines continue to harass $map:02020030$, and Humanitas has requested your aid to address the situation. Go to $map:02020030$ and reduce the $npcNamePlural:25020102$'s numbers.
94000010-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: The Tairen Kingdom's machines continue to harass $map:02020030$. Go to $map:02020030$ and reduce the $npcNamePlural:25020102$'s numbers.

94000011-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
With supplies being a constant concern of operation in Kritias, $npcName:11003534$ suggests securing and restarting the mineral extractor at $map:02020031$. He proposes that the Alliance then trade those minerals to Humanitas for supplies. Much to your surprise, the Captain signed off on the operation.

Defeat $npcNamePlural:25020202$ in $map:02020031$ to secure the extraction equipment.
94000011-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Defeat $npcNamePlural:25020202$ to allow resource extraction to resume in $map:02020031$.

94000012-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Violent $npcNamePlural:25020003$
94000012-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: Sky Fortress's scientists are studying the aggression of the $npcName:25020003$. They hypothesize the crystals along its spine may be involved. Go to $map:02020029$, defeat $npcNamePlural:25020003$, and collect their $itemPlural:30001219$.
94000012-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Go to $map:02020029$, defeat $npcNamePlural:25020003$, and collect the $itemPlural:30001219$ on that grow from their spines.

94000013-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Tairen Aggression

94000013-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: The Tairen soldiers are attacking $map:02020030$. Move swiftly to aid Humanitas.

94000014-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Data Recovery

$npcName:11004312$ wants you to destroy the $npcNamePlural:25020203$ hacked by the Daemon Army and collect their $item:30001220$ to determine how the feat was achieved. 

Go to $map:02020031$ and get the job done.
94000014-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Collect $itemPlural:30001220$ from $npcNamePlural:25020203$ in $map:02020031$ to help determine how the machines were hacked by $npcName:11001813$.

94000018-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
The Sky Fortress expedition are in need of some much-deserved shore leave. And $map:02020001$ would be the perfect spot, if it weren't full of deadly monsters. The solution? Extermination!

Defeat $npcNamePlural:25020501$, $npcNamePlural:25020502$, $npcNamePlural:25020503$, $npcNamePlural:25020504$, $npcNamePlural:25020505$, $npcNamePlural:25020506$, and $npcNamePlural:25020507$ in $map:02020001$.

94000019-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Problematically Cute
94000019-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
The crew of the Sky Fortress have fallen sway to the $npcName:25020301$'s cute face, and are feeding the creatures their own rations. The time for diplomacy has long passed. It is time for a violent intervention.

Go to $map:02020006$ and reclaim the $itemPlural:30001221$ from the $npcNamePlural:25020301$.

94000020-Kritias_2018_12-.name: The World's Greatest Swordswoman
94000020-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
$npcName:11004312$ was excited to learn that there were sword-wielding robots in Kritias. Though she was eager to confront one and study its fighting style, she is unable to leave her post. That's where you come in! Study the machines' fighting style and relay what you learn to the Captain.

Go to $map:02020004$ and defeat $npcNamePlural:25020401$.
94000020-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Go to $map:02020004$ analyze the fighting style of the $npcNamePlural:25020401$'s through combat.

94000022-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Leafy Beatdown
94000022-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: The $npcNamePlural:25020502$ are hampering the exploration of $map:02020001$. Show them you won't stand for that sort of thing by delivering a much needed whooping.

The docile lifeforms of Kritias could prove valuable as livestock, pets, or beasts of burdens. But the only way to find out is to study them!

Go to $map:02020006$ and capture $itemPlural:61000157$.

94000026-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: $npcName:11004312$ wants to try a diplomatic approach with the $npcNamePlural:25020501$ in $map:02020001$.

94000028-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Collect $item:30001223$ in $map:02020006$ so that Sky Fortress can invent a cleaning solution to get rid of $npcName:25020303$ stench.

You've been assigned to destroy those mechs and collect $itemPlural:30001226$ to aid that research.
94000040-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: The Tairen $npcNamePlural:25021001$ in $map:02020016$ are surprisingly agile despite their heavy armor. Destroy the mechs and collect their parts for the Sky Fortress research team.

94000041-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Kharon forces have been kidnapping exiles to use for labor! Head out to $map:02020010$, fight off the $npcNamePlural:25020602$, and help as many people as you can.

94000042-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Weaken Tairen's defenses around the $map:02020034$ by destroying $npcNamePlural:25020802$, so Humanitas can take control of the facility.

94000043-Kritias_2018_12-.manual: Defeat $npcNamePlural:25020702$ at the $map:02020032$ and collect their $itemPlural:30001227$
94000043-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Defeat $npcNamePlural:25020702$ at the $map:02020032$ and collect their $itemPlural:30001227$, so the research team can begin studying them immediately.

94000044-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Go to $map:02020013$ and try talking to the $npcNamePlural:25020902$ there. If it doesn't pan out, you may need to employ more aggressive negotiation tactics.

94000056-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: The contamination oozing up from the ground has reached critical mass. Destroy $npcNamePlural:25021101$ in $map:02020051$ before they make it worse.

94000057-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: If the $npcNamePlural:25021402$ are left unchecked in the $map:02020014$ much longer, there won't be anything left of the beautiful refuge.

94000058-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Secret of Organizational Power

94000059-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Defend the Base
94000059-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: Humanitas took control of $map:02020033$, but they're about to lose it. The new $npcNamePlural:25021302[gender:0]$ are too strong to overcome. Help drive out as many as you can.
94000059-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: The $npcNamePlural:25021302$ are threatening to overtake $map:02020033$. You must help drive them out!

94000060-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Sky Fortress's crew goes through regular testing to ensure they're fit for duty. Show everyone you've still got what it takes!

94000130-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $map:02020051$ is a real problem, what with the deadly scrap robots and deadlier stench. Recently, it's the robots giving us trouble, attacking some of our people. They can hardly be expected to work under those conditions, so head to  $map:02020051$ and defeat $npcNamePlural:25021104$.
94000130-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: $npcNamePlural:25021104$ in $map:02020051$ are going after our people. Take them out before they take us out.

94000131-Kritias_2018_12-.name: She Can't Take Much More
94000131-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: So, you've heard that terrible noise out on the Sky Fortress deck. We've been afflicted with some kind of mechanical issue in our travels between Maple World and Kritias. Repairs will take more spare parts than we have, and the engineers say the $npcNamePlural:25021105$ can supply what we need. By dismantling them, of course. Defeat $npcNamePlural:25021105$ in $map:02020051$ and collect their parts.
94000131-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: If we're going to get the Sky Fortress ship-shape again, get us parts from $npcNamePlural:25021105$ in $map:02020051$.

94000132-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Defeat $npcName:25021405$ in $map:02020014$ to end the spread of the disease.

94000133-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Energy of Kritias: $map:02020017$

94000133-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: You're way ahead of $npcName:11004316$ for once. Savor this moment, and then collect aetherine from $map:02020017$.

94000213-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: $map:02020035$ has been occupied by the Daemon Army, and they're producing more mechanical warriors. Weaken the security forces to prepare for an assault on the factory.

94000286-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: Sky Fortress's researchers believe that monsters with a blue glow have aetherine in their bodies. $npcName:11004316$ wants you to look into this. Vivisect $npcNamePlural:25021101$ in $map:02020051$, $npcNamePlural:25021204$ in $map:02020017$, and $npcNamePlural:25021501$ in $map:02020003$.
94000286-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Conduct research on $npcNamePlural:25021101$ in $map:02020051$, $npcNamePlural:25021204$ in $map:02020017$, and $npcNamePlural:25021501$ in $map:02020003$.

94000287-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Inelegant Weapons
94000287-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004316$ thinks that swords are better than guns. Even so, he wants to know more about the gunslingers of Kritias, so defeat $npcNamePlural:25021103$ in $map:02020051$ and $npcNamePlural:25021407$ in $map:02020014$.
94000287-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Swords are better than guns. Also, defeat $npcNamePlural:25021103$ in $map:02020051$ and $npcNamePlural:25021407$ in $map:02020014$.

94000288-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Cutting the Line
94000288-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: Despite your best efforts, the alliance between Kharon and the Daemon Army goes strong. Cut the lines between them by defeating $npcNamePlural:25021904$ in $map:02020035$, $npcNamePlural:25022005$ in $map:02020036$, and $npcNamePlural:25021602$ in $map:02020009$.

94000289-Kritias_2018_12-.name: A Simple Conclusion
94000289-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004316$ has identified the Deamon Army as the greatest threat in Kritias. Defeat $npcNamePlural:25021903$ in $map:02020035$ and $npcNamePlural:25022001$ in $map:02020036$.
94000289-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Weaken the Daemon Army by defeating $npcNamePlural:25021903$ in $map:02020035$ and $npcNamePlural:25022001$ in $map:02020036$.

94000290-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Robot Bug Collections
94000290-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: The Lumiknights are exploring the many ways that Kritias differs from Maple World. They've grown interested with the strange robotic insects in $map:02020029$. Collect some insects from there.

94000291-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Secret of the Dark Crystals
94000291-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcNamePlural:25020104$ constantly appear in $map:02020030$ and $npcName:11004316$ doesn't know why. Go to $map:02020030$, investigate the dark crystals scattered all over the place, and collect some samples.

94000292-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Humanitas-ian Aid
94000292-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: The transmission tower in $map:02020030$ is being attacked by monsters. Repair the fence around the tower to prevent Humanitas from losing it.
94000292-Kritias_2018_12-.manual: Repair the fence near the tower in $map:02020030$
94000292-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Repair the fence near the transmission tower in $map:02020030$ to prevent monsters from approaching it.

94000293-Kritias_2018_12-.name: A Helping Hand
94000293-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: Sky Fortress's research team is overwhelmed, so $npcName:11004316$ has graciously offered your help. Examine the strange ore in $map:02020031$.
94000293-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Help the Sky Fortress research team by examining the strange ore in $map:02020031$.

94000294-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Waters of $map:02020001$
94000294-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004316$ is impressed by the diversity of life in Kritias. He placed some devices disguised as plants in $map:02020001$ and needs you to see if they've gathered any new data.
94000294-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Find out if the monitoring devices in $map:02020001$ have gathered any data.

94000295-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Ship's Maintenance
94000295-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: The ship has been anchored in $map:02020041$ for a long time. $npcName:11004316$ says that it's your turn to do regular maintenance.
94000295-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Perform repairs on the Sky Fortress while it's anchored in $map:02020041$.

94000296-Kritias_2018_12-.name: $itemPlural:30000232$ for Research
94000296-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $itemPlural:30000232$ grow in Kritias, too. $npcName:11004316$ is curious how it came to be there. Collect some for him for his "research."

94000297-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Local Remedies
94000297-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: In this war, there is never a shortage of injured soldiers. Because supply lines are stretched thin between Kritias and Maple World, you need to gather a local herb called $item:30001299$ to use for medicine. You can harvest it from $npcName:25020705$ in $map:02020032$.

94000298-Kritias_2018_12-.name: $map:52100112$
94000298-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: The Sky Fortress team managed to hack some enemy robots, but the robots are finicky and difficult to control. Go to the $map:52100112$ in $map:02020041$ and get an update from $npcName:11004522$.
94000298-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Go to the $map:52100112$ in $map:02020041$ and get an update from $npcName:11004522$.

94000299-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Poings of Rage
94000299-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: The rafflesia of $map:02020013$ emit a constant fog of poison, and it's making the $npcNamePlural:11004342$ very, very angry. Go to $map:02020013$ and pacify them.
94000299-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Go to $map:02020013$ and take care of the angry poings there.

94000300-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Cherry Blossoms for Someone
94000300-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004316$ has asked you to collect $item:30001300$ for him. It's not clear why he needs these blossoms, but you can find them in $map:02020014$.

94000301-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Silent Research
94000301-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: Understanding $map:02020014$ is critical to understanding Kritias, but Sky Fortress has lost contact with its researchers there. Head out and make sure they're safe.
94000301-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Go to $map:02020014$ and make sure the researchers are safe.

94000302-Kritias_2018_12-.name: What's in a Waspling
94000302-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: Even though they live throughout Kritias, wasplings aren't yet well understood by the Sky Fortress team. A researcher spotted would appears to be a brood of baby wasplings in the north of the $map:02020017$. Go back there and examine the baby bugs.
94000302-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Go to the north of the $map:02020017$ and examine baby wasplings.

94000303-Kritias_2018_12-.name: $map:02020018$'s Dew
94000303-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $map:02020018$ may be the highest region in all of Kritias and appears to be untouched by the technology that covers the rest of the continent. It is here that $item:30001301$ beads on the local plant life. Search these plants for this miraculous dew.

94000304-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Aetherine Botany
94000304-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: The plants of $map:02020037$ seem to have an unusually high level of aetherine. Head there and gather $itemPlural:30001302$ for $npcName:11004316$.
94000304-Kritias_2018_12-.manual: Examine the red plants in $map:02020037$ and collect $itemPlural:30001302$
94000304-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Examine the red plants in $map:02020037$ and gather $itemPlural:30001302$.

94000305-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Willing Investigator
94000305-Kritias_2018_12-.desc:
$npcName:11004315$ feels overwhelmed by her research on Kritias. Help her by gathering information on the $npcNamePlural:25020003$ in $map:02020029$, $npcNamePlural:25020103$ in $map:02020030$, and $npcNamePlural:25020203$ in $map:02020031$.

In this case, "gathering information" means "defeating," of course.
94000305-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Gather information on the $npcNamePlural:25020003$ in $map:02020029$, $npcNamePlural:25020103$ in $map:02020030$, and $npcNamePlural:25020203$ in $map:02020031$.

94000306-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Peculiar Foes
94000306-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004315$ never has enough data on the villains of Kritias! You volunteered to investigate the $npcNamePlural:25020101$ in $map:02020030$ and $npcNamePlural:25020201$ in $map:02020031$ to help Sky Fortress. Fight them and figure out what makes them unique.
94000306-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Fight $npcNamePlural:25020101$ in $map:02020030$ and $npcNamePlural:25020201$ in $map:02020031$ to learn what makes them special.

94000307-Kritias_2018_12-.name: No Time to Waste
94000307-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004315$ is worried about the frequent injuries to the agents sent to $map:02020004$, $map:02020001$, and $map:02020006$. Help $npcName:11004315$ by defeating $npcNamePlural:25020405$ in $map:02020004$, $npcNamePlural:25020502$ in $map:02020001$, and $npcNamePlural:25020303$ in $map:02020006$ who are giving her people trouble.
94000307-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Defeat $npcNamePlural:25020405$ in $map:02020004$, $npcNamePlural:25020502$ in $map:02020001$, and $npcNamePlural:25020303$ in $map:02020006$ to protect Sky Fortress's people.

94000308-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Her Hypothesis
94000308-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: It bothers $npcName:11004315$ that $npcName:11004316$ has been snooping on her research since arriving in Kritias. Now she wants help proving her hypothesis about blue monsters before her rival can swoop in. Study the $npcNamePlural:25020302$ in $map:02020006$ and $npcNamePlural:25020505$ in $map:02020001$.
94000308-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Prove $npcName:11004315$'s hypothesis by investigating $npcNamePlural:25020302$ in $map:02020006$ and $npcNamePlural:25020505$ in $map:02020001$.

94000309-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Systematic Investigation
94000309-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004315$ wants to bring some order to Sky Fortress's research strategy. Start by studying mechanical monsters with unique shapes. You can do this by fighting $npcNamePlural:25020605$ in $map:02020010$, $npcNamePlural:25020807$ in $map:02020034$, and $npcNamePlural:25021001$ in $map:02020016$.
94000309-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Gather data by fighting $npcNamePlural:25020605$ in $map:02020010$, $npcNamePlural:25020807$ in $map:02020034$, and $npcNamePlural:25021001$ in $map:02020016$.

94000310-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Poings Everywhere
94000310-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004315$ is in awe of the variety of monsters who call Kritias their home. She's particularly interested in $npcNamePlural:11004342$. Research them by hunting $npcNamePlural:25020704$ in $map:02020032$ and $npcNamePlural:25020905$ in $map:02020013$.

94000311-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Not Enough Data
94000311-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004315$ rolodex of monsters is missing critical details for certain species. Help fill in the gaps by fighting $npcNamePlural:25021102$ in $map:02020051$, $npcNamePlural:25021203$ in $map:02020017$, and $npcNamePlural:25021401$ in $map:02020014$.
94000311-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Gather data on $npcNamePlural:25021102$ in $map:02020051$, $npcNamePlural:25021203$ in $map:02020017$, and $npcNamePlural:25021401$ in $map:02020014$.

94000312-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Perfection
94000312-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004315$ rolodex of monsters is missing critical details for certain species. Help fill in the gaps by fighting $npcNamePlural:25021104$ in $map:02020051$ and $npcNamePlural:25021201$ in $map:02020017$.
94000312-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Gather information by defeating $npcNamePlural:25021104$ in $map:02020051$ and $npcNamePlural:25021201$ in $map:02020017$.

94000313-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Fearful Future
94000313-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: Sky Fortress is gathering data on the plant monsters of Kritias. It seems that Kharon and Tairen is plotting to use these monsters in their armies. Disrupt their plan by defeating $npcNamePlural:25021801$ in $map:02020008$, $npcNamePlural:25021603$ in $map:02020009$, and $npcNamePlural:25022101$ in $map:02020037$.
94000313-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Disrupt Tairen's plan by defeating $npcNamePlural:25021801$ in $map:02020008$, $npcNamePlural:25021603$ in $map:02020009$, and $npcNamePlural:25022101$ in $map:02020037$.

94000314-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Next Steps
94000314-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004315$ has identified the Daemon Army as a major threat. Keep them in check by defeating $npcNamePlural:25021901$ in $map:02020035$ and $npcNamePlural:25022002$ in $map:02020036$.
94000314-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Keep the Daemon Army in check by defeating $npcNamePlural:25021901$ in $map:02020035$ and $npcNamePlural:25022002$ in $map:02020036$.

94000315-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Rumors of Treasure
94000315-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004315$ wants you to look into a strange rumor. They say that whosoever can move the heart of the giant $npcName:11004342$ in $map:02020006$ will uncover a great treasure. Investigate this rumor.
94000315-Kritias_2018_12-.manual: Move the heart of the giant $npcName:11004342$ in $map:02020006$
94000315-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: They say that whosoever who can move the heart of the giant $npcName:11004342$ in $map:02020006$ will uncover a great treasure.

94000316-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Checking In
94000316-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: Sky Fortress deployed a squadron on a difficult mission in $map:02020031$, but they've lost contact. Travel there and check in on them.
94000316-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Check on the Sky Fortress agents in $map:02020031$.

94000317-Kritias_2018_12-.name: $map:02020034$ Rumor: Rings
94000317-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004315$ is researching the rumors of Kritias. They say that there's a machine in $map:02020034$ that summons a shiny ring in the sky. Head there and see if there's any truth to the rumor, then use a flying mount to go through the ring.
94000317-Kritias_2018_12-.manual: Use the mysterious device in $map:02020034$ and go through the shiny ring
94000317-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: There's a rumor about a shiny ring and a strange machine in $map:02020034$.

94000318-Kritias_2018_12-.name: $map:02020016$ Rumor: Blossoms
94000318-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004315$ heard a new rumor. Apparently there's a device in $map:02020016$ that makes flowers bloom! Head there and see if you can get the device to work.
94000318-Kritias_2018_12-.manual: Use the device in $map:02020016$ to make flowers bloom
94000318-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: See if there's really a machine in $map:02020016$ that makes flowers bloom.

94000319-Kritias_2018_12-.name: $map:02020032$ Rumor: Treasure Run
94000319-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: At the $map:02020032$, soldiers are reporting that adventurers are loitering around the binoculars, than taking off at full speed. What could be going on over there?
94000319-Kritias_2018_12-.manual: Find out why people are running in $map:02020032$
94000319-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Adventurers have been spotted running at full speed around the $map:02020032$. What could they possibly be running for?

94000320-Kritias_2018_12-.name: $map:02020014$ Rumor: Sky Garden
94000320-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004315$ heard a new rumor. It seems that there's a machine in $map:02020014$ that makes floating platforms appear. Head out and see if there's any truth to that.
94000320-Kritias_2018_12-.manual: Use the device in $map:02020014$ and climb the platforms
94000320-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: There's a rumor about floating platforms in $map:02020014$.

94000321-Kritias_2018_12-.name: $map:02020017$ Rumor: Rings
94000321-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004315$ is looking into rumors from Kritias. $map:02020017$ also has a device that summons shiny rings in the sky. You should check it out.
94000321-Kritias_2018_12-.manual: Use the mysterious device in $map:02020017$ and go through the shiny ring
94000321-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Go to $map:02020017$ and use the device to summon a shiny ring.

94000322-Kritias_2018_12-.name: $map:02020018$ Rumor: Sky Garden
94000322-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004315$ heard a rumor about floating platforms in $map:02020018$. Are these the same platforms from that other rumor? There's only one way to find out.
94000322-Kritias_2018_12-.manual: Use the device in $map:02020018$ and climb the platforms
94000322-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Go to $map:02020018$, operate a weird machine, and jump on floating platforms.

94000323-Kritias_2018_12-.name: $map:02020035$ Rumor: Rings
94000323-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: A scout witnessed a shiny ring in the sky near $map:02020035$. Head out there and check it out.
94000323-Kritias_2018_12-.manual: Use the mysterious device in $map:02020035$ and go through the shiny ring
94000323-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Go to $map:02020035$, use the mysterious device, and check out the shiny ring.

94000324-Kritias_2018_12-.name: $map:02020009$ Rumor: Guardian
94000324-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: The Sky Fortress team encountered a stubbornly stationary $npcName:11004342$ some time ago, and now another has been spotted in $map:02020009$. $npcName:11004315$ doesn't know what it's guarding, but she wants to find out.
94000324-Kritias_2018_12-.manual: Find out what the $npcName:11004342$ in $map:02020009$ is guarding
94000324-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: See what $npcName:11004342$ wants and give it freedom.

94000325-Kritias_2018_12-.name: $map:02020008$ Rumor: Blossoms
94000325-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: A familiar device has been spotted in $map:02020008$. According to rumors, it causes flowers to blossom on nearby trees. $npcName:11004315$ wants you to check it out.
94000325-Kritias_2018_12-.manual: Use the device in $map:02020008$ to make flowers bloom
94000325-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Go to $map:02020008$ and use the device to make the flowers bloom.

94000326-Kritias_2018_12-.name: $map:02020037$ Rumor: Blossoms
94000326-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: A familiar device has been spotted in $map:02020037$. According to rumors, it causes flowers to blossom on nearby trees. $npcName:11004315$ wants you to check it out.
94000326-Kritias_2018_12-.manual: Use the device in $map:02020037$ to make flowers bloom
94000326-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Go to $map:02020037$ and use the device to make the flowers bloom.

94000327-Kritias_2018_12-.name: $map:02020033$ Rumor: Treasure Run
94000327-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004315$ has an idea why some adventurers have been spotted zipping about certain areas of Kritias. She claims that there's a machine that causes treasure chests to appear. She heard about just such a machine in $map:02020033$ and wants you to check it out.
94000327-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Use the device in $map:02020033$, find the treasure chest, and open it.

94000328-Kritias_2018_12-.name: $map:02020036$ Rumor: Treasure Run
94000328-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: Treasure runners have been witnessed in $map:02020036$. Give it a go and report your findings to $npcName:11004315$.
94000328-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Go to $map:02020036$, use the device, and run for the treasure chest.

94000329-Kritias_2018_12-.name: Unidentified Researcher
94000329-Kritias_2018_12-.desc: $npcName:11004485$ is a Sky Fortress researcher in $map:02020009$. The problem is... $npcName:11004315$ doesn't know who he is or what he's researching. As a responsible head of research, she wants you to find out for her.
94000329-Kritias_2018_12-.descFameUI: Go to $map:02020009$ and find out what $npc:11004485$ is doing.

90000000-null-.name: A New Path
90000000-null-.desc: The large door behind $npcName:11000160$ in $map:02000001$'s leads to the $map:02000188$. You should find someone who has already walked the path of the you pursue to assist you with the job advancement.
90000000-null-.manual: Travel to the $map:02000188$ in $map:02000001$, and complete a job advancement.

90000417-null-.name: The Legacy of the Ancients
90000417-null-.manual: Enter the $map:52000016$|Investigate the situation at the $map:52000016$

90000419-null-.name: The Faithful Disciple
90000419-null-.desc:
$npcName:11001257$ told you that $npcName:11001229$ has departed for a place called $map:2000001$ in Victoria Island, and asked be patient while he prepares to teleport you there. 

$map:2000001$... $npcName:11001229$ said that someone important was there... Who could he be talking about? Utilize the power of  rune magic to teleport there, and find $npcName:11001229$.
90000419-null-.manual: Speak to $npcName:11001257$ at the $map:63000013$'s and teleport to $npcName:11001229$

90000420-null-.name: In the Blink of an Eye

90000430-Striker-.name: The Way of the Underworld
90000430-Striker-.desc:
$npc:11001618$, the godfather of the criminal underworld and boss of Blackstar, will grant you one request... provided you manage to best the champion of $map:63000020$ in combat.

The person who will direct you to $map:63000020$ is waiting just outside the corridor. Leave $map:63000015$ and speak with them.

90000431-Striker-.name: Into the Underground Passage
90000431-Striker-.desc:
You're supposed to meet someone named $npc:11001545$ in the underground passage to get you set up for your fight with the champion of $map:63000020$. 

Find $npc:11001545$ in $map:63000017$.

90000432-Striker-.name: Sewer Sanitation Service
90000432-Striker-.desc:
$npc:11001545$ was supposed to take you to $map:63000020$, but he's run into a problem with the $npcPlural:29000098$ that've come up from the sewers. 

He wants you to retrieve the $itemPlural:30000553$ that the $npcPlural:29000098$ have gobbled up.

90000433-Striker-.name: Fighter Registration
90000433-Striker-.desc:
$npc:11001545$ says he's too busy to take you where you're supposed to go and tells you to go on alone.

Find $npc:11001545$'s associate $npc:11001546$ in the $map:63000018$.

90000434-Striker-.name: Sting Like a Bee
90000434-Striker-.desc:
Still skeptical you are who you say, $npc:11001546$ tells you to warm up for your fight with the champion of $map:63000020$'s, $npc:11001547$ who is said to be extremely strong.

Humor him and warm up with a punching bag in the $map:63000018$.

90000435-Striker-.name: The Proof is in the Punching
90000435-Striker-.desc: $npc:11001546$ thinks you're taking this $map:63000020$ business way too lightly. Show him you know exactly what your doing by using $skill:11000001$ in front of him.

90000436-Striker-.name: Serious Chops
90000436-Striker-.desc:
Despite his apparent surprise, $npc:11001546$ tells you that your $skill:11000001$ is rookie stuff, and that you'll need a lot more to take down the Champ.

Perhaps you should show him your $skill:11000011$ technique?

90000437-Striker-.name: Meeting with the Boss
90000437-Striker-.desc:
While you're eager get all this over with, $npc:11001546$ says you match in $map:63000020$ won't start until $npc:11001623$ wants it to. 

Looks like it's time to visit $npc:11001623$ in the $map:63000019$.

90000438-Striker-.name: A Toast Between Friends
90000438-Striker-.desc:
Before your fight against the champion, $npc:11001623$ proposes a toast. You can't help but be skeptical, but in the end you decide to be a good guest.

See the $npc:11001624$ in $map:63000019$ and get your drink.
90000438-Striker-.manual: Order a drink from the $npc:11001624$ in $map:63000019$
90000438-Striker-.complete: Receive a drink from the $npc:11001624$ in $map:63000019$

90000439-Striker-.name: A Lesson in Trust
90000439-Striker-.desc:
After passing out in the middle of your fight, you learned the hard way that accepting drinks from suspicious characters like the crime boss $npc:11001629$ might not always be such a good idea.

Return to the $map:63000019$ and confront $npc:11001629$.

90000440-Striker-.name: Fair is Fair
90000440-Striker-.desc:
Exactly how things shook out this way is unclear, but you find yourself working for your worst enemy, $npc:11001629$. He's got a job for you, and it involves the Empress and $map:02000001$.

For the specifics of the job, speak with your handlers at the $map:63000023$.
90000440-Striker-.complete: Speak with your handlers at the $map:63000023$

90000441-Striker-.name: Lith Harbor
90000441-Striker-.desc:
It turns out your new handlers are $npc:11001545$ and $npc:11001546$ who you met inside Blackstar's headquarters.

According to $npcName:11001631$, the organization is planning to sell wares at the Empress's upcoming event for a boatload of cash, and it's your job to defend the shipment.

You don't like helping criminals, but right now it's hard to see another option. Get in the car and travel to $map:02000062$.

90000442-Striker-.name: Juice or Something
90000442-Striker-.desc: Well, you drank the beverage you got from the $npc:11001624$. You should check in with $npc:11001623$.
90000442-Striker-.manual: Tell $npc:11001629$ how you liked your drink
90000442-Striker-.complete: Tell $npc:11001629$ how you liked your drink

90000443-SoulBinder-.name: Mystical Jewel
90000443-SoulBinder-.manual: Take the training equipment from the showcase

90000445-SoulBinder-.name: A Strict Disciple's Guidance
90000445-SoulBinder-.manual: Go on top the pillar and train your sense of balance

90000446-SoulBinder-.name: The Practice of Animus, Standard Version
90000446-SoulBinder-.complete: Receive evaluation about your achievement of $skill:11100011$ from Brother $npcName:11001557$

90000447-SoulBinder-.name: Rapid Cohesion and Emission
90000447-SoulBinder-.complete: Receive evaluation about your achievement of $skill:11100041$ from Brother $npcName:11001557$

90000455-SoulBinder-.name: The Climb Down
90000455-SoulBinder-.desc:
The Guidance party, in pursuit of their Master's revelation, decided on the track to $map:02000001$ for their future plans after leaving behind a burnt Halo Mountain.
Before the dark shadows devour $map:63000030$ as well, hurry and head for $map:02000001$.

90000500-ContentsGuide01-.name: Cast Your Line
90000500-ContentsGuide01-.desc: $npc:11001861$, a fishing goods salesman on $map:52000058$, kindly gifts you a worn-down fishing pole and suggests that you give fishing a go while taking in the sites and smells of the island.

90000530-ContentsGuide01-.name: Music to My Ears
90000530-ContentsGuide01-.desc:
You stumbled across the $map:52000060$ by following an entrancing melody. Everyone within is hard at work practicing for the upcoming Moonlight Ensemble.

$npcName:11001866$ was kind enough to lend you an instrument and music score to practice with. Pick up the instrument and try playing it.
90000530-ContentsGuide01-.manual: Use the Music Score and play the Piano in the $map:52000060$

90000560-ContentsGuide01-.name: Homespun Fashion
90000560-ContentsGuide01-.desc: $npcName:11001176$ is the most prestigious designer in Maple World, and she's convinced she has got the perfect fashion for you. But can she really come up with an outfit that fits with your style?
90000560-ContentsGuide01-.manual: Use a template to design your own outfit

90000561-ContentsGuide01-.name: A Perfect Fit
90000561-ContentsGuide01-.desc: $npcName:11001176$ of $map:52000062$ won't acknowledge your talent for design until you model your new outfit for her.

90000562-ContentsGuide01-.name: Smile!
90000562-ContentsGuide01-.desc: $npcName:11001176$ of $map:52000062$ begrudgingly admits that you may have an eye for fashion. Speak to her for an introduction to the League of Fashionistas.

90000590-ContentsGuide01-.name: Handicraft 101
90000590-ContentsGuide01-.desc: $npc:11001867$ possesses a special talent when it comes to making charming Handicraft accessories! She welcomes you into the workshop, and offers you a free lesson in the art of Handicraft. Using the [Life Skill] menu on the bottom right of the screen, navigate to the [Life Skill > Craft > Handicraft] window and try crafting something.

90000600-ContentsGuide01-.name: Arts and Handicrafts
90000600-ContentsGuide01-.desc:
You run into $npcName:11001867$ at the $map:63000046$, where she
asks you to help her collect important materials to fulfill a special accessory order.

90000610-ContentsGuide01-.name: Girls, Interrupted
90000610-ContentsGuide01-.desc:
$npc:11001867$ was just about to head off to entrust her sister $npcName:11001871$ with an enchantment, when suddenly $npcName:11001871$ stormed in requesting an urgent Handicraft project.

$npcName:11001871$ is not satisfied to merely wait around while her sister works, and offers to enchant an item for you in the mean time.
90000610-ContentsGuide01-.manual: Entrust $npcName:11001871$ with an item to enchant

90000611-ContentsGuide01-.name: No Such Thing as a Free Enchant
90000611-ContentsGuide01-.desc: $npc:11001871$, who you met in the $map:52000057$, says she's ready and eager to enchant more items.

90000640-ContentsGuide01-.name: High Octane
90000640-ContentsGuide01-.desc:
You happened upon the $map:52000063$, where $npcName:11001873$ the inventor approached you with a request: test out his newest invention, a super-engine!

Since you've agreed to enter the race, you might as well win while you're at it, right?
90000640-ContentsGuide01-.manual: Race along the $map:52000063$ track to the specified location.

90000650-ContentsGuide01-.name: Getting High for Science
90000650-ContentsGuide01-.desc:
You ran into $npcName:11001873$ the inventor in $map:52000064$. According to him, he's put his super-engine research on hold to research aviation technology, and presents you with a $item:40400001$. Can you really entrust your life to a bunch of balloons?

Surely $npcName:11001873$ wouldn't ask you to test it if it weren't safe. Besides, you're an adventurer! Grab those balloon-strings tight, and don't let go! Soar through the sky to that building across the way.
90000650-ContentsGuide01-.manual: Follow the rainbow in $map:52000064$ and fly to the building on the other side

90000660-ContentsGuide01-.name: Furnishing Fundamentals
90000660-ContentsGuide01-.desc: $npcName:11000185$ has dispatched one of her associates to help bring a little flare to your empty house! Click the House icon on the bottom right of the screen, or press the shortcut key ([T] by default) to travel to your house. While inside your house, press the Furnishing shortcut key ([B] by default) to enter Furnishing Mode, then search for $item:50200094$ in the furniture list.

90000661-ContentsGuide01-.name: A Lesson in Product Placement
90000661-ContentsGuide01-.desc: $npc:11001876$ suggests that you purchase furnishings you find aesthetically pleasing, and place them in your humble abode. While inside your house, press the Furnishing mode shortcut key (B by default), then search for [$item:50200108$] from among the furnishings to proceed with the quest.

90000670-ContentsGuide01-.name: The Importance of Aesthetics
90000670-ContentsGuide01-.desc: $npc:11001876$ gifts you one $item:50200299$ and suggest that you try placing it inside your house. While inside your house, press the Furnishing mode shortcut key (B by default), then search for and place the $item:50200299$ in your home.

90000680-ContentsGuide01-.name: Classing Up the Joint
90000680-ContentsGuide01-.desc: $npc:11001876$ tells you your home looks gloomy, and suggests you liven the place up with the latest trends. While inside your home, press the shortcut key (B by default) to enter Furnishing Mode, then search for and place both the $item:50200300$ and $item:50200080$ in your home.

90000690-ContentsGuide01-.name: Feathered Friends
90000690-ContentsGuide01-.desc: $npcName:11001877$, who runs a livestock farm in the vicinity of $map:02000076$ says he will give you a free $item:50400159$ if you are willing to try your hand at raising some friendly fowl. While inside your house, press the Furnishing mode shortcut key (B by default), then search for $item:50400159$ in the Ranching section to proceed with the quest.

90000692-ContentsGuide01-.name: A Foul Harvest
90000692-ContentsGuide01-.desc:
$npcName:11001877$ tells you to groom the chickens from your $itemPlural:50400159$ and pluck any loose feathers.

Go near a [$item:50400159$] with a green hexagon and press the action key to harvest its byproducts.
90000692-ContentsGuide01-.manual: Attempt to harvest $itemPlural:33000026$ from the $item:50400159$ placed in your house

90000720-ContentsGuide01-.name: Go for the Guild
90000720-ContentsGuide01-.desc:
The Guild Registry  is an organization that supports the many guilds of Maple World and the adventurers who fill their ranks!

$npc:11003079$ urges you to join a guild to socialize with other adventurers and take advantage of the various benefits guilds have to offer.

On the bottom right side of the screen, open the Community menu (click the icon with the blue smiling face), open the Guild window, and search for guilds. You can apply to existing guilds or create your own!

If you've already applied to a guild, consider waiting for your application to be reviewed. If you're not the patient type, resubmit your application!
90000720-ContentsGuide01-.manual: Apply to a guild or create your own

90000730-ContentsGuide02-.name: Grade A Herb
90000730-ContentsGuide02-.desc: You meet a man named $npcName:11003140$ in the $map:63000052$ who cultivates ancient and endangered species of herbs. He suggests that you harvest some $itemPlural:33000166$ on your own and sample its unique scent.

90000760-ContentsGuide02-.name: A Gift from the Stars
90000760-ContentsGuide02-.desc: $npcName:11003142$, a mystical boy unexpectedly appears at your house! He says he wants to be your friend, and presents you with a gift.

90000762-ContentsGuide02-.name: A Joyful Harvest
90000762-ContentsGuide02-.desc: $npcName:11003142$, a mystical boy from beyond the stars unexpectedly appears at your house. He asks to harvest $item:33000118$ from the $item:50400191$ which he gifted you as an overture to friendship.
90000762-ContentsGuide02-.manual: Attempt to harvest $itemPlural:33000118$ from the $item:50400191$ placed in your house

90000790-ContentsGuide03-.name: Monster Taming 101
90000790-ContentsGuide03-.desc: $npc:11003505$ tells you to speak with $npc:11003507$ to learn about monster taming.

90000791-ContentsGuide03-.name: Monstrous Dietary Restrictions
90000791-ContentsGuide03-.desc: $npc:11003507$ says you need a special item to tame monsters: $item:63000000$. Luckily, she's already placed an order for some with $npc:11003508$. If you pick up her $item:30000882$ shipment for her, she'll share some with you.

90000792-ContentsGuide03-.name: Taming on an Empty Stomach
90000792-ContentsGuide03-.desc:
$npc:11003503$ says that you can tame hungry monsters by feeding them $itemPlural:63000000$, and suggests you give it a whirl.

You can find hungry $itemPlural:61000002$ in $map:63000056$,. as well as other locations. You can check the Pet Album to see where the monster can be found.

90000793-ContentsGuide03-.name: The Way of the Monster Tamer
90000793-ContentsGuide03-.desc: $npc:11003503$ tells you that monsters can be pacified for capture using $itemPlural:63100000$. For now, you should try crafting some.

90000794-ContentsGuide03-.name: Forced Adoption
90000794-ContentsGuide03-.desc:
$npc:11003503$ tells you to pacify the monster by feeding it $itemPlural:63000000$, and then use the $item:63100000$ to capture it.

In addition to $map:63000056$, you can find $itemPlural:61000002$ at the habitats listed on the monster's Pet Album page.

90000795-ContentsGuide03-.name: Empowering Your Pet
90000795-ContentsGuide03-.desc: $npc:11003510$ says that if you have several of the same pet, you can fuse them together to raise their experience. Try it by fusing $item:61000002$!
90000795-ContentsGuide03-.manual: Raise the $item:61000002$'s experience through pet fusion

90000007-SurvivalTutorial-.name: Welcome to $map:02000499$!
90000007-SurvivalTutorial-.desc: You've ventured to $map:02000499$, the biggest amusement park in Maple World. If you're going to succeed in Mushking Royale, you'd better start warming up. Go and take down the $npcName:29000403$!

90000008-SurvivalTutorial-.name: Onward to $map:02000499$
90000008-SurvivalTutorial-.desc: A gift is ready for you at $map:02000499$, the biggest amusement park in Maple World.

90000009-SurvivalTutorial-.name: Blowing Off Some Steam
90000009-SurvivalTutorial-.desc: Throw a bomb in $map:02000499$. It'll help relieve any stress you might have.
90000009-SurvivalTutorial-.manual: Speak with $npcName:11004210$|Throw a bomb from the training area
